SwVBnU-Qi7bhPadxbpBzpg.text: If your a soda fan, this is your place.  Must have 200 different kinds of bottled soda.  Fried veggies are fresh and hand battered, very good.   Burgers were decent, but patties seemed like they were previously frozen or maybe just overcooked.  They looked like preformed frozen patties.  Food came out pretty fast and pretty good price.  I would try it again if I wanted a quick fast food meal and a new variety of soda.

o9rwvMgIryE5Pj2j9jqbGQ.text: Love this place. Family owned feel with friendly staff. It's my family's favorite calorie splurge place. The burgers are amazing. We always leave stuffed.

Great variety of bottled sodas. Good seasoned fries. . Onion. Rings looked good will try those next time.  Always great to give a non big chain shop a good review, these guys earned it!

l4Pwr-ekI_08b3qBTtCabg.text: Get the garlic melt! It's amazing. The regular single is great too. The buttery buns really make the burgers.

2iBEoHpScYW_JREeZa2Dyw.text: I was skeptical of this place when my coworkers told me about it, but when I walked in for the first time and saw the wall of bottled sodas, I changed my mind.  They didn't even mention that!  Seriously, though, they have a lot of sodas.  A whole refrigerator full of root beers.  A row of birch beers, a couple rows of colas, a row of Faygo sodas, a couple rows of ginger ales/beers... Really, every soda you can think of besides spruce beer (I guess I'll still have to go to California to stock up on spruce beer).  Of course, this is also a burger place.  The burgers are fantastic, as long as you're not expecting a gourmet, 95% lean, thick patty $12 burger.  It is better than the Five Guys and Smashburgers of the world.  Try the New York burger (Pastrami, slaw, rocket sauce), the Santa Fe burger (bacon, fried green chili, rocket sauce), or the Baja burger (pico de gallo, bacon, rocket sauce I think).  Those are my personal favorites.  I have also had the gyro burger - pass on that one; the tzatziki sauce is great, but the gyro meat is probably the frozen variety.  They don't specialize in gyros here.  I pay this place a visit every week now.  The fact that their A/C doesn't seem to work well in the summer doesn't even dissuade me.  My biggest complaint is that they have a soda fountain.  People who prefer carbonated sugar water over delicious specialty sodas are simply not worthy - they're casting their pearls before swine.

3KtElSEUCBQFfkGDR1D2Cg.text: Such a great variety of sandwiches, burgers, hot dogs and SODAS! I usually always get two bottles of unique soda, one to drink and one for my collection at home

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Tons of sodas!

bZKGu4xS2zvFcV7LutMB9w.text: Wow! So a friend introduced me to this place and I have to say, I'm quite impressed.   My first time there, after perusing the menu, I got a single "gyro burger". It's as awesome as it sounds! My friend and I ordered two combos, a 6 pack of their awesome classic soda collection and some chili cheese fries.   The portions will fill ya'.   The owner is very friendly and quite helpful if you're new to the menu.   I loved "Pop the Soda Shop" and it moved all around AZ until, I guess they closed. I don't know if they merged or something, but they have everything they had there. All the sodas!   I'm introducing another friend of mine to the place next week! I can't recommend  it enough!

wVKWoDdm3a6O-9fqQzd6Dg.text: Greatest burgers, sandwiches, soda pop and zucchini fries but the French fries are disgusting. I'll never order there fries

OPDeG_-VjvxoCyqoG92omQ.text: Rocket Burger's teriyaki burger was 12 inches of messy, drippy, delicious madness. I probably used at least 10 napkins while eating that thing, but looking like a socially unacceptable slob was so worth it. It was huge, tasty, and took me from "hungry" to "omgwhydididothat" in no time. Rocket Burger is America.  In addition to selling ludicrously sized burgers, Rocket Burger also sports an impressive collection of specialty sodas. The vast walls of varied sodas more closely resembles the beer selection of a very-good liquor store, which alludes to the restaurants previous life as a bodega.   If you've got a 12 inch burger and a soda, then you most likely don't need a side dish, but for fellow Yelpers with monstrous appetites, their fresh-cut fries are wonderful. I haven't tried the onion rings or cheese curds yet, but I don't know if my body is ready just yet.   If you're suffering from an extreme calorie deficit or just wanna stuff your face like no one's looking, make Rocket Burger a priority.

GHUjBOelzHkavtNywr6D3Q.text: I absolutely love their crispy chicken salad! The chicken pieces are moist, delicious and flavorful.  The portion size is more than generous and it's just plain beautiful. If I can post a picture I will so you can see for yourself.

Tb3qfarfpqaaZcWpY58vIA.text: Good verifying of burgers... Tons of different ways to make a burger just the way you want it...tons and tons of soda options.. The place isn't all that ..it looks a little stand off ish but all's good.....a definite must

eNpdxE9DA2ELwXdBHzkRzg.text: 'There is no way we are going to finish all of this'   This is what we told ourselves we stared at the sizable amount of food placed in front of us.  What possessed us to order two double cheeseburgers, fries AND onion rings?  We wanted them. That is why.   I can see how easy it is to over-order at Rocket Burger. Everything looks good. Cheese fries with real cheese? Yes! Rocket (onion) Rings that magically and mysteriously aren't greasy? Yes! Tender, juicy burgers with lots o' cheese? Yes, Yes, Yes!   Rocket Burger isn't fancy. It isn't a 'dress to impress' destination. In fact, it appears that maybe once upon a time it was a convenience store. Coolers line one wall containing a fascinating assortment of beverages, including one whole section dedicated to root beer, and one drink the owner admits tastes like 'tree'. Really, tree. If you can't find it here, it probably doesn't exist!   The charm in Rocket Burger is that it isn't trying to be something it is not. In fact, you can see the whole open kitchen area behind the counter/cash register. It is simply good food, prepared and served by friendly owners and staff.   Oh and yes, we ate it all. :)

IKZhVIIZuB7G-iV2TXflSw.text: Onion rings are good. The breading is very light and salty. Most definitely Not heavy like other places.

LkFIkuhClFoBsMxI2JMxog.text: A few months ago I set out to find the best burger in town. I tried The Grind, Wineburger, and a couple of others but none can top Rocket Burger.  It was the best cheeseburger I have ever had, by a mile! I ordered a double cheeseburger with everything. The bun was toasty yet soft, the veggies were fresh, the meat was perfect, and the thousand island sauce was the icing on the cake. I had the fries and the onion rings as well. Both were just mediocre in my opinion. The beverage selection was huge and beyond awesome! If you are looking for a great burger at a great price look no further. No other burgers  can compare! I am going to have to work out harder because I plan on going back to eat there very often!  Went back today just to make sure it was going to be as good as the first time. I honestly could not believe a burger could be this good. Guess what? It was just as amazing the second time!!!

1kWkrpSwfKvG4XoePGrCOA.text: My first visit was last week. Good food and good prices. Had the burger and the wife had a sub. Both were very good. Good fries and rings as well.   If you order a "combo" you will get a HUGE basket of fries. Even my family (who loves to eat fries!) could share one order between two of us.  The interior needs a bit of TLC but these guys are just starting out and they are independent (which you have to love in our chain saturated restaurant).  The location is a bit ghetto but you don't need to pack heat. You do leave smelling like grease...so bring an extra shirt. :)  I really liked the huge selection of unique soda. The kids loved it too.  This was a really cool touch.  The owners are really friendly and nice and you just feel good supporting a local business. We need more restaurants like Rocket Burgers.  Keep up the good work guys!

9aRTqgpxrcdPoRWef7XDiA.text: This place is surely a blast from the past.  With the prices it's definitely a restaurant fit for the high school students located just a short walk down the street.  I wish there was a place like this near my high school back in my days.  Rocket Burger isn't just for the kids though.  If you're looking for some tastey food and don't want to pay much this a place worth stepping foot into.  The choice in beverages offered is also another reason alone to come here.  You name it, just about every non-alcoholic drink is in their wall of drinks.  If in the area I'd recommend stopping by.  If not for one of their burgers, subs, hot dogs, gyros, or corn dogs, maybe for a drink to cool off.  I can't wait to come back to the Rocket.

_KH_QH2-ybIr0dBzOuh-FQ.text: Definitely not somewhere to go if you are looking to eat healthy!  But it was so good!  I ordered the chicken teriyaki sandwich-and although it looked difficult to eat, I scarfed it down without a problem and without a mess!  Have some fun and try to find the craziest sodas amongst their giant selection!

nq7tQYAbMpFSZU9A600P8Q.text: When my fiance and I decided to go to Rocket Burger, I was extremely excited about it...she, being a vegetarian, was not.    We got there, and I'll admit, from the outside looking in, and even once inside the door, I was a little put off.  I wasn't sure I wanted to stay there and eat.  All that changed once we got a good dose of the service (and food)!    She ordered some pizza bread, with pretty much every non-meat topping available, and some cheese fries with no chili.  I ordered a Chicago dog with chili fries (no cheese).    We got a few drinks from their AMAZING soda selection.  She got two of the original Dr. Peppers, and I got a Leninade.  She ended up hating the Dr. Pepper because it used real sugar, and drank my Leninade...a taste of things to come once married I suspect.  The pizza bread, according to her, was delicious.  The fries, superb.    My dog was amazing.  I expected the actual hot dog to be a little bigger, but with all the things you get on the dog, it's a real meal.  I ate that, and some of the fries (which were really really good...though I should have gotten the chili cheese fries instead of just chili) and was stuffed.    The people that work there are very friendly.  They brought the food to us rather than just calling out our names, offered to exchange the unopened Dr. Pepper for something different since she didn't care for it, and had good humor when my fiance made a joke about them not having veggieburgers.    The only thing holding it back from being 5 stars is that the tables needed wiped off.

zjsRWUXUEIdVDS4bGigDXA.text: I'm going to go back.  If only to try a different soda.  Fantastic!  It honestly would be a 4.5 kind of place but I'm rounding up because of how quick the service was and the insane variety of sodas you can choose from.  it's basically the Total Wine of soda places.  I got some Leninade soda and it was delicious!  The wife got a grape soda that made you forget about any other grape soda you've ever had.  The food is great too.  I had the Santa Fe burger and it had a weird sweetness to it that I wasn't expecting (it had to be the pickles!) , and a very nice bun that absorbed everything the burger was throwing at it, and it was a lot (Good house sauce!).  Again, I will go back, and I will get root beer!

JV_YeA9h1Y1fCf6qrViRQw.text: It's hard to not give this a five and I may just end up doing so just to frustrate people that hate seeing perfect scores: Seriously I was skeptical but after what seems like a streak of  3 star reviews I finally have something good to report on the end of the food chain I can speak to:)   Is it the best chili cheese dog I've had? No.The best  chilli-cheese fries? No.Most extensive selection of sodas? Again no but truly this place adds up to more than the sum of its parts.It has nearly the best of all three  in one friendly, clean place that I'm looking forward to returning to.   Their Chili-cheese dog takes Sonic's to school and steals its lunch money. The texture of  fine ground meat  / amount makes it easy enough to eat and theirs actually has flavor in the chilli, you know  unlike every chain that tries to sell you the same thing.   When added to cheese and the  fries it was really great  though my preference is for fatter fries this was a great portion for the money.    Wife's  bare lettuce and meat burger was tasty with maybe a slightly enthusiastic shake of the seasonings  but to be fair if it was a fully dressed burger I bet it would be hard to tell.  Kid's Cheese burger ,oh yes, very very good and hopefully he appreciates now why we keep him away from that clown.     Really the choice is great, the soda's great,  friendly people that ask, and really seem to care, if you liked the food give this a 4.5   rounded to five.

hFxfo-wdxbTYa4AJGOUPqg.text: The burgers at this place are amazing! The different combos that are available create a burger that goes above and beyond, like the Reuburger, a combo of delicious burger and a reuben sandwich. The subs are pretty delectable, too. I helped my wife finish off a Philly Cheesesteak that hit the spot. Don't miss the mushrooms...a real treat! And talk about an incredible soda selection!    I did experience a small issue on a recent visit...a part of my order was left out, and a return to pick it up was required. I contacted one of the owners, Steve, who sets a very high standard for customer service. He went above and beyond to correct the small issue, demonstrating genuine concern for his customers and the quality of the product and care with which it is served. Don't wait to try this little local joint...I can't see how any self-respecting lover of excellent burgers could be disappointed with this gem!

Dzy8nJen2XBdP1htYFiHtg.text: Stopped in for a late lunch on a work day.  Friendly place, they weren't busy so the service was pretty quick.  Had a burger combo, really enjoyed the fries.  Should have had a double on the burger though.  If I'm in the area I'll eat there but I don't think it's going to be one of my "usuals".

WFsA355YtFZC596JxUO9Uw.text: Love this place! Burgers are great and you get a ridiculous amount of food with your combo meal! Plus you can't beat the selection of old fashioned sodas they have! A little hole in the wall but the place is very clean and the staff is always friendly. Burgers are to die for!! Definitely give it a shot!

_TPp3UbQVMtVljoNeq889A.text: We were in the area so we stopped in for lunch on Saturday. I had a regular cheeseburger and the BF had a regular chili cheeseburger. We shared a side of chili cheese fries and onion rings. That and two can sodas came out to about $14. Sweet deal! Food was good. The burger buns were good... (I think they make their own?), the meat was nicely cooked and it was tasty. The burgers come with shredded lettuce... normally I'm not a fan, but in this burger I didn't mind so much. The onion rings were coated with cornmeal and was nice and crispy. Not overcooked or undercooked, they were just right. The chili cheese fries was huge. That could be a meal on it's own and then some. Also, I liked the fact that they had gingerale =)  So, basically... it's a place to consider if you're in the area but I wouldn't make any special trips from Chandler for it. But I might just find excuses to go out this way just so I can eat here again ;) Oh and the people there were super nice and friendly!

dWbM6Ky_JHefTaGxVZCekA.text: AMAZING!! The burgers were perfectly cooked. We had the Cali Burger and the New Yorker. We shared half of each and neither one of us could decide which we liked better. Loved them both! Daughters had kids chicken fingers and they were actual chicken, not just mostly fried breading with little chicken. Girls also had milkshakes that were thick and full of flavor! The staff was extremely nice, helpful and had wonderful suggestions. Will come back many, many more times! Thank you Rocket Burger for a great dining experience!

szi2AXajAv-Whv6yyn2eNA.text: Yummy little dive in a strip mall. We got takeout from here- French dip sandwich, pastrami, and fried zucchini. It was yummy but wish the zucchini was cut in strips instead of rounds. They have every kind of soda you can think of so that's pretty cool as well.

6xer7Pwfcd9Pswr2K2FuWA.text: I like this place, a lot. It's right behind Church's Chicken at Cactus and 35th Ave. This used to be a run-down strip mall, and this particular store was "Latino Food Market" and looked terrible inside. The 2 owners renovated it and started it up as "Rocket Subs" before changing it to its current name. Now, it looks bright and inviting.  They have Hebrew National hot dogs and a vast selection of soda, including the Mexican variety. The BLT sub I had was also very good. I've not had a chance to try the burgers. I recommend checking this place out if you're in the area.

Must try if your craving a soda different from the normal selections offered.  But, they do have the standby soda selections available as well.  Stop in, burgers have some crazy combinations to try.

58yznvGGzMcK3KAHHEr05w.text: One of the best burgers I've ever had (Philly cheesesteak burger). Add a pumpkin pie soda and BAM, awesome lunch!

GtBgR5cf4w4gElv4P_xHRA.text: I love the variety of burgers, they are to die for , and they give you a yelp discount.The service is fast, and lots of drinks to choose from.I  went there one time on a friday, and some garage band was playing in the background. Not only did they suck, they were so loud, it was hard to even talk... Fortunately that has never happened again, or I swear, no matter how good the food I wouldn't go back....And I love rock a billy music.

B_rXnx7Z7_WQaABqpQSltw.text: Rocket Subs & More opened about three weeks ago. It's hidden away in the Church's Chicken plaza at 35th avenue and Cactus. The boy and I were on our way to another sub shop today when we drove by this sub place, we made a quick executive decision to go here instead and pulled in.  Walking in, there's the counter to order on your right, seating to the left, and cases of sodas and beverages along the back wall, with shelving for chips, corn nuts, etc. After some brief decision making, we decided to order a Rocket Dog combo meal (easy on the mustard and ketchup, with onions), and a Country Club sub, toasted.  Combo meals here are awesome, you get chips or fries and a drink from their first case (cans of your everyday soda brands), for a dollar more, you can select a soda or drink from one of the other cases - and that is where the fun begins. They had TONS of different brands and flavors of sodas to choose from. I chose a Mason's root beer in a super cute glass bottle, and the boy chose Pepsi (boo - boring choice!).  It took less than 5 minutes for our food to be brought out to us. The sub? Amazingly toasted goodness - eat your heart out, Quizno's! My hot dog and fries were also awesome. The fries were well seasoned and crunchy, the hot dog made perfectly to order. :)  The owner swung by our table and asked how everything was (awesome, thanks!) and he also shared that starting next week they will be serving hamburgers and cheeseburgers.  Overall, the food was awesome, the selection of drinks was great, and we will be back for more.  Last, but certainly not least - the price? Great! For two sodas, a huge sub, a hot dog, and a giant side of fries it came to $11.00! :)   Before leaving we also took some sodas for the road (Captain Eli's Ginger Beer, anyone?)

BCynqH7inr9WH60UjatDCA.text: Presentation is good. Beef patties/ burger meat had no flavor and patties are super thin--if used real burger meat and made own patties it would be better. Bacon used on burger was deep fat fried not pan fried and could tell by grease taste. Cheese looked yummy melted but again no taste--not real. Fries were way over-cooked and not seasoned with anything. Ranch dressing waa good for dipping condiment and tasted homemade. Fountain drinks were all low on flavor and just not good. My double bacon cheeseburger with fries and drink combo was $11.00 with a 10% off coupon. Not worth it. If they upgraded quality of food products served, I'd consider a return trip but not otherwise. You're seriously better off with a fast food chain burger combo. Sorry, keeping it real for real.

zpoBs8NNPqVKsBBERMONCw.text: I think this place qualifies as a dive. In a good way. Not much on decor and located behind a Church's Chicken which is very hard to find the restaurant.   if you are into different kind of sodas this is your heaven. Not only different kind of soda for display but to drink.  Had the Eddie Lopez Single Burger which was a burger with Pastrami. Was pretty good and a solid bun to hold the burger together.  The fries were on the soggy side which I personally prefer to be crisp.   The soda selection is second to none and really overwhelming but if you want to try something new and different this is the place.   Would like to come back to try a hot dog or a sub which both look great.   Overall come for the food and not the decor, this could easily be a candidate for diners drive ins and dives.  Good find and good food, I like these kind of unique places. Will be back again

JRhcDdjACPMN6plkP13TtQ.text: Delicious and fresh, my 2 favorite things when I'm trying a new restaurant. Friendly staff and we got our food pretty fast. Will definitely be coming back.

V08_MM5BbUWGEQYKQ2JGuw.text: Burgers suck, thin and dried meat, expensive as my four year old put it in and out has better burgers. The Great soda selection is the only saving grace.

ZnWvPTyOLx7cYGguyJOQaQ.text: Just driving by Rocket Burger, you don't think much of it. Looks like no frills, hole in the wall burger joint thrown into the cityscape with every other place but TRY IT! It's a cute little counter service burger/sandwich joint owned and operated by an adorable married couple.  Honestly the food is in my opinion an A- but the customer service and selection of menu items as well as beverages is outstanding. The burgers are really good. Not the best I've ever had, but for a modest price, very well worth the money. Their fries are well seasoned and come in big portion sizes too.  Warning: this won't be everyone's experience! ...but, on my fiancee and my first time through, the wife/co-owner ended up bringing us a sample of some of the sides we had asked about while ordering. Didn't charge us or tell us she was doing anything; just brought it out and told us to enjoy. So nice!   So the decor won't wow you and yeah you may find a slightly better gourmet burger somewhere else but this little gem is worth a visit for sure and I'll be going back!

iAfgEmddKfqN2OoHYu2eNg.text: This place is great! I ordered a burger combo with something they called the ghost pepper burger. Had some spicy cheese, bacon, and a few other things I don't really remember. Came with a large side of fries and a drink. The burger was great. I don't agree with other reviewers who said there is too much sauce. The sauce definitely dripped out, but the bun kept everything in place. The fries were cooked perfectly but could have used a bit more seasoning. Food came out very quickly.  The only thing I wasn't a huge fan of was the craft sodas. I didn't try any of the bottled sodas, but the craft fountain sodas were not my favorite. Still they also have standard sodas as well. So no worries there.  Will definitely be back. Used both the 10% off check in promotion and also got 10% cashback from yelp. After those, the meal is almost free!

cBb85UOkd-KPaPxi4-QJ6w.text: So happy to find a place where my friends and relatives can enjoy a delicious hamburger while I have the best vegetarian sandwich in town.Then, to top it off, there are great fries and an endless selection of pop to complete the meal. It takes me a while to decide which soda I'd like to try each time I'm there. The service is great and the employees are very curtious and helpful. I love this place.

PkI9Dzzsl-TgmMVKYnLI3A.text: Love this place.  Definitely my go to burger and fries place when I'm in need of a 5 star meal.  Prices are super reasonable, service is friendly enough, and they have an array of sodas from which to choose.  I've tried maybe 5 different burgers/sandwiches, and they've all been amazing.    Go out of your way to come here.

MwNuS3VBoK_8AbxfONomNw.text: I went to Rocket Burger this afternoon and got the single Ghost Burger. If you like something with a little kick this is the burger for you! The chipotle mayo, along with the Ghost cheese will have you feeling a little heat. The fries were delicious. I got a raspberry soda and wish I would have chosen a different one -- it was just weird tasting. The restaurant looks like a hole in the wall but was very clean with great staff.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Ghost Burger with fries and a raspberry soda

1kBj641_vS-8R0Z94EICyA.text: WOW.   Trust me when I say This place is the only place to go for a burger!  If you like onion rings some of the best.  Let's not talk about their Fried Zucchini or their Ranch Dressing because they are just as good.  Oh and did I forget to say that everything is made from scratch.  Another place to put on your bucket list!

XB_xbFMbcCxEnB7GF8ALIg.text: Priced right for great food. And the soda shop the have next door has a great selection along with good pricing.

PpzYxdtdH-QpyorRRwDX1Q.text: Wow! Great food and hundreds of pop choices too.  I had gyros and a unique root beer.  I highly recommend it!

7LApF4ts8D-oVOT5_RxzIg.text: Guys, I love this place! We found it on accident and I've been back 5 times!   Classic burger joint. The ambience is what you would expect. It's a burger joint! Come on!   Every single roll I've had was delicious, warm, and fresh. It was great!  If you love classic, real potato fries, this is your joint!   I had the cherry slush-puppy with a gyro burger and it was freakin' great! I was  expecting just gyro meat, and it was loaded with meat & a burger patty that was flavorful and moist!   The Philly is good, but we don't do green peppers, that's a Jersey thing! Get it right!   There was this WALL OF SODA. This place has every flavor and brand of soda out there! Try the cream sodas, the maple bacon, the butter scotch, so much!   Best part of the meal was the fried mushrooms. BEST. IN. THE. WORLD.  I've never had better. Seasoned to PERFECTION!   A little more expensive than average, but the food is above average so it's OK!

OVE5T-DklGS-qE-Nui_1sg.text: Picked up Waialua Hawaiian soda for my restrnt, and decided to have lunch there also. Previously had the double cheeseburger w/ bacon and fries was at least a five napkin lunch!!! Decided to try the New York burger today! What can I say but another winner!!! The pastrami was flavorful and the burger juicy! Cole slaw was spot on also. The owner was from Hawaii also Filipino descent very nice lady. Think this going to be my to go burger place. Prices are very reasonable for the high quality you are getting. Thank you Rocket Burger!!! Two thumbs up!

3GgpPo_iR5HLLbw9uPLWHA.text: My first time here.....I have not even eaten the food and I will already come back.  The people working here are amazing!!! They will help toy customize anything you want!   Also such a huge selection of soda!    The food was very good.   Juicy burgers, perfectly made.  Cheese curds were good and fries were nice and crispy.     We will come back here for sure!

YsBnZ-J5zQoPZeJSw7LxAg.text: I would give it zero stars if possible. I couldn't even eat my cheeseburger. The meat had no flavor whatsoever. Went with two other people. They said the same. For the amount of money they charge, save yours and go somewhere else. So disappointing.

WyfjkqoRxmmdDhIrvqNvWQ.text: Decent burgers not over priced like a lot of places but it also wasn't as good as a friend had led me to believe so I was slightly disappointed.

It was good enough that I'll be back to try them again eventually, just not anything to drive out of the way for anytime soon.

maek7BTGVsb6f0mTDLUrlA.text: I was excited to try this place based off of the reviews but in the end I was disappointed. It has a convenient store feel with a fast food place inside of it. If I go back it will only be to get drinks because of all the unique drink options that you can't find most place.

9PgVK4lRtm6NHMFKqMwKtA.text: The best burgers so far! Fresh, not salty. Cool place and super friendly peeps. We loved it and my boys are very selective and I'm done searching finally. It took 7 years.

xHM1hi8GMfeAsdpIw_8DHA.text: Hands down best burger I've had in a long time.  Ordered a garlic melt, very tasty! The service was great;  love the Soda selection too.

2Vs19jm2qbtWxUJjzk29lg.text: Favorite place to go to for a simple yet great burger and cheese fries! Oh and also a very unique option of beverages bottled up in all the refrigerators!!

TA6hEx7ewmSzb9H4PLJCWg.text: A couple of coworkers and I went to Rocket Burger for lunch today based on one of those coworkers' recommendation of the place.  The staff member who took my order was very nice and the food was ready within about five minutes which was nice. And the wall covered in different sodas from all over the place was pretty cool.  While I enjoyed the fries very much due to the seasoning I was only mildly impressed with the burger itself. I got a double bacon cheeseburger which I expected to enjoy and finish. There was something about the sauce though that I couldn't figure out and it ruined my experience.  I hate the fact that something like the flavor of the sauce has anything to do with my rating of the place, but it was something I couldn't get through and I couldn't finish my burger. I tried working through it, too. It just got to a point where o couldn't ignore it any longer and the aftertaste was no different.  Would I visit again? Most likely but I won't be going out of my way to do so.

j2Q9uQViFX6x-zY4fhacxg.text: This place is AWESOME!! I have been going here for years and they never dissapoint..their New Yorker sandwich is the best!! And they have really good burgers too..I moved to downtown Phoenix but I go back there because I can't get that sandwich anywhere else...I wish they had another location close to me

skJl6ScOfZZ86lhLIalNiQ.text: Came here yesterday because I was craving a burger. This is definitely a no frills type of place.  8 or so tables with order at the counter service (they'll bring your food to the table when it's ready). Settled on the Cali burger and a vanilla milkshake.  While I waited, I browsed what seemed to be an infinite number of bottled soda selections.  They were categorized by what appeared to be flavor so you can hone in on what you're in the mood for.  Both of the girls working the counter were extremely pleasant.  My food (to go) took about 7 minutes from the time I ordered it.  Total for the burger(single patty, no fries) and milkshake was about $9.50.  Got home and tore that burger apart.  Man, that was good.  I liked the Rocket Sauce that came on the burger.  Think a ketchup/mayo blend with a ton of pepper for kick.  I didn't even need to put ketchup on the burger.  The bacon was crisp (score!) and the avocado perfectly ripe. The buns they use are also on point.  Definitely more "sturdy" than a traditional bun (it reminded me of challah bread).   I saw a couple other burgers I'd like to try so I'll definitely come back and bring some friends along.

L4qADZL8O0RLv5fxFESYvQ.text: Mm this place is great. Kind servers, fast service, good food. My son spilled his drink, they were so understanding and nice about it. We had a good time while we were here. We will definitely come back n bring some friends! :)

9gbjRTi0wxnVsv_pxaSu3Q.text: It's okay but this place is a bit overrated for their food. Great select of soda though.   Hot dogs seem like they've been warming all day, fries are alright but are too thin to be over cooked. Chili is decent. The wall of soda is what makes this place unique.

388O-MnqmN-JZoUqQhjKGg.text: We went here for dinner tonight. Had the Chicago Dog and Fries. Steve had the Philly cheese steak sandwich and zucchini and a bottle of Dad's root beer. Loved everything. Will be going back soon. Good service and excellent food. Worth the drive.

lt6CWVQqpYzPJeOSqGpXXw.text: awesome place! took my parents while they were visiting phoenix. great food and even better sodas and prices!

siwIN1Xpe3bLbHK2meMqgg.text: Me and the hubby have been here twice now and everything was great! Service is very friendly, very mom and pop hamburger shop, very cool and great food!

19uwKw9lPSt1lKgbk-ob2g.text: This burger joint is amazing...  Very limited seating so be prepared to eat family style if necessary; it adds to the charm.  The beverage choices are amazing and the prices are ridiculously cheap.  It takes me almost an hour to get there from my house and they've never disappointed me.

1y5bpM2x6VcHH2ttX7I69w.text: Don't miss this place!!! My wife and I tried this place the other night and Im so glad we did. The burgers taste amazing and the chili cheese fries are to die for. The guys who run this place honestly care about their customers and want to make sure you leave absolutely happy. Prices are great and the food is even better. LOVE IT!!!

88PFCjD-4sgsIIuAwehdPg.text: A '94 Rocket myself, I heard a good buzz about this place from folks in the old 'hood.  I brought my two little burger critics with me as well (ages 10 and 12).  Lots of soda to choose from, great hamburgers, and delicious fries.  It beats the heck out of a chain burger place in quality and character.  I even ordered the "Rocket Burger" which is a ridiculous three-patty monstrosity on a 10-inch sub roll.  I was embarrassed in front of my kids because I couldn't even finish my fries.  Rocket Burger has the makings to be a classic joint, legendary if they can match Capin' Bills longevity!

VAV2hNbo7bW_peF9jUuyZQ.text: One phrase, SLUSH PUPPY! I've been looking for Slush Puppy in Arizona since I moved here.  Rocket Burger has it!!. Also they feature an modest selection of eclectic bottled sodas; root beer, sarsaparilla, blue etc.  Friendly & fast service, very casual atmosphere and cheap.  Had a basic burger and a bag of chips (sweet Maui onion)  $3.50. The burger was well seasoned, bun was toasted, served with a thousand islandy sauce.

QS2JAoIwj5juM9dGUR2Tlw.text: They have a HUGE choice of all kinds of bottled sodas and delicious homemade chili sauce. Their rocket sauce is outta this world and the shakes are bomb too. Definitely come here!

MoY_9WmabTiIW_xtMc6BKg.text: We decided to try this location after our favorite burger place was closed for the day.  I had a chicken sandwich and my husband had a burger.  The flavor of the sandwich was good, but I was disappointed that they didn't tell me it was a fried chicken breast.  My husband didn't care for the size of the bun compared to the size of hte patty.  The atmosphere was fun and service was quick.

Hky0WZPk5N5swcWL1b-DGw.text: I found this burger joint on yelp, being from out of town yelp is a big help. We missed this restaurant the first time it's tucked in an unassuming strip mall right next to a church's fried chix.  We almost did not go in it was not impressive looking , but because of all the positive reviews we sucked it up and gave it a try . I had the double Teri burger ( lett, Tom , onion mayo,and pineapple) usually when I have a teri burger I omit the pineapple, what the heck does pineapple have to do with teriyaki? I did not omit the pineapple because they dip it in cornmeal and fry it, crazy,but good . The sauce was a little to thin. The burger was very good even with the runny sauce. The fries were made in house and very good , large portion. The owner or manager? Very friendly. We will be back

yL7oLXQpxvf_k7i0LGGNaQ.text: Always phenomenal! It is always worth the 30 minute drive! Highly recommend the Mexican Burger

kljShqetBSBx-GLjFDTiDQ.text: Wow.  Plain and simple.  Wow.  The Eddie Lopez pastrami burger was pure Awesome and the fries they came with were a delight.  Came in because of the yelp reviews.  Our party of nine was pleased.  I recommend the blueberry Maine root soda and the Gale's rootbeer.  I am glad there is a place like this on the west side.  I am looking forward to my next visit.  Cheers to rocket burgers and subs!

xwmTQsPJqCeL1S_U0YKY_w.text: I have to admit, the burger disappointed me.  I had high hopes after reading reviews, but I didn't feel it lived up to the hype.  I got the $3.99 cheeseburger deal.  The saving grace of my lunch, besides the price, were the fries.  Skinny, salty, and just crispy enough, they truly made my day.  I enjoyed my In-N-Out burger far more, but Rocket fries are superior.

iVG7pNACxnH4_tfYwgj8mw.text: This place has some great deals on great food. The burgers are wonderful and the soda selection is amazing.

ecOVLIWfoFIFM9bWdN3FKg.text: This is quite literally the best burger I have ever eaten. The rocket bacon cheeseburger with 3 patties of meat on a 10 in. sesame sub roll and is nothing short of amazing. It could easily be shared. The cheese fries and onion rings are homemade. We love the casual environment and the huge selection of glass bottled soda. To top it off the prices are amazing! This is our first time here but we are hooked. We would love to see this place on Diners, Drive-In's and Dives, DDDinfo@mac.com, so if you love it here, nominate it!

H9vUAEYJJxI61qf-UTspJA.text: We've been here twice now and we love this place! Everything we have ordered has just been fantastic and we can't wait to go back again!  The rocket burger? Yum, yum, yum!!! The roast beef with the horseradish mayo on sourdough? Delish!!!!! Fries? Could they be any better?? The large greek salad (add a side of gyro for a $1?). Uh yes, please!!  Top off all that food, with great prices, more kinds of bottled soda than you can shake a stick at (including a Judge Wapner variety!), and super friendly staff --- we will be lifetime addicts! :-)

cCfW_F-bEENAL0bUYq09fw.text: Darn good burger n skinny fries!  Too bad and lucky so far for me. Driving friend to her car n found this place craving a burger....cool old time feel, great service...cheap!   If I'm ever on this side of town again.... I'll be back!

_GnhFcqPWg6CJrY5Dvtw9A.text: Great sandwiches! Skip the chains and get the REAL stuff here for less! HUGE selection of bottled sodas. Do not miss Rocket Burger & Subs!

tV_UuUi_WaHUtTDrHm0oWw.text: I would give it 4 stars if they would use the Air Conditioner.  With all of the soda combinations and solid burgers what's not to like.  It's hard to enjoy your food when it's so dang hot inside.  I will return when the temps come back down.

2yrMflNfw65CHIKMtSXSSA.text: How can I be craving a Rocket Burger Reuben and I have only had 3 in my life? That is how delish this place is! Went there for carryout today. The owners are super nice, as usual. When I got home, mu food was piping hot and YUMMY! I hope everyone in the Northern Phx area begins frequenting this semi hidden gem. The food is excellent and affordable and the service is the best!

p9K5LY0rueJYHVZkcanJLw.text: If you are looking for a place to get a great burger, this is that place.The burgers, fries, and customer service was excellent. Definitely will be coming back.

63asxK95ooc_NIUWbkxZDw.text: One of my favorite local burger spots. The owners are extremely nice and the array of sodas is actually pretty impressive. I've had burgers, chicken sandwichs, gyros and pretty much all the sides they have, I've never left not full.

7CRwTyODXNjKv6GW3IaL8A.text: Good food Great atmosphere Great customer service Brought back childhood memories with the sodas from the past  I will be back

fnRaYEsktGRyL9Hx26UQpw.text: The place is cool with all the vintage decor and sodas. But the food was terrible. I was recommended this place by a friend and I regret spending money here. I ordered my food to go..that was my 1st mistake. My 2nd mistake was not checking the food before I left. When I got home (I live 2 minutes up the road), I opened my food containers and saw my fries were 100% burnt. I couldn't even eat them and had to throw them away. My burger looked good. Key word: looked. When I picked up the burger, it fell apart because the bread was SO SOGGY. I had to take my first bite using a fork and knife. When I tried the burger, the meat was under cooked. I asked my fiance how his food was it and it was completely the same. Disappointed. Won't be back.

Ga4bB1ZEJu6IDTqK89znHA.text: Pretty good spot. Love that they have so many drinks available - that's the real reason for the stars. The food was just okay, nothing too exciting. We will be back again.

PxrllH9Ky_9f8-wvhONO9g.text: Great burgers and amazing soda pop selection! You can updgrade their sodas to make it a float! They also have slush puppies (slushie) in a bunch of flavors! Great place to bring kids or a fun date night! You can stop next door to Pop the Soda Shop to find an even bigger selection of bottled soda!

uHT6fkPC4gQpaMs0L8vsrw.text: My boyfriend and I have been coming to Rocket Burger for over 3 years now and let me tell you the food is soo good every time . We would literally come here every week to get the New York Burger. The owners are so sweet and they really take pride in their restaurant and it shows through the food, the sodas, and the service . The best burger we've ever had comes from right here at Rocket Burger! Cheers to many more burgers from Rocket Burger

AQfC1VA9EOUtuYE1PIFNWw.text: If you're reading this, this is your sign to eat here. Even if you think you're "not craving a burger right now", or you're "not hungry", you will be when you get there so don't pass this place up. This is hand down one of the best burger joints I have ever been to (and I've been to a lot). You will have a hard time choosing which burger to get, but I guarantee they are all good so don't sweat it too much. And if that doesn't sway you to go, how about a wall of soda? The entire back wall is a cooler full of all kinds of delicious sodas in probably every flavor known to man! lol. It took us a good 10/15 minutes just to pick one of those! You won't regret it though. The food is delicious and the prices are fair. Eat here once and you will have a hard time not going back. I promise.

qFtCO4bTH63fvKsVQMEW_A.text: This is a great neighborhood burger shop! Delicious burgers and one of our family's favorite spots! The soda wall is fun to look at as well.

WIzMWWofTAAbqs6A5djiOA.text: Items Ordered:  Double Bacon Cheeseburger; Crispy Fish Sandwich w/Coleslaw; Pick 2 sides  Total Bill:  Under $25  Quick Tips:      - Take a look at the soda wall before you order...there are hundreds of choices.      -  Buy yourself a four pack of soda when you leave.  They have a separate soda shop next to the restaurant.  Ok so this is our place for burgers and we drive all the way from the East Valley to get them.  Hands down, the best.  And not only the burgers.  We have had the hot dogs = great; the crispy fish = delicious; and the pastrami w/ coleslaw = AMAZING!  Everything they fry is awesome.    The one thing I would say could be improved is the onion rings.  The batter is not very thick and tends too be very crumbly when eating.  Still tastey though!  And the owners/cooks are awesome!  Always have a friendly word to share.

SSnIzpjUaRvFxeXJraUUJQ.text: Love me some Rocket Burger! As a family we usually go on a Saturday for lunch. I would give 5 stars but the parking is tight and recently there has been a storage container next to Church's Chicken which makes it even tighter.   My husband and I both usually get a bacon cheeseburger but this time I ventured outside my box and ordered the Thai chicken sandwich special. it came on the signature bun that is great and always fresh but never seems to hold up and at the end of the burger it falls apart..but I'm not complaining!  Sandwich was a real chicken breast breaded and fried with a spicy peanut sauce and a spicy slaw. Sandwich was amazing. Now I will be torn on what to order on future visits.  Hubs bacon burger is just that. A bacon burger, single patty with fresh customary burger toppings. Fries are always hot and freshly cut.  We also love the hundreds of bottled soda collection but find it a little pricey at $1.99 a bottle.  Rocket Burger is a great break from chain burgers and blows  most of them out of the water. Be prepared during busy times to wait for a table or clean your own.

o0WKWoJZaFxLRL5X8yhS_w.text: First off this place is not 5 stars by any means.  For all of you that did give 5 stars you need to get you taste buds checked.  5 stars is for greatness.  What I do like about the restaurant is the soda selections.  This is by far the biggest selling point of the restaurant.  My kids love coming here just so they can pick a new bottled soda to try.   I have ate hear twice.  The first time I got the Italian sub while the kids got hamburgers.   The kids said "meh" to the hamburgers and that is about how I felt with the sandwich.    The second time this place smelled in the inside.  Its that smell of rancid oil.  That smell tells you that the fryers are not clean and makes it questionable.   I would go back to Rocket Burger but just to buy the soda.

iE692QzgMgxcDDG7pkSLHw.text: Always a great spot to grab lunch. Never disappointed! I love the Mexican dog . And when you see all of the bottles of soda you will be amazed. So come and check this place out.

Q0zMPNwHd5imL59TpdbyBg.text: This place has the ability to be the best burger place in town. It has all the trimmings; uniqueness, quality products, and in a really badly managed strip mall. My first visit-everything was salty, like mouth bomb salty. In my second visit- l found that the burger was good but the fries were insanely salty. I'm not sure if maybe I went on two off days or the cook is very liberal with their use of seasoning.

iQ3LVul-vtdh9g8XEgIlNw.text: Burgers are super tasty. We will be back often. And we live in Scottsdale. We were here two weeks ago and were back today. That's how much we like this place. Seriously the burgers are amazing. My husband and I definitely recommend this place. Try it, you'll like it!!!!

5N1qkEbsCJP0rwoGU4gH-Q.text: Their cheese curds and burgers are great! Loved that they carried the energy drink bawls. I also had the turkey avocado sandwich and it was fresh pulled turkey.

8qJhHvZlR1lrWSGELaBuew.text: Good burgers, good sandwiches, and about 300 different kinds of sodas. What more can you ask for?

z5c3bn91Zbb_8IxOWeUOJg.text: Came in on 6/19 for lunch. My buddy was hyping this place up, so we came here.  The staff was very friendly and helpful with the menu. But, the prices are a little pricey for the size and quality of the food.  I ordered the Afterburner burger (single patty) with ghost pepper infused cheese and an order of zucchini. Along with the drink, it came out to just over $14. And to be honest, it wasn't worth it as I was expecting a decent kick from the jalapenos and ghost pepper cheese. The jalapenos were not even close to spicy and the cheese did provide a hint of spice. It also had this rocket sauce (I think that's what it was called) and I'm not sure what it was trying to do. It had no flavor. Then, I saw the patty and it was pretty sad as it looked like one of those frozen patties from those commercials. So the burger I rated as a 1 out of 5 stars. Then we had the fried zucchini and they were pretty good. I think they used corn dog breading and it was tasty. So those I'll rate at 4 out of 5 stars.  I'm pretty sure I wouldn't recommend this place for the burgers, but good thing they offer a good variety of other items. They also have a ton of different soda to choose from. Hell! They have root beer on tap.

_suoqw0Jvpj_n15VIEyqHQ.text: Great selection of every kind of bottled soda.  Had the country sub and it was tasty but the marble rye was a little dry.  Staff as friendly.  It's not special inside.

SXbUu1D9BQF7tjYqym2qUQ.text: They have a huge selection of burgers to choose from. But the chicken and fish are awesome as well. Plus they have a huge selection of sodas and ice cream. Great little out of the way place.

mi_X_qvxN6RAB_crpl3UDg.text: My hubby and I were jonesing for a burger. First thought was Lenny's, but of course I had to yelp and came across rocket burger. I was so excited to try this place out after reading the reviews. My mouth was watering. The plethora of nostalgic drinks, the hole in the wall atmosphere, ice cream, french fries, and burgers.  Sounds like a carb coma made of dreams. I first grabbed a cold cream soda in a bottle made with cane sugar from the refrigerator. Yum, my favorite! Starting off great..... I tried the french fries next which were hot and fresh. While they weren't crispy, I liked the seasoning and they were good. Saving the best for last, I took a ginormous bite of my New York burger. Pastrami, swiss cheese, and coleslaw on a burger.  Sounds like heaven right? Wrong! First, the bun to ingredient ratio was off. The bun was more substantial than the meat and other ingredients or lack there of.  Very lackluster in flavor and somehow wet and dry at the same time. The rocket sauce which soaked my burger was not my cup of tea. It was a watered down mayo that was sweet with a hint of vinegar and other flavors I couldn't put my finger on. It was weird tasting to say the least. My husband who doesn't have much of a palate went as far as to say it was gross. Both our burgers were heavy and dry.  He got a regular bacon cheeseburger. Can't go wrong with an original. Apparently not in his case. He was so grossed out by the soggy scrapping of lettuce and over abundance of chopped onions soaked in rocket sauce that he scrapped off everything and ate only the burger patty as there was only a crumbling of bacon. The worst part of the whole experience was my hubby's look of severe disappointment and the all knowing "I told you so," followed by "I wished we would've just gone to Lenny's." I know everyone has their own ideas on what's good and what isn't, or maybe it was an off night, but it was the first time the yelp reviews didn't match my expectations.  In fact my culinary experience was the polar opposite. So disappointing To end on a good note, the cream soda in the bottle was the highlight of my meal as well as the nice staff. The person taking my order was really nice and the lady that brought over our food was pleasant as well.

26qe3S0RVw_qDN-G4Y1SxQ.text: This is definitely the best burger joint in town! All bottled soda you could ever dream of, in fact the largest selection in Phoenix I believe. Portion sizes are great too! I would recommend everything on the menu as I have tried most of it.

zhErTrYU_yP6mf3DEt1bXg.text: Awesome food! Sooooooo many hamburger combinations, my favorite is the Teriyaki burger, shoestring ff...and every brand of soda you can think of....

RHfdHB2HqcGQsjFCyvhKdQ.text: I've actually visited Rocket Burger for several times already. One word that I can describe their service is it is CONSISTENTLY GOOD. I've tried other burger joints but they simply don't get it that when I say "well done", I mean "well done".   Anyway, my fave is their Bacon Cheeseburger and their Philly Burger (hey, I'm a burger guy!). Meat is fresh and is cooked very well. The cheese properly melted making every bite a sumptuous rush. Will be back for more my friends!

2A0g5kg2PkrEfhVFLO_CGw.text: Gone to this place a few times and its been good. ( see past review ) decided to go tonight to try the rocket burger... Well lets just say I was highly disappointed tonight. I ordered online and my large burger was supposed to be nice and long sub style. Well instead the chopped it in half and threw it in a box. So much philly cheese steak cheese and peppers that i couldnt even taste the actual burger. It was flowing off the sides. I couldnt even pick it up with my hands. Literally. That gets me to the next point. It was so covered in junk that the bottom bread was literally soaking wet. Mostly grease from what I can tell. Absolutely not edible. Presentation on this burger was literally 0. I mean... I had to use a fork. Greasy toppings with hardly any bun. So our next item was a large cheese curd. It came in tinfoil in a to go box and was extremely greasy. The top looked presentable but the bottom was covered in grease. Let it sit hanging in the fryer longer next time! Disgusting. After just a half of my burger and 3 cheese curds I was feeling quite ill. Not food poisoning type sickness but certainly queasy probably from all the grease I just ingested. Honestly, I don't think ill be back. What a shame.  Pictures posted. There is actually a burger and some bun somewhere under all those toppings.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. And the soggy bread on the bottom. Tore in half to see consistency of wetness. Disgusting.
Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Flash on for grease visibility... Again 2 halfs of a bun are somewhere underneath all that junk.
Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Grease on cheese curds. These suckers were chewy

1tPnmE_eyF5jw1-ol29eZw.text: Never A disappointment when I come here. Vast variety of burgers and Sodas there is something for everyone.

f1arDSRCQI89-J8WY1OVWA.text: This is an easy to miss/pass up local...which I stopped to check out a few years ago and am so glad I did. It is locally owned and operated. They have a standard menu and a rotated special.  The most obvious thing they sport is the vast selection of boutique sodas.  The food is fresh, ex, the fish is hand battered--in their own kitchen. The buns are very good, solid enough to hold up under all the marvelous stuff they put in their burger/sandwiches but soft with a nice bite/texture.  Back to the sodas...I think that it would be a very fun thing for a group of friends to gather and have a soda tasting event. It could event be a MeetUp. I do not want to even start listing the selection--just visit and take a look for yourself.  Finally, I have always been served by the same pleasant gentleman all the years I've been going there. Consistency, is something I value.

oQloYXl0IJsTGp1cfH8MWA.text: I heard about this place by watching Check Please. We finally got to get there, today. It's such a cute little place. Almost, back in time. I ordered the single Cali burger, it had bacon, avocado cheese and the usually fixings. It was good but way too greasy for my stomach to consume. The onion rings were so-so.  Greasy and a little over fried. The service was exceptional. The gals were so friendly. I wouldn't return, but I think one should give it a try, maybe your stomach is stronger than mine!

QhTHI9nVLaZa-oYptdZGuQ.text: Best place ever to go eat. They prep everything there, home make all sauces and salad prep and it's absolutely delicious! Their California Club is absolutely delicious and outstanding! Their burgers are to die for! 12/10 would recommend.

kchhl9R2Pvyonaz71Ud6Ww.text: A good place for satisfyingly indulgent bad for you, but oh so good foods. New Yorker burger is great. Remember to grab napkins before you leave! They put rocket sauce and their special coleslaw on many of their items. Both are delicious , but make for a messy experience. We also love the mini corn dogs. Large portions of everything, especially the fries (one side is totally enough for 2 adults). They have every soda you could ever want, even faygo which is hard to find outside of Michigan. They've also added taps with craft soda. Cool place, not for those on a diet lol :D

g4eO4RcEmXgxE0hQQ9LsMA.text: There is a big hype about this place, but...my gf and I ordered each of us a burger, after moving. Was looking forward to the delicious food. We watched a video review about them on "Check Please, Arizona" great reviews. Ugh. I would easily say I'm a foodie, and know what food should taste like. I got my "burger" the New Yorker, which was highly recommended by the show and by the cashier. The pastrami was fresh, their coleslaw was okay, the burger wasn't even cooked and it wasn't  2 cm thick. And it was worse than a few fast food burgers. Ugh!! Then, when you walk into the place, it looks like a grocery store. Not real inviting. The wall of different soda pops was cool, but way over rated! I will never go back to this place. Not good enough food to retry! Sorry, just my opinion.

e4TQju_hm8OVtcBISw8UCg.text: Awesome Burger joint. The best soda varieties in town!!! All the employees were fast and efficient.

KTQd1uhDeRBGY7KaAFsFVw.text: My husband I love coming to rocket burger. The afterburner chicken sandwich is so yummy! The service is fantastic & the sodas never let us down!

3dZKkEMtm-bLjkLrNfxnMw.text: Rocket Burger is a fun place to go for lunch and the food is excellent!  My favorite so far is their Philly Burger.  The double size is only $6.99 and is very filling. It's topped with grilled green peppers and onions, along with provolone cheese and mayonnaise. Another good sandwich is their California Club.  It comes with Turkey breast, tomato, avocado, sprouts, cheese and mayonnaise.  It's on whole wheat sub that only costs $6.69. Both are great!  I've also had their roast beef sub.  It has roasted peppers, provolone, and yummy horseradish mayonnaise, along with lettuce and tomatoes for $6.69.  If you are seeing a trend on prices here, that's because all of their medium sandwich or double hamburgers are $6.69. But, they do have smaller sizes which start at $4.49.  One of the most cool and impressive things about Rocket Burger is their assortment soft drinks bottles in their refrigerated case behind where you sit. They say it's over three hundred. Have you ever had a Judge Wapner root beer? How about a Dad's Cream Soda, maybe Grape Nehi, Royal Crown? It's impressive that's for sure.  My friends, Arlin B and Rand H have written glowingly about their sandwiches. But the best line comes from Arlin regarding their double burger pastrami.  He says: "It was a mouth watering double burger that came with Hot Pastrami stacked on top of the two patties covered in melty-cheesy goodness, toppings and their thousand island dressing.  It was FANTASTIC!!"   Got the visual image? Good. Enjoy!

mgTxgqWUeZBGokcoivMKhA.text: I just had a rocket-sized bacon cheeseburger and soda float from Rocket Burgers & Subs. They were both absolutely delicious! This is a great place to dine and order food from. They have an amazing array of soda flavors. The staff is awesome with great customer service. Make sure you check out their menu.

MeK-FmRZs3FPrPJyKTA3cQ.text: I'm not sure as to the reason behind the high rating for this organization, but IMHO, the food was fairly average. A letter grade of C-.  The fries had a sweet aftertaste, which for not being sweet potato fries was strange. The portion for the standard combo fries is rather large and would have been a plus if not for their sweetness. The burger itself was not particularly memorable, with its blending of flavors advertised (gyro double burger) into one creamy greesy taste. The soda choices however are large and encompassing so I'd your not a fan of Pepsi products, you've got choices.   P. S. An item that did concern me was the cooks decision to take their smoke break at the kitchen door at front of the store. Eye contact was made along with a wiff of Tabacco when I walked in, followed by the uneasiness of watching the same cook enter the kitchen area while I was placing my order. I will not speculate if the cook had washed their hands or not, or whether they were the only cook on duty, but there was no sink in view of the front counter that was used upon their re-entry.

TL2rf9Nd3iiJb-jlfR98KQ.text: After reading tons of reviews on this place, and considering its right up the street, I decided to give it a try. The soda selection was awesome but the food was just ok. The burger bun was twice the size of my double burger patties, although the bread was yummy. The sauce was way too sweet for my liking and tasted exactly like coleslaw dressing, and the bacon, instead of being nice crisp strips, it was chopped up burnt little scraps. The cheese fries were just ok too. I usually am a big fan of thin cut extra browned french fries but these had very little flavor, and zero salt. Fries should be salted as soon as they come out of the fryer while they are still wet or else the salt will never stick... Lastly, the older gentleman who took my order kind of seemed inconvenienced by having to take my order, which is a very uncomfortable feeing.  None of the food I ordered today was bad, it just wasnt all that great. I will probably be back to try a sub and some onion rings. Maybe I can give them a better review next time.

Mmn61k5zh5-UMRbVLdFKzw.text: Great service. Menu is huge. Got a bacon cheeseburger single. Definitely recommend getting onion rings. Best I've ever had. French fries reminded me of what my dad would make when I was a kid. Even the brownie was delicious. Just all around great place to eat.

GFpvoNnYUWRkPoWCLPZvPw.text: Well thanks to Yelp I found another local hidden gem. Specifically in the west side! I had no idea about this place but was in the area and was hungry and wanted something that wasn't a chain. Well Rocket was just the answer. Located in a small run down strip mall I wouldn't have expected such a good place. I was on the run so I ordered the open faced  Big Dipper to go. I really liked how even though it was to go they included a large Cup of an jus to dip my sandwich in. After the sub I was very satisfied.   As mentioned in other reviews they have a large selection of sodas to drink for sale. I really wasn't in the mood for a soda or I would have tried one.   I'd like to come back to try more sandwiches and a burger. I was impressed with the friendliness of the staff and value and quality of my sandwich. I'm so glad for Yelp for introducing me Rockets, I will make my way back here sometime soon!

33NncIqhXSKb8YSXqyHjcA.text: Excellent. Truly excellent. Rocket Burger has a huge menu with very creative burger concoctions, subs, sides and more. Ive only had the burgers, becasue they're SOO GOOD and I cant get anything else (yet) however, the subs that ive seen others get are massive, and look delicious. They make everything fresh and its obvious. Workers are polite and quick. Place is clean, not very big but it works. Now, the soda selection. Holy moly. They have any soda you can think of, and theres more at the "Pop shop" right next door. Pepsi and another craft soda that im not familiar with on fountain, and EVERYTHING else in bottles. All in all, great experience. One of my favorite hole in the walls in phoenix. Would recommend to anyone and everyone who loves a good burger and a cold soda.

XjWJJwpqOtE373pGkwdA9Q.text: I love this place !!!!! Living in cali im still to find good philly cheese steak out there and trust i have looked  . I will gladly drive 4.5 hours just for a good meal ...... thanks for the best philly cheese steak in the west !!!!

D9n0JmyUaev4gXtZEvV1uw.text: Honestly best all around burger joint in central / N phoenix. Menu is stacked with amazing burgers and selections great dynamics to have for building such a juicy burger. they craft in house soda with cane sugar, fries are amazing, bottle soda selection is amazing. make sure to check into the specials on hand also, props to Rocket Burger keep it up!

iAp1LVLwgSjammWpy62GqQ.text: I have been in so many times since the time of my initial review that I had to write an update. It has been awesome every time. The fries, still deep fried awesomeness!  There soda selection is always growing and if you get a chance you have to try; The Flying Cauldron "non-alcoholic" Butterscotch Beer.. If you tell other people that you 'like' butterscotch so they don't think you're weird, this is your dream soda. Whenever I go I buy two because the 1st one I inhale and the 2nd one I actually drink slow enough to enjoy..;-)  I realize that I have never mentioned the service which has always been the "no-brainer" part of deciding if I want to eat at Rocket Burger. There are those places you love to eat, but wish you could get someone to go get it for you "You know 'cause the food's great but.." and the 'but' is not wanting to have to actually go there.   This is not one of those places..I swear on my bones. :-)

lPFWzVHfS-kqH3luvbxQew.text: Wowza!  This place is AMAZING!  Thanks to Paul V. I was able to try Rocket Burger many times and every time has been fantastic.  I had the Bacon double cheeseburger  with fries or cheese curds and it's so delicious.  The burger is greasy, cheesy, and has lots of bacon.  Ya can't go wrong!  The french fries are also good, especially the cheese fries.    Paul has ordered take out from here for me quite often as well.  The cheese curds get a bit mushy if not eaten right away so go with french fries if you have take out.    Whether you eat in or get take out the food is awesome!

c73V37sRP_p9y92f_xAftw.text: I love me a good burger and I was excited to check this place out.  Unfortunately their burger left me feeling queasy, it was just too much grease.  The service was friendly and I bought some tasty sodas but not enough to bring me back again.

xADMDjdIR8AFC7sx6c669g.text: I saw the place thinking it was going to be an average burger spot. The place from the outside is not the best. I got the Santa Fe and got my woman the afterburner burger. Wow they where delicious  Better IMO than in and out, five guys and smash burger Burgers is good , toasty bun fresh ingredients  Loved it will be going here instead of the other places

bIpun8iJGZfISfht2qH9eg.text: It may not be health food but it sure is tasty! The burgers are yummy and the fries are plentiful but the best part of this place is the soda selection. There is a whole wall of bottled sodas from classics to crazy. We always try 4 or 6 different ones when we go.  I always get the teriyaki chicken sandwich. It is incredibly messy but so good. I usually go through 10 or 12 napkins trying to finish it. My husband has tried many of the burgers and said they are all great. Be warned, the servings are huge so you will leave full.  Seating it limited in this small place, as is parking, so we try in go in off hours so we don't have to wait for a table after we place our order at the counter.

AGA3_z8UIVCwCwObEiq0Xw.text: Edit 11/02/18 I came back for a second try and got the afterburner burger , fries and a drink. The fries were still vastly over salted, but were fresh.  But the burger......   I'll give them props, because the sandwich was good, but I refuse to call it a burger, because the patty is barely an eighth of an inch thick and there is nothing to taste. It is, by far, the skinniest patty I've ever had had. I couldn't flatten it anymore if I ran it over with my xterra. Lennys, a few blocks north , has better burgers and it's actually a burger....you know, with meat and then condiments.  Not 3 inches of condiments,  then a sliver of a patty.  I wont be coming back anymore.

6ES_qzvpGtVYK4QhrdNxJQ.text: Another incredible experience at rocket burger. This is the ultimate dive spot! Food is amazing and like no other. Perfect comfort meal. It's a small quick place so you wouldn't expect the quality of food that comes out of here! I love the wall of the fun soda brands you can't find anywhere else. Always got to get me a sarsaparilla when I'm here!   I love the philly cheese burger. Caramelized green peppers, onions with melted provolone cheese on top. My mouth is still watering!!  There fries are good too! They could be a little crisper but overall they still have a lot of flavor. We got a chilly cheese hot dog too that was very good. Good size hot dog.   Highly recommend! Perfect place to take a friend, family, or even boyfriend/girlfriend for an amazing casual comforting meal.Thanks rockets! (:

They also have very friendly service!!  Strange location in a strip my mall kind of hidden from the main intersection but well worth seeking out.

xc4ElO9h2cnHGM6qkTmyYw.text: This place is a gem. You would not notice it from the outside. But if you give it a chance, you will be impressed by the burgers this place create. The place looks like a convenient store, but much nicer. It has a huge wall of refrigerated soda of all kinds, in glass bottles. I haven't checked, but I wouldn't doubt if someone said that they have every flavor of soda known to man.   Couple of suggestions: I would order double patty burgers. The patties are a bit thin, so the single patty burgers tend to be cold due to the vegetables on top. Also, I would break out of the norm and order a burger out of the ordinary cheeseburger. They have some great "out of the box" burgers. This place is worth trying at least once.

JBg2G73Yb08NYUeuf-PJyQ.text: 2 words:  Slush Puppies.  They actually still have them here not to mention all of the other vintage sodas!!  Oh yeah the food is pretty darn good too.  Family got the gyro, CA burger, Italian sub and regular burger.  Great mom and pop place.  Highly recommended

njIRhz3vfuPLJqnki1z7jw.text: Anyone who doesn't go here is Severely Missing Out!!! Everything is just AMAZING!! Sammiches totally Beat Out any sandwich chain!!

9UekRd4cNRgRI_BBtPvRaA.text: Absolutely delicious!!!! I have yet to order from here and not be 100% satisfied. This is a must eat place!!!

aJyWmU-Yu9QETJh7ypordA.text: I actually love this place. I've moved from Phoenix but whenever I am down visiting family, I go grab a burger and try a new flavor soda. They never disappoint and they are so friendly!

3mh5i8E1zD2yxHOMRDkygA.text: What the what?! Where have you been all my life! We stopped in here because we followed a Pop Soda van and the food was so good yet affordable. We split a Gyro Rocket burger and fries - holy huge sandwiches...how in the world could anyone eat this much food without a partner!!?  Love the on tap sodas and bottles too. We tried to play guess the number and we each picked a number between 1 and 400 and the counter service Girl went directly to the cooler case doors and counted down until she hit our numbers (189 and 332) and surprised us with amazing Apple soda and a strange root beer blend, both good and less than $2!!

1cEOaU4XOUPRqEng7YJGYA.text: Great selection of Burgers, Dogs and Subs. Huge selection of sodas and pop from around the country. Food is a bit on pricey side but portions are generous. Would and have definitely gone back.

bWR3wygJ4saOlhNzkvRXIw.text: This place has amazing burgers. I've never been disappointed. They carry a wide variety of sodas as well, from all over the world. It's kind of a small spot, or a hole in the wall. Even if you're not hungry, stop in and grab a weird/strange soda!

Ajk1HNkJZYopAHsLX1tTxA.text: Did we order the wrong burgers? We just were not impressed with Rocket Burger & Subs.  Two of us ordered burgers and the other ordered a chicken sandwich. I opted for the Cali burger and the main flavors I could glean were the special sauce, avocado, and lettuce. The thin slab of beef was smothered by the sauce and veggies it had no chance of being savored unless eaten alone. Maybe I needed to make it a double but the single was already large. I think the focus of the burger was put toward the additives and not the patty. At least my friend enjoyed her special crispy garlic chicken sandwich.  The fries were our favorite side and the cooler after cooler of a gazillion different types of sodas was impressive. Service was fast and friendly but right now the next visit to Phoenix will not include Rocket Burgers, unless it's for fries and their unique selection of soda.
