0dcakZ6TAdx79X_jfVp4Jw.text: This place has a lot of options to choose from. They are pretty expensive but the food is decent. I like the selection they have of drinks. They have like 50 different root beers from all over the world. I've been here 3 times and have been satisfied.

qZLA9WUhiLBhCPIMys-hWQ.text: HOLY COW! An entire WALL of frosty specialty drinks?!?! Are you kidding!?!  I had a standard cheeseburger and it was phenomenal. The service was great- the flourescent green sodas that my kids chose from the wall were good. Weird, but good. Had a great time here with the family, will definitely go back the next time we are all in the mood for burgers and sodas.

cwydZLbEFgtkVay9Tp_fBA.text: Love this place. A wall of coolers contains every bottled soda and rootbeer known to man. Great burgers, try the New Yorker sub.

-9P6VyJwgleVlglG0S5yOg.text: I go here several times every month.  For lunch and dinner.  I have never been disappointed.   Burgers, sandwiches, hot dogs and fries.  It is all good.    My favorite is the Mexi-burger.  Fresh salsa, avocado, bacon, pepper jack and much more.  A great burger.  And then there is the great collection of soda.  My wife loves the fact that they carry her favorite "Rock n Rye" Faygo pop.  Straight from MI.  This place is definitely worth checking out.

Fx-RFsXkRp6O72_LJ_6d6A.text: Best damn burger in town hands down they will make almost anything to order! Their topped burgers are dynamite the fries are super. The chili OMG is absolutely out of freaking sight. Oh and the soda selection is perfect compliment to wash down all the amazing food they have to offer. Thank you guys for the best quality beef,  best service,  and damn yummy food love this place..

0TNGEda252Gb9pRZU6O2PQ.text: I'm shocked by the reviews. All of the good reviews are what led us to this place. Was so excited to try it out. Akward (not very friendly) people at register, the place was filthy, the food was not great at all and we tried several items on the menu (about 5 different things). The fries were very greasy and mushy. The food was nothing to rave about. And the bathroom was disgusting. After seeing the bathroom, I really regretted stepping foot in there and eating! Not sure what the hype is about. Will not go back.

LlIZYt0VRfo7akkkyEPbgQ.text: This place is great.  I am a faithful customer and I even recommend it to people I work with in the East Valley all of the time.  Items I have had (and enjoyed) as well probably should have made more than one meal out of: -Rocket Burger -New York Burger -Cali Burger -Santa Fe Burger -Philly Burger -Gyro Burger -Western Burger -Red White & Blue Burger -California Club Sub -Country Club Sub -New Yorker Sub -Gyro -Pescado de Cohete  I still have quite a bit of items I want to try but hands down this is the best burger and sub place I have EVER been to in Arizona and I am an AZ native.  I always try to give tips as well due to the fact that 1) I support local business 2) The owners and staff are very professional and cordial 3) the food is always well prepared not just slapped together like a typical fast food business

lXklrn1EYvd5y2cAxvUtrA.text: 2 of us had the New Yorker it was amazing! Fresh bread great slaw packed with tender pastrami. 2 had the Angus cheese burger on home made bun equally as good. 1 had the chicken bites real chicken breast freshly breaded excellent! Try the fresh made onion rings delicious. Can't wait to go back.

AJSmw6tRCf_1gx5RCrXOcg.text: This place was deilcious! I went there today with my boyfriend and we both loved it. He got a bacon cheeseburger "Rocket Style" and he let me have some. The burger was cooked perfectly and the toppings were fresh (I especially loved the crispy bacon). I got a cali sandwich but ended up being so full from the bites I stole off my boyfriend's burger that I didn't finish it. Next time I think I will just get my own burger . I say get a burger "Rocket Style" and you will never want a normal burger again!  Also make sure you give your self some time to pick what soda you want because there are a ton of choices! I don't think of this as a negative factor (as some reviewers did), I think it makes this burger joint unique!

vGrGrvWJdNdJTU3Nj-yEBA.text: Top 3 west side burger shop. Can possibly make # 1 after a few more visits and a couple cracks at the burgers on the menu. Philly burger with homemade fries oh my.

rf1QvusLsWS7YNyt39TPTQ.text: O boy I just discovered ROCKET BURGERS &SUBS. TOTALLY AWESOME!!!! This is the first time in a long while I drank 7-up from a bottle...tha fries are the bomb too!!!!!

7ulIa1nKNtz-XPR-n2yMGg.text: So worth the drive! It's about 1 1/2 drive from where I live, but we had to come to Phoenix anyways. I'm glad we stop by this unique burger joint... I had the AfterBurner Burger & Onion Rings also got the Pizza Bread... Yummy! I was starving ok lol. My fiance got a Fish Sandwhich and Fries he said it's like the best Fish Sandwich he's had. My little ones had the mini corn dogs & fries. So we enjoyed our self and the owners are really nice...

qyHKpdoVSYH6FxIqPp-dFQ.text: They sell Dublin Dr Pepper. The food was good and reasonably priced, but let's stick to the important facts, they sell Dublin Dr Pepper.

F9RxGdsC9vUQZggMQiye8w.text: Ahhhhhmmmmaaazziing! I had the mexi-burger and it was probably the single best burger I have ever had. Perfectly juicy and crisp. The fries were also very good. and oh my the soda selection. I did the math and there is about 500 different sodas. A must go in my opinion.

SKKZ_pWOi3VrwDim2PjR-g.text: Amazing! The fish sandwich is SO good, fries are amazing and soda selection is fun!

qE2cuuC2gIq5_BGbBodVeQ.text: If you're looking for a good old fashioned  mom and pop burger joint Rocket's your place.  Cheap, delicious, fresh burgers and sammiches, crisp cut fries, friendly attentive service and a wall of assorted soda's that'll put any other in town to shame.  Rocket doesn't need to be flashy or have a big hook.  It's simple food done well.  If I lived a little closer this would be my default hangout.

BZglLRo5REMpq7JV95INtg.text: Some of the best subs I have ever had!! And I travel a lot and will most definitely be coming back for more! Love the selection of soda's they have and being from Hawaii.... They even had some from there also. Loved the place!

J_u8_A708mXVQIaXUyy-0Q.text: Absolutely awesome old school place. Soda selection is massive and simply delicious hand crafted food. You gotta eat here!

Hdi14m5bu0PlUqbYOiSikA.text: Can I get a "god damn" for the best New Yorker in town.  I think its the cold slaw that has a sweet flavoring that matches well with everything.  If you haven't tried the New Yorker....get it done already, if you haven't tried Rocket Burger.....then you are neglecting yourself.  It's great food at super great prices!

qQwSt9kOv39qhwi4xDXvIQ.text: My wife and I have been living close to this place for a while now.  We've seen it coming home more than a few times.  Tonight we jumped here on Yelp and saw they were rated pretty high and decide this was the place for dinner.    I got the gyro burger combo with French fries and a sarsaparilla and my wife got the Cali Burger and onion rings.  Everything was fantastic.  They have a huge selection of pops that you won't find anywhere else.  Everything we had was great.  The French Fries and the onion rings were some of the best around.  If you are hankering for a good burger joint, this is definitely a good place to go.

7PMbf4zw9f54TCTDUqDC1A.text: Awesome place with quality service.  They have an incredibly large variety of sodas. And management is perfect.  I appreciate places that show quality and care, not only in what they produce but also in how it's shown through customer service. I will definitely be coming back!

Rq9F8ZYuo9aAdNtG2QLgQg.text: Cute concept place with a huge selection of sodas. I ordered my lunch for pick up today. Cheeseburger with decent amount of fries. Both were very good and reasonably priced. Will be back for sure. Oh, and thanks for the 10% check-in coupon, Yelp!   Next time, I'll be trying something else, like the New Yorker, which looks and sounds amazing. May add the ghost pepper cheese too ;)

osqDNO7gDAi8Aq80Oik7mA.text: This place is great! I had the Santa Fe with a fried chili on it! Delicious! Also tried the onion rings which did not disappoint. The soda selection is amazing and completes the meal.  Only draw back is sticky floor and tables.

QRp5HpNIQrlG_WLQtNREpQ.text: Meh. My Burger wasn't that great. The Bacon was overcooked. I came mostly for the soda selection. It takes a while to find the one you're looking for. They do have a lot of choices. I found the birch beer I wanted. I'll be back but mostly for the sodas.

fvzYVKQ6kvkOi2b5BzYhAA.text: Food: Burgers are ridiculous! If you want a burger with hot pastrami and special sauce this place has it. They have a variety of weirdly but awesome combinations of burgers and for the price it's better then any "Fast Food" burger. They also have other type subs like their French Dip is amazing and comes with a side of fantastic au jus for dipping. Let's talk about the ginormous variety of sodas from all over, their coolers take up most of the space to display all the sodas. Gotta try if you are craving a burger.  Decor: not much to say but it looks very much like a liquor store that sells burgers in the back of the store.  Service: Counter Service but friendly, willing to help you find something you'd like.  Overall: I like the Burgers but will probably take it Togo. Not really a place you want hang out in.

_pwZ_VuzqDD6VlXfgT4sUg.text: Your Cali burger rocks, it's the best burger in town, when ever I'am really hungry I stop at this place and order the Cali rocket burger and that fills me up like nothing else, love this place, and your staff are always kind and very helpful. Thank you Rocket burger!!!!!!.

rxEDdv4YNJ2rJAMIa0iHSQ.text: I recommend getting anything they have on special, never disappointed. Everything is hand made, and fresh. I think they no longer make their own bread tho, which leads to me giving 4, rather than 5 stars. Love this place regardless

RcsFP3snnZoK1duOt2725Q.text: I'm never ordering a rocket burger again, was it bad?  No of course not, I got it with the intention of having half and saving the other half for later, instead I'm in a food coma because just couldn't stop pecking away. It literally took two hours to finish with fries on the side. Sure I could have had self control but just couldnt, was too good. Second time been there while visiting, will be back before leaving town. Fries are fresh cut as well, all around good stuff.

GHUX2VW0CAukUj3D2nskqg.text: Do not even consider another burger joint. This place is better than THE BOMB. The burgers, oh the burgers, are so delicious. The toppings are even on point like Stacy Adams. I had the New York burger. Unbelievable!!! It's topped with pastrami, coleslaw, and rocket sauce. The pastrami was easily way better than any deli has here in Phoenix and the coleslaw mixed with the rocket sauce which made the burger BEST IN PHOENIX. Hands down. And speaking of hands, the hand cut fries are so delicious. Near perfect. And the snozzberries taste like scnozzberries. Haha!! Yes, this place is also a Soda Shop!! Are you kidding me?!?! I was a 39 year old kid in a candy store with their amazing selection of bottled pop...yes pop...and fountain pop. I ended up with a Snozzberry fountain drink. You MUST try this. Thank me later. Beyond refreshing. Finally, the customer service was even better than the food and that is saying something. So don't even consider another choice. Get yourself to the intersection of 35th Ave and Cactus and devour Rocket Burger. I promise you will be a repeat customer. Well done and thank you Rocket Burger!!!! Customer now for life. Sincerely, Cory Pierce

2nygvVPzwEQ5eEmGCyTJCQ.text: Rocket Burger is the best burger place in town! My go-to burger is the Cali Burger, but everything I've had so far is delicious, particularly the Eddie Lopez and Mexican Burger. All of the sides are amazing, as are the floats, and the soda selection is out of this world so I'm always able to try something new!  The only thing about Rocket Burger that I don't like is the fact that it's a bit of a drive for me, but in all honesty that's a good thing, because I'd probably eat there every single day if it was just down the road from me.

uc-oXU4Ku3RWU8DEotpy9w.text: I was fixated on the Rocket "Burger" of Rocket Burger & Subs... so much so that for my first visit, I though I'd be doing an injustice if I didn't get a burger.  Truth is: what's special about Rocket Burger is 1) the bread and  2) the rocket sauce.  The burger itself... eh, just fine.   And, yes, there's forty million sodas to choose from but if you're looking for "diet," you'll be forced to choose pepsi.  Still: four stars because the bread is awesome! I can not wait to go back and get a sandwich! Chewy, but you're not going to break your jaw or cut the roof of your mouth on it.   And, the rocket sauce puts other "secret sauces" to shame!  Bottom line: don't forget the "subs" at Rocket Burger!

cD4nWR7vwqu6zyDfa9NR0A.text: I arrived here with my beau before a dinner rush. We both got the bacon cheeseburger and loved it! He rated it a 7.8/10 on the fast burger scale and i rated it a 7. It was messy, it had good fresh lettuce and tomatoes, everything a good burger should be and have in my opinion  The bottled soda was fun to look through. We both are fans of huckleberry so we got different huckleberry sodas, very fun. Price was very reasonable for a good thick burger.

0kh8SVAa1H3GzksALB_o2g.text: Just so you know a bit about me, I will drive miles for a good burger. Lucky for me this place is close by and seriously delicious. So not only are the burgers good but there's like a thousand different bottles of soda to pick from. Holy memory lane batman, there were things I haven't seen in bottles since childhood. Good place to bring the fam too.

oBkg4FDic-_RoYT4yDi2_A.text: I never noticed this place when I used to live on 35th and Greenway driving to work every day...man I missed out. Recently I decided to try it based on the good ratings/reviews. On the first visit I decided to try the Sante Fe burger (double) w/ habanero cheese that was nice and melted running down the sides of the patties, It was like biting into heaven. There is so much flavor packed into this thing its ridiculous...in a good way of course. First walking into this place was a little intimidating for me because I'm just weird like that. To the south wall  they have about a 24ft cooler of all kinds of sodas and to the west is where you order your food. The staff is VERY friendly and polite. If anyone is looking for a good ol local place to eat with a good variety of burgers, subs, sandwiches and drinks then give them a try, you will not be disappointed...and if you are then you are the one with the problem haha

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. I had the double bacon cheeseburger with ghost pepper cheese. Photo doesn&#39;t do this sandwich justice...SO GOOD
Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. The lady had a California chicken club minus the lettuce and tomato, she loved it.

J52AixfTjhW245huIIbEGw.text: NY Burger, fries and a soda. Drank the craft root beer on tap.  The soda was stellar, loved it.  The sandwich was ok. Not balanced well, pastrami was very light... if I didnt see it I wouldnt know it was even there.  Fries were old school shoe string. Nothing great.  The building itself is run down and beat up. Not a lot of work having been put into it at all.  Staff is excellent. Great people and great service.  Four stars for the soda selection and originality of menu. Will probably go back for one more pass at it but only because the reputation is good, first experience wasnt positive enough on its own.

M0IUdz7pOFw5fnqAz6-f-g.text: Was expecting a great burger after reading the reviews, but I honestly didn't even finish half of my burger because it was just disgusting. However, this was my first time here and I may have just ordered the wrong thing. Also, a warning for anyone who orders online they don't check the 'special instructions', as there were mushrooms all over my burger. It's a good thing that I'm not allergic. Overall, the burger wasn't made with quality ingredients and left the grossest feeling in my stomach and taste in my mouth. I feel bad saying that, but would have taken an in-n-out burger over that in a heart beat.

yiBB3Z_SF0xbotUFZgq2eA.text: Checked this place out for lunch today looking for a hotdog. I got the chili cheese dog and cheese curds. Everything was mediocre at best. The curds are super greasy, more than could be enjoyed, and the chili wasn't the best. Maybe the burgers and sandwiches are better.

fHIifYIA0RXd2JTuW3If9A.text: I was blown away by the menu, my lunch and the kind people who work here.

ns97vVV9a08hJrKwRmi-YQ.text: Thank you Yelp. Another amazing find. In a world so dominated by fast drive thrus and cheap junk to take the edge off its nice to still walk into that hole in the wall that doesn't care how nice the new tile looks. This place is all about solid food. Bring your patience and your appetite. Both will be tested. Well worth the wait. This place re invigorates the reality that your burger doesn't need to be seen with cardboard.

CEn4WL4UqLh4Qjy7HCP9XA.text: Not too sure about Phoenix folks tastes in burgers.  2nd 4.5 star joint in a row that was meh!  Seeing is the name of this place is "Rocketburger", that is exactly what I got.  I ordered a Rocketburger with cheese and a fountain drink.  My total was just under $12.00.  Here is how it was..........  Rocketburger with cheese-  Meh.  This thing came with 3 patties, lettuce, tomato, onions and cheese.  It also had pickles and a "rocket sauce" aka thousand island.  The bun was a sub type roll and was fine.  All the ingredients were not that great though.  The burgers were way way way too salty, small and didn't taste good. The dressing had a weird "tang" to it also.  The cheese and bun were the only good things about it.  At around $10.00, I was dissapointed.  My mouth was swollen dry afterwards because of the salt!  Never again!  I ate the whole thing but would never get another one.  Diet Pepsi-  This was partly my bad.  They have 1000 or so bottled sodas for sale but I chose a fountain drink.  The Diet Pepsi was nasty!   The worst fountain soda I have ever had.  Tasted like root beer mixed with dirty water.   So nasty!  The guy at the counter and the guy who brought me my burger were friendly.  The food was below average and pricey,  and the soda was straight up nasty! Unfortunately I'm never coming back.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. One half of a Rocketburger with cheese.  Not good at all.

N3PpfoGzSoTejfEsQNFT0Q.text: Messy and delicious! I loved the fry seasoning. The whole soda float deal for $3 is amazing! Yeah, it looks shady as hell on the outside but it's essentially low on BS and high on entree and drink variety and deliciousness! It was a great place to hit up after hunting through Brass Armadillo.

NbXozC074sJgwyaDht0CKQ.text: Good customer service.  Clean dinning area.  Knowledgeable staff.  I had the large New Yorker pastrami sub and fried zucchini , my wife had a large turkey bacon avocado sub on wheat and fries.  The food was tasty and very large portion wise.   You definitely get you money's worth in food.  Their soda collection is vast, eclectic and nostalgic.  I will definitely go back again.

KHpcqcaBDOD8ohxAQdT4yA.text: I'm not sure if I get the rocket love.  Maybe it's just not my speed, but after one visit, I'm not really inclined to return.  There is an awesome selection of soda's in the bottle though.  Maybe that's worth the trip.  The wife and I rolled in after attending an RV show in Peoria.  On the way home, I remembered all the raves about this place, and it was about lunch time, so we re-calculated our route and made a stop in here.  I'm kind of a Root Beer fanatic, and it was great to see all the different brands.  I just randomly picked one.  Not even sure what it was, didn't have much head, but good flavor.  I also had been craving a hot dog.  Got one of those along with a cheeseburger.  The hotdog was awesome, grilled all-beef quarter pounder served nicely on a toasted bun.  That fixed my craving.  The cheeseburger part was simply for reference.  It was decently prepared and presented, but the bun was stale.  Not stale enough to taste bad, but enough to crumble into unworkable chunks of bread before I finished the burger.  I probably left a quarter of the bun in crumbles in my basket.  So overall, this was a first-impression review and I can say while I wasn't blown away, It also was not bad either.  Maybe I'm spoiled by all the custom-burger places in my neighborhood, and after all the raves I've heard, maybe my expectations were too high.  But for the price, quality and ambiance (which is not something they have) of Rocket Burger, it's a decent option.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Old - timey root beer

xW83xMtyV-SmDiQd9-jhtw.text: Wow!!!!!!!! Now that was a great lunch. Found the location on Yelp and decided to give it a try. We were rewarded with a wonderful meal at an affordable price. I have driven by this location numerous times and truly never even thought twice about stopping by. Boy, had I been missing out. We knocked out the fish sandwich, the Cali burger, the chicken salad, and the best cheese curds I have ever had. Every item listed was awesome. The burger was huge, as was the salad. The fish sandwich was so tasty. The negative, the place is so far from my house. Love the food and the large variety of drinks to try. Who has ginger soda as a fountain drink? Yep, this place. And Shirley temple? Yep, this place. Oh and to top it off, 10% off by checking in on Yelp. A perfect experience!!!!

You have a craving for an unusual soda, this is the place to go.  We ordered chili cheese dogs and french fries. Everything was really tasty, hot, and the staff was extremely nice.  The only thing that kept it from getting that 5th star was the tables all needed cleaning.  Bits of food on all of them.  Will absolutely go back!

z-OLTZksAmzTleHj7YfCWQ.text: I visit Rocket Burger several times a month. Not as often as I would like.  There are many reasons I go there. The food is good and the people that own the place and the workers are the best.  We go there to eat and visit. The nicest people you could ever meet. We try to go in the off hours so we have some time to talk with the owners and workers.  Go in and say Hi. Again the food is good and the people are the nicest you can find anywhere.

SH7Wg4fGP5E-IPSMSJpcGg.text: Not bad, but did not live up to the hype.  I've been told about this place by many people and that I, "have to try it".  So I tried it, a few times.  The burgers are not bad, the meat patties themselves are not good but the cheese, bacon and toppings were good.  The meat patties did not have a good flavor to them, and I mainly went to this place for the burgers!  The fries were soggy and had a burnt look to them but they were not burnt, they tasted decent.  The Chicago dog is bomb, great fresh toppings and the fried zucchini isn't bad.  Overall, not a bad spot, but would prefer other local burger joints.

VDWNCfnnJYmhKqmS2D6Zbg.text: This is a place you want to take visiting friends. It looks like a hole in the wall in a sad strip mall, but it doesn't let you down. The burgers themselves aren't super special, but the topping combos are killer. The Santa Fe burger, with a whole fried green chile on top, is a sight to be seen. The fries are surprisingly delicious and have the skins still intact. They remind me of the fries at Five Guys, which I think is a really good thing. Last time we went I decided to try the subs, and I would heartily recommend you do the same. I was feeling something a little more traditional, so I tried their Reuben. The sauerkraut wasn't too overwhelming, the dressing was perfect, and there was a ton of melted cheese. Mmm. I will warn you though: Whatever you get is going to require a LOT of napkins, and possibly a knife and fork. This isn't a place to take a dainty eater.  Their selection of pop (yeah, I said pop) is insane. All of them are priced the same. No stressing out over picking one out before ordering and wondering how much each costs. And after you're done eating, go next door to the pop-only storefront and pick up a 4 or 6 pack to go. I asked the owner how many different varieties he has, and he said right now it's 700+, so the choice won't be easy, but you'll come away with some interesting varieties. I picked up a rhubarb soda, and a espresso soda last time, along with the key lime one I had with my meal.

hUO5hMnktMrPJcFWUBl5sg.text: So.. went to Rocket with the hubs based on other Yelper reviews. Yelp did not do us wrong!   First off, the location is a bit seedy.. 35th and Cactus, but you cant let that deter you. From the outside it could almost be mistaken for some kind of convenient store.. at one point it was a meat market or something... in a little strip mall next to a Church's chicken and a cash title loan place...   The inside has a row of booths again the window and a mishmash row of tables and chairs down the middle. One major wall is a giant cooler stocked full of beverages. To one side is the register and grill with 2-3 people manning that area.   The have a HUGE selection of root beer, cream soda, ginger ales etc. Totally cool... certainly a compliment to a great burger, no?   The hubs ordered a combo- dbl bacon cheese burger with everything on it (let, tom, onion, thousand island, pickle) with rocket rings. I ordered a single combo- cheese burger with everything on it and rocket fries.   The burgers were awesome... not too greasy, grilled nicely.. great flavor. ..Little bits of thousand island and onion falling out. The rocket rings looked to be hand battered, fresh onion rings.. a total surprise from a typical onion ring (usually of the frozen variety). The rocket fries were shoestring cut- my personal fav- not too greasy, just enough crunch and sogginess all in one.... served up with ketchup or ranch.   We both had a cream soda as part of our combo as well. Two different kinds, neither tasting anything like the other. The whole thing came out at about $15. Not bad for everything we got... pure deliciousness. Why would anyone go next door to the chicken place and get that crap?!?   I really hope these guys do well. I will definitely be back to try something else on the menu and grab a a different root beer or cream soda I never had before.   Yum.

rwwP1-Ukcc3qXAWsTympZA.text: This place made a quick, great burger. They have enough variety to satiate any tastes (if that taste is for something burgerlike) and their wall of unconventional soda and NA beverages is worth the trip on its own.  In one trip it has been a staple of the area.

EMfSHgOUU1Kq6Ixxb71dOA.text: Okay, so i went with 4 stars but there are a few caveats.  My first visit was a 5 star experience: i went on a weekday night with a moderate crowd.  The Chicago burger was everything I could ask for in a burger - super juicy and tasty.  My second experience was unfortunately a 3 star experience: I went on a Saturday afternoon with a line to the door.  Now I didnt mind the long line because thats a sign of quality food and my last burger had been amazing so i was happy to wait.  Unfortunately, the staff didn't seem to handle the rush all that well.  The girls at the register were still friendly but things got a little messy out on the floor and in the rush to get the food out to so many people a few things got overlooked.  Most noticeably, my fries came out a bit undercooked and there were some pools of oil in the basket.  I have a family of 5 and all of our fries were way too greasy, also I went with the Chili burger this time and the chili itself tasted canned so the burger lost that freshness.  Still, this is a good spot just avoid the rushes

YHrtKtw4N6Zz7z9yBrHjcQ.text: It's a strange phenomenon that happens so very rarely, where something is redone, a song or movie for example, and ends up better than the source material --   *More Real Than The Original*  ...Buffy the Vampire Slayer television show vs. movie    ...Jimi Hendrix vs. Bob Dylan All Along The Watchtower (even Dylan admitted it was Jimi's song now)  There is a restaurant concept sweeping the valley right now, based on a certain small number (between 1 and 3) of people of a certain philosophy (free-wheeling, nature-loving, noodly-music-listening) and their crazy atmosphere establishments full of odd "paraphernalia".  Well, think about how one of those places got your hopes up and then  left them dashed, and head on over to Rocket Burgers & Subs for everything you thought you'd get with those other guys:  ~A fresh, clean, uncluttered atmosphere that you can sit comfortably inside of while enjoying your meal. ~A HUGE selection of almost any kind of soft drink you'd desire to quench that thirsty, dry mouth of yours. ~Lots of variety of menu, all with inexpensive good quality items of decent portion ~A radio playing the xmsirius Grateful Dead Channel for your soothing/stimulating dining pleasure. ~and a couple of really nice, friendly, hippy-on-the-inside-not-just-for-show restauranteurs eager to discuss their business and products, who are not only present now, but seem that they'll be sticking around to ensure the quality and value of their new place doesn't wane.  The food is fresh, fast, and inexpensive.  If you want burgers, subs, dogs, pizza-bread, gyro, salad, handmade fries &  onion rings, PBJ with homemade jam  -- they've got it.  The chicken sandwich had a light crispy breading and a solid chunk of breast meat.  The burger was a smaller patty (available as a double) but not dry, and the condiments were fresh and generous.   For both sandwiches, the standout part was the fresh bun from Simply Bread (local).  It was soft/firm enough to be just right, and had great flavor. They have a cooler chock full of interesting and bizarre selections from Pop The Soda Shop (Jones Soda, imported ginger ales and root beers, glass bottle real sugar sodas from mexico, dublin dr pepper, etc). My spicy Bleinheim Ginger Ale did not skimp on the ginger flavor!  A couple of real ex hippies would do it like this --  no flashy superficial emphasis on outward appearances and gimmicks, just quality, freshness, and friendliness that is truly genuine and sincere. I feel like I made a new friend. Rocket Burgers & Subs is one out of this world place, and I'm glad it landed in my neighborhood.

-iGnFx-_nV7bvOo8wvvKzw.text: The coolest part of this place has to be the wall of the sodas. Bottled sodas that you've never heard of; I want to go back just to try more. I got two to take home: a Moxie for myself and this Japanese soda for my wife. The former was very old fashioned (I should have known by the Ted Williams poster they have displayed by the case) and not very good, at least to my taste. My wife's soda was a strawberry-flavored beverage with a really interesting bottle design and mechanism to open. It looked like a baby bottle and you use part of the top to open it...hard to explain.  As for the food, I had a chili cheese burger that was quite tasty. The burgers are served on large, soft buns perfect for their hefty burger creations. The chili was pretty sold, a firm B+ (nowhere can come close to the best chili cheeseburger in the world, which fyi, is at Tommy Burger in Los Angeles). The fries were just so so, not quite crispy enough.  I'll definitely be back and I'll come with an even bigger appetite, probably for the Philly Burger :)

YjaxzABUfbaw4B4_GKt_Ng.text: I have no idea where to start on this review.. This place is just phenomenal.. Right when I walked in I knew i was at the right place, with all the sodas everywhere and the place was packed with people. When I looked at the menu I was lost because it had so many things. I saw the New Yorker Burger and I said this has to be amazing with some fries and a nice creme soda! I also added a side of mini corn dogs because who wouldn't???.. The girl helped me out also on if my choice was good and she said yes that's one of the popular items. She was nice and kept saying thank you. After I ordered I went to the fridges with all the sodas and I was literally lost.. I had no idea on what to get so many choices and so many things I didn't know about. I wanted to try one of everything to be honest. I grabbed creme soda and sat down. Waited about 5 minutes and the food came out, so the service was excellent too. The burger was fantastic the coleslaw with the pastrami that just melts into your mouth so juicy so good. The fries are seasoned so perfect not having a lot of salt like most seasonings. The corn dogs were as expected so amazing.. This place is just incredible and I can't wait to come back to try other things!! Just wish it had more room and not one bathroom.. But it's okay I like the old feel to it! If you want good food this is your place!

4HAQCBYRmaqahnMHquwTYQ.text: First time there. So I wanted to play it safe, not go for any wild things. Just try standard fare and work up to others later. I figured if they can't get the basics right, maybe I don't go back.  My wife had a single cheeseburger, I had the double regular. We ordered these as combos, expecting regular French fries. We were quite surprised at the fries that arrived - scrawny, over-cooked, oily, not good flavor, and a strange orange tint to them. The burgers were better than the fries, however, I believe they put too much sauce on them - it was dripping everywhere, making it a difficult eat. (I prefer a burger that stays together and keep a fairly dry bun, not soggy like ours.) Also, the meat was still pink in the middle. If I get a big, fat patty like at Fuddruckers, a medium burger is OK, but on these thin little patties at Rocket Burger, pink inside is just not appealing.  Despite all this, I did enjoy the flavor of the burger, and could have actually eaten another (if I ordered with very easy sauce).  The big plus for this place that saved the experience for me was the management. I guess I was chatting with one of the owners when I was there, and he was very polite and cordial. I mentioned the name of the guy who recommended this place to me, and barely started to describe him, when he knew who I was talking about and where I know him from.  I will go back based entirely on the friendliness I experienced there. Only thing is, this time, I'll order some real kind of sandwich, and go for a different side item than their "standard" fries.

t3AnBTe0ynY1uo0Jq5Mg_g.text: I came here again with my wife for dinner. She had a chicken sandwich with a teriyaki pineapple sauce that was absolutely delicious. I did the Mexican hot dog again.  Once again I was reminded why this place is so highly recommended. The food was amazing, the fries have gotten much much better too! Keep it up Rocket Burger!   I can't wait until next time. There's just so much good stuff on the menu that I think I'll be busy trying something new on each visit for a long time to come.

ZlMHEYsxw_OcQ1KFZJ1tBQ.text: First time here today. As awesome as I had hoped! Total hole in the wall place in phoenix, but definitely worth the drive if you aren't close. Lots and lots of burgers and subs to choose from. I had a double new york burger, and it was everything I wanted it to be. Greasy, meaty, cheesy. Root beer and fries? Yes please. Plus a six pack of assorted premium not-from-this-world sodas to take home. I miss pop the soda shop, as it was so close to where I lived. Same sodas here for the most part, plus...burgers. It's a bit of a drive, but worth it.   I'll be back. GET IN DA ROCKET BURGER YEEAARRRGGGHHH!!! Give me your clothes, your boots, and your rocket sauce.   I'm gonna go watch T2 and enjoy my dogs and suds root beer now.

53QUdydLCPg9ujuJkNrocg.text: So is this a burger sandwich shop or a fantastic specialty soda / pop store? This place is SO COOL!  I honestly never knew there were so many kinds of soda pop and the flavors are just as cool as the design and names on some of the bottles.  Anyway I can't express enough how impressed I was witht their soda selection but my reviews are more about a restaurant and their food and this review will not become an exception.  I ordered three burgers to go. Two double cheeseburgers a chili burger two orders of fries and one order of onion rings. My 21 year old grandson had their chili burger and an order of fries. My wife and I had the double cheeseburger. She had the fries I had the onion rings.  My grandson said he liked his burger and that it was OK but nothing to write home about. He said the fries were about the same.  My wife commented that her cheeseburger was a little spicy and ate half of it because she just didn't care for it.  Her fries were OK.  My first impression was this: Right from my first bite there was something about the burger I didn't like. It tatsed OK, Their sauce is great but it does have a bit of a kick to it.  so what was it? I finally determined that the combination of their "sauce" and the way their lettuce is cut so thin it appeared there was coleslaw on the sandwich instead of lettuce. In fact if there wasn't it sure seemed like there was and I just didn't care for it at all. But everything else about the burger was fine.  The burger was good, the bun was different than you normally get a burger on, it tasted good and was hot. I agreed with my grandson though it was noting to write home about. My wife and grandson also commented on how they weren't really impressed with their fries, but I have to say my onion rings were deeeeeelicious!!!   Bottom line: Better than Rocket Burger is better than any fast food place. I guess I just expected a little more especially after reading the reviews.                      So I will have to give them another try   FOOD: NO wow factor or anything, however they are  better than any fast food place. PRICE: The prices are reasonable. SERVICE: The guy at the counter was nice and polite. AMBIENCE:  Looked more like a convenient store than a restaurant. CONCLUSION: Two Words: SODA SHOP The selection is intense. Best I've seen in years. Great selection of small batch brews. I love mom & pop establishments so stop by and support this really friendly neighborhood shop.

TxvcEVbuV4WhJqJrvQjT-Q.text: There is something special about having a whole wall dedicated to bottled soda. It really make my mouth light up with joy. This is what makes this whole in the wall memorable. I went for one of the blue cream sodas and really enjoyed it. Price wasn't too bad either.  The food on the other hand... Well my bf would be able to make a more impressive sandwich. The ingredients seemed fresh and of good quality, but my sandwich, the turkey special for the day, was definitely lacking in the sauce department. Which was sad because it was a spicy root beer BBQ sauce, and what I could taste of it was spot on.  Would have asked for extra sauce on the side, but the folks working there weren't very friendly or approachable. Seemed like there was some tension in the air. Maybe they were having a bad day...

DG_n5rD8V48A52bCnwjq-Q.text: The serving sizes here were gigantic. The pricing is fair, and the menu is varied. I came with a group of 10 and everyone liked their order. The service wasn't incredibly fast, but it was reasonable. The people there were also really nice, and the soda selection might be the most at any restaurant in the state of Arizona. I look forward to returning.

KZsD4eiPY9XxzptH5wpI7Q.text: The guy at the counter seemed impatient while i looked over the menu as i have never been here before. I told him ill just need a minute to look it over, he replied by saying nothing and continuing to stare. Talk about pressure. I loved the massive variety of soda in a glass bottle. I got a sandwich with a side salad. Loved the bread with the sandwich, it was stacked full making it a little messy to eat. Great, simple flavour. The salad was simple with large chopped veggies such as carots, cucumbers, bell peppers. Overall a great stop for lunch or dinner.

uCtlvG9Rw118DQfr-vihxw.text: Burgers were good. The sides are great. Skip the fries and get the zucchini or mushrooms. Next time I'm going to have to dig into their selection of Root Beers... Can't wait!

zEp58jDK1qSuNs40bTuwZA.text: How did I not know about this place?!!  Food is fantastic and a huge wall of vintage sodas with your meal??

1xWt2LCZjE2VSsuzYXKbZw.text: My Favorite place to enjoy a Burger and Soda!  Fries are delicious too, just the right amount of salty.  California Burger is my Favorite.  Just tried the Onion rings too, they are a salty, crunchy delight. As noted soda selection is huge.  The thousand island sauce on the regular burgers tastes zesty and fantastic!  Excellent experience here.

g6C1Yxi0JnoG6EoFU_hmKA.text: I went here with a buddy for lunch and was pretty satisfied with my experience.  It's not fancy or much to look at, but they definitely focus on the food, and that's all one can ask for.  The Philly Cheesesteak was great and so was the extensive selection of sodas.  Definitely worth checking out if you're in the area and looking for something quick and cheap.

yO5bWYgiA2vld7XaCcDlyg.text: Try it, you'll love it. Good food and great selection of bottled soda (about $2.50 each). You can make any drink into a float by adding $1. The owner actually helps out & chatted with us a bit. It's always fun to learn the history & passion of how an eatery came to be. Try Ghost Cheese Pepper on your burger or sandwich. They also accommodate for those who are on a low carb diet & want to omit the bread, they replace it with extra lettuce or coleslaw.

cVAncXTPK4pRlGpuoSASGQ.text: The burgers are good but not as good as the Yelp rating would indicate.  I had a sandwich there once and it was very mediocre.  The fries are terrible.  Ditto for the frozen soft serve ice cream or yogurt product.  It taste like low fat.  Exceptionally low quality.  I'd certainly eat the burgers again but not the other offerings.

mG2akQsSBWMqEOUz8CXw2g.text: The food was great and so was the service. I ordered the Newyork Burger and orders a soda from the wall of unique flavors and brands, I definitely recommend it. The food came quickly,  the only thing I could say wrong was the trash area needed some cleaning.

YXQiumvavOVOi_feoxC5fQ.text: I was craving a burger and I wanted a good one so I searched yelp for good burger reviews. I decided to try this place out today because it's just two miles from my home. The location isn't all that great, like someone else mentioned it's more like a convenient store than a restaraunt. I ordered the gyro burger and it was such a great idea and delicious. My only complaint is the burger patty was really small and didn't cover the whole bun. I washed it down with a Fentimans Dandelion & Burdock soda which was interestingly different tasting. They have so many different soda's it was hard to pick one so I just tried the one with the oddest ingredients I could find. My friend ordered the Baja burger and it was very messy but she said it was awesome. She liked the bread and the toppings. We're both fans now.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Gyro burger and dandelion soda

q-h3Gtk7B4lPSJA-PI_XqA.text: If only I could give this place 50 stars...  They really do force me to grade every other eatery on a curve..  I've been coming here about twice a week for a year now and it just keeps getting better.  The staff is welcoming and eager to please, the selection approaches infinity, the value is absolutely unbeatable, and the food... OH MY GOD THE FOOD!!!  I've had so many amazing experiences here.  Like how we mentioned to the owners how cool it would be if they offered ice cream, only to find a whole slew of ice cream treats we never would've dreamed of a month later.  Like how I mentioned that I missed the Flathead Lake Blueberry Pomegranate soda (I wanted to try it in a float now that they had ice cream), and I came in 2 days later to find new ones in the freezer and a full case on the rack.  Or the time my girlfriend and I just stopped and stared at each other after our first bites of our Red, White and Blue Special burgers on the 4th of July.  Or my feeble attempt to finish a 3-patty-on-a-sub-roll Rocket Burger by myself on my first visit...  I've tried just about everything on the menu and have yet to be disappointed.  All of the burgers are incredible, but my personal favorites are the Philly Burger, The Afterburner, Teriyaki Burger, Steak Burger, and the Red,White & Blue Burger.  The Pescado de Cohete, a zesty spicy citrus fish sandwich, is a must try, as is the chicken (sandwich or nuggets).  And don't get me started on the subs...  I'm halfway through trying them all and picking a favorite just depends on my mood, none have disappointed me.  Same goes for the hot dogs.  The sides are perfect as well.  Aside from the MOST ADDICTIVE FRIES AND RANCH IN THE WORLD, they also have cheese curds, pizza bread, OVER 300 SODAS, SLUSH PUPPIES, and one-of-a-kind treats like PECAN PIE SHAKES!!!  On top of all of this, they're the best value ANYWHERE.  Where else can you get a $4 burger combo this epic???  I challenge anyone to leave hungry!  Every time I come here I think it just doesn't get any better.  But then I come back and they prove me wrong.  Long live Rocket Burger!!!

zqNUIxAR68JAjbkGA349ew.text: One of my favorite places to eat! New York Burger is absolutely delicious! Plus the enormous selection of soda is the best! If you haven't eaten here before you are missing out! It's a one of a kind place.

MGXlD8lcCSVXKE6ZXUWnyw.text: We had high expectations for this place based on the reviews and I'm happy to say they delivered!. I was first of all so excited to see all the cream sodas..I'm seeing one after ages. I had the cali burger..this one i suppose is the spicy one..I'm loved it! The crispy bacon and avocado combination was lovely! My husband had the Sante fe burger and that went down quite quickly..the fried chilly was the highlight of that burger. Another point I must mention is the fact that the burgers arrived super quick.. this made me a very happy diner.

Q03gsnZm0-UfmdM4giVjjQ.text: I am grime El Paso, TX. I traveled to Phoenix for the weekend to visit my son. Looked up burger places and this business came up. Well gotta say it was better than what I thought! The New York burger was delicious and definitely coming back.  They also have a variety of sodas and pop to choose from. Great little business in AZ.

Jxq5M4ZCvCt_xAyWhgyHBg.text: I am so grateful to say I have had the famous Rocket Burger.  This place gets so much Yelp praise and for great reason.    The soda selection is off the hook every soda you grew up with and then some all in coolers in bottles the even got YooHoo.  Fries are all natural cut and amazing there is just something great about fries with the skin on them they just taste better.   The burger was Phenomenal I had the Santa Fe which had the amazing Rocket Sauce, bacon, and fried green chili.  It was outta this world good.    I will be a loyal customer and I am sure will post numerous updates to this review cause this place is just that good.

hlYipg2tn8p8b8WTmGcXSQ.text: I will travel for a delicious burger. So why the eff did I not know about this place that I can effing walk to? Seriously?! First thing, when you walk in, you're overwhelmed by all of the yummy soda. I mean there is stuff here that your parents grew up with. Jolt cola? Yummo! Espresso cola? Why yes please, butterscotch root beer? Omg yum. And here's a fun fact, you can make ANY OF THEM  a float! Sold! Next thing is the burgers. The bun is effing delicious. So not only is this burger giant, but the bun will not fall apart. I'm not sure if they are made in house, but who cares! Lastly the fries. Oh god. Fresh potato fries that are cooked to perfection. This is a great place to have a cheat meal, plus they are very quick with the cooking and delivery to your table. This place is a KEEPER!

JReT04URAIe-b3W0usjC7Q.text: I had the "Afterburner"... It was really fresh and really good. I wasn't real crazy about the horse radish on it, but that's just me. The chicken was awesome. My daughters had the Gyro burger. I sniped a taste, it was exceptionally good. They have an absurd variety of sodas... including Jones and Jolt -two of my childhood favorites. My bill with those three combos was a little over $27. I don't ever give 5 stars so this was as good as it gets. 4 stars.

zGIreXZmVON1HzykxjVf7w.text: Over a year later and still great. Went in on a Sunday afternoon for a late lunch and got the California burger (sans tomatoes and pickles). The avocado was fresh, the bun wasn't dry, and their "secret" sauce was still perfectly peppery and went great with the avocado and cheese. It's also one of the only places to get a lot of the soda they have on offer and today I chose a vanilla root beer from Barrel Brothers.  It seems that they bought most of the mini-mall they're in so there's more parking and will soon be a lot more seating. Good for them!

7GKwCc-Te2zEHzBfeh0JCQ.text: I loved there Baja burger! The slaw and salse in that burger went extremely well. The workers here are nice as well to always ask how our food was and if we enjoyed it. I had a smile on my face the first bite of that burger. The zuchini and onion rings were huge portions, so that was a plus. They overcooked them alil bit, but i still enjoyed them with the dipping ranch sauce!

OOgRqusm6H479FGPWeuGMw.text: Super Yummy!! Got the NY burger,  Gyros Burger,  fries and onion rings!  BAMM! ! All home runs... don't get the brain wash soda.  Heheheeeehe

_qKALU4zrdOU51_EwuHe6Q.text: Went here for lunch after looking at great reviews on Yelp. Divey place with very cool selection of sodas and quite a selection for burgers or subs. Ordered Bacon Ghost Pepper Cheese Burger, Fried Mushrooms, Philly Cheesesteak with Fries. The burger was great, not spicy at all. The Philly Cheesesteak, Fries and Fried Mushrooms were okay. Fast and friendly service. Will go here again and will try some of the sodas as well.

I3diWflOfAWygO5-Xl-wwg.text: This place is really good. I had it bookmarked for such a long time & one night, I couldn't figure out what I wanted to eat for dinner & figured it would be the perfect time to check this place out. They have so many different options to choose from, it was so hard trying not to order everything all at once! Haha. I've been craving a Philly cheese steak for such a long time and this was also recommended by one of the employees at the register.   I've had quite a few different Philly cheese steaks from other places but this one is definitely one of the best! The bread was so soft and nicely toasted & didn't get soggy (as some of them do from meat juices). Perfect amount of meat and cheese too. Their fries, I wasn't that impressed with. They definitely look and taste hand cut fresh potatoes. I usually like my fries crispy so I asked them to be well done. This was a mistake because they actually tasted burnt rather than being crispy.   They have so many different soda's to choose from. They have so many bottle lined up against their windows and fridges full of bottles soda. & they also have craft soda on fountain.

42tgC4NHW9GDsP5IlLTADA.text: This place is awesome can't wait to come back best burger place in AZ Noah Sheryl were so helpful you guys rock!!!

aCqgymcJABkZncDGK45FZw.text: Surprise!  Best fries I've had in awhile! Tons of choices, I tried the special. Bonus craft soda on tap!

y26ZdWQFgAuZsebMlzy1sw.text: Was just driving by looking for a place to have lunch and came in on a whim. Dude one of the best burgers I've had and the fries are great. Awesome soda selection with brands and flavors I've never heard of. Had chocolate soda for the first time. People there are nice and service is fast

-bd5qzv9CWgO0EHgVoLtDg.text: I am sitting in this establishment right now, just having finished the second burger I have ever had here. When I got my first burger here about a month ago, it was amazing. Still, I decided to try Rocket a second time because I thought it may be a fluke. It was not a fluke. These burgers are out of this world. So far I have had the Mexican burger, and now the Garlic Melt. Everything is cooked perfectly and the fries are awesome. Fast, friendly service and at a reasonable price! Will recommend to everyone I can find!

pfJlq4NOUdguXO52nKH2jw.text: Okay like they pretty much know my voice when I call! I love this place! They even finish my sentences like we've been married 20 years I call and say..." Can I have a veggie sub..." And before I can finish they say (once they recognize my voice) ..."with ghost cheese" I'm like "ummm yes its me AGAIN"...LOL....so while we are on the topic...have you ever had ghost pepper cheese? If not your missing out! The ghost cheese is like my personality it's spicy but good at the same time! I always get the fried mushrooms they are perfectly seasoned fried to perfection are even good reheated...today little baby (my youngest) got a hot dog with onion, relish, and because she's not a Chicagoin ketchup (gross)! The moment she bit it she said and I quote "this hot dog is everything" which means yummy! I also ordered a Baja burger with a veggie patty (cuz I don't eat the meats) I'm not sure how good the actual patty was because like all their burgers and subs are piled high with the good stuff! Just try it if you're in metro phx... Your welcome...just thank me later.

2YojT-Kz51fQ-7X4zVyjnQ.text: Don't judge a book by its cover! I am always on the quest for a great bacon cheese burger and Rocket fit the bill! It doesn't look like much from the outside. But when you come in you will be amazed. The soda selection is amazing. I could stay there all day trying different root beers!  I tried the gyro, bacon cheeseburger, and fries. I was in fat man heaven.  Burger was juicy and good bacon too, not the cheap bacon a lot of places  use. The gyro had thick lamb. I was very impressed.  The service was spot on too. Very quick and answered my questions. When I mentioned I liked root beer they took me over to the giant selection of sodas and told me if I wanted more they had a whole store next door (Pops). I appreciated that he walked me over and didn't just point like a lot of places tend to do. I will definitely be back to try more of the menu.

xTuU_yVrXzrgwjDhVGzvBA.text: Great food!  Was in the mood for a burger, heard about this place for awhile. Packed the family up and had a great lunch here. I had the bacon cheeseburger and chili cheese fries. Burger was great, Bun, cheese, bacon, ground beef. It's a little big, and messy but worth it. Kids loved the hot dogs, and fries. Wife enjoyed her burger also. There were other options on the menu I would love to try next time.  Parking is not the best, but thats the way it goes. Not a lot of seating, however there are some. When we where there, they were have an issue with their soda fridge leaking water. Watch your step. Over all we had a great time, this is a place with great food!

qe46hb0DazcZBxRJ7G0SEA.text: Soda pop shop with burgers and sandwiches best describes Rocket Burger. Went on the fly waiting for  a nearby appointment. Grilled cheese on rye, way too much cheese and yes there is such a thing even for this cheese heard. Fries were the star for me, crispy and flavorful. Husband enjoyed his club sandwich. Downside for me was cleanliness, bathroom was unusable, tables were not clean, always makes me think the kitchen may be dirty too?  Probably not worth the caloric investment.

41EvKLUaRMbvg_G0ibKG7A.text: Horrible. Fresh, never frozen burgers? Yeah right. They taste just like a McDonald's burger and this place even puts a ton of pepper on the bottom of their patties like McDonald's. Not worth the money. Inside was dirty and old. I seriously have had better burgers from Burger King, Wendy's and McDonald's. If you're looking for a good burger place, check out Lenny's.

kpmXckE8aBKlIyv_SJpf2Q.text: Had the New Yorker burger, onion rings and peanut butter shake. It was all delicious. Bottle soda selection is amazing and have had many of the different root beers all of them awesome!

3xHu9FXCDlb-TniRmVx9Xg.text: I had bookmarked this location after looking for new places to try out and decided to give it a try this past weekend. When you first get here, it doesn't look all that inviting, but the food is soooo good!! I can see why this place has good ratings. The service here is amazing. The two girls working behind the counter at the registers were very friendly and helpful and gave great suggestions of things on the menu to try since this way my first time here.   I decided to do the bacon cheeseburger combo and upgraded my fries to chili cheese fries. Food came out fairly quickly, considering there were many people ahead of me. The young man that brought out my order was very professional and courteous. He smiled and asked if I needed anything extra before he left. Food portions are generous. I wasn't sure how big the burger would be, so I just order the single which was more than enough for me with the chili cheese fries. The burger was cooked well and tasted great! Chili cheese fries were a huge portion with lots of chili and cheese on top. Love that they give you enough chili and cheese to cover all the fries and not just the top ones.   Inside of the restaurant is small, so many people had to take their food to go. Need to enlarge the seating area so more people can enjoy the whole experience of this restaurant. Parking isn't the best, so come early if you want to be able to find front parking, otherwise, you may be parking out by the dumpsters.   Can't wait to come back and try more delicious food!

ezIkQqQ_t2nfGEfI9odA3A.text: When I go somewhere that is rated 4.5 stars, I expect more.  This place did not deliver.    Lets start with service.  The girl behind the register was new, I give her that, but there was a line about three deep and several other employees were just standing around, letting this girl drown.  I could see her struggle and frustration and felt bad for her.  I ordered the hatch green chili burger and fries and my husband got the teriyaki burger with onion rings.  Food comes out, smells good, take a bite, bun is stale.  Not toasted, but stale.  Instead of pitching a fit, I just pick off the stale ring around the bun and keep on going.  Decent flavor but I think I got a veggie burger with a piece of hamburger added.  I have had thicker pieces of deli meat if you catch my drift.  Thin.  Disappointing.  Fries were ok, but nothing exciting.  The onion rings were weird.  Battered in what looked like breadcrumbs and cornmeal.  Different, but not great.  Onto the bathroom.  It was filthy, no toilet paper and just overall not sanitary.    I dont eat burgers often, but when I do, I expect greatness.  This wasn't great.  Not even mediocre.  It was disappointing.

cNbmY6tnxpOEG9V7DfTw6g.text: My husband was craving a good burger so in our quest we turned to Yelp! For help in deciding where to go. They make their own roast beef and its layered on on top of your burger along with grilled onions, bell peppers, and melted cheese. It's amazing, anything you could possibly want! Plus they have some homemade sodas on tap.

iliJrW3oGi4DMXcJ2I752g.text: My friend's daughter had been here before and the online menu looked interesting.  We had four burgers total, 2 Cali, 1 Bacon Cheeseburger and 1 Garlic Melt. FFsOmjXpbQQGONp4_GAyYw.text: OMGGGGG sooooo good I love this place!!!! Just moved from Chicago and haven't found a great place to eat like this in months! I love it service is great. The atmosphere and decor is so different I recommend this to anyone

I really value the fact that the meat doesn't taste like it's been simmering in a steam-table all day. The variety of rare bottled drinks is a really cool way to enjoy a refreshing beverage with your meal. I will definitely be back when I'm in the area.

L5wCroM1Tk6IjmA5b2FU_w.text: This was my second time here. I had the double gyro burger.  I thought it was awesome and I was impressed for the second time in a row.  The owner brought out some Mexi Slaw and it had some amazing flavors.  They also have craft sodas on tap now and all of them were very True to taste and not too sweet. Love this place!

BIpngWTEjv7zQrxyzkjNeA.text: Most amazing burgers ever. And I am picky. My family loves it here and the prices are not bad at all. Subs are great too! And the fries with ranch are my daughters favorite. You have to try this place. Thank me later ;)

OOiJDDFBPFxZAiQw5uEwRw.text: This is one of the best dive burger shops in Phoenix.  They have a whole wall dedicated to glass bottle sodas, and you can find pretty much any soda you've ever wanted to try...including some you may not want to try (bacon flavored soda!)...but that's the fun of it.    As far as food and burgers go, there are some real options here like the New York burger which comes with Pastrami, or the Philly Cheesesteak burger, which is also incredible.  They also have hot dogs, subs, desserts, and so much more. There are so many options, which leaves me hesitant at most places because I wonder how they can do so much and still uphold quality, but this place manages to do it (try the ghost pepper cheese on your burger!).    On top of the food and soda, this is a local family-owned restaurant with friendly staff.  I have personally seen the owner talk with a homeless man who walked in and he gave him a drink and made him feel welcome even though the man didn't buy anything.  It's nice to have places like this in the neighborhood, and whenever I am in the neighborhood, I make sure to give this place my business.

S72anzlLYEZeo-g1QDI_2g.text: The Soda Pop Shop is the star of the show here.  The selection is very good.  Plus, I've heard if they  don't have it, they can order it for you.  The food was ok, but not the standout I hoped for.  French fries were served hot, but the burger was not.  Service was fast and friendly.

QC6v5no1wgrvMjFLhNH3uw.text: Holy crap! Can't believe I have never been to this place before. A must go place in PHX. Had the philly burger and country club sandwich on wheat, and both were on point.

tFlFGEqYnIL2M_MGP5voQw.text: Burgers were awesomely awesome! I ordered the Philly double burger and the NY double burger. The burgers were very reasonably priced at $8 a burger. The burgers were humongo!!! The only down side were the fries. They were soggy. I had to place in oven and turn the broiler on for a moment to crisp them up a bit. This was a great place to pick up burgers.

-qL4kQvhVYlSjn0lUeb79g.text: I just happened to stumble upon this place. This place has some awesome food. I live in Avondale and I drive across town to get food from here.

CgVZozkrbMcdgbgP94HRCQ.text: Rocket Burger is totally out of this world! This place blasted into my universe about a year ago and I have been coming in for frequent landings ever since. Rocket has arguably the best burger in Universe! I bet the astronauts on all of those Apollo missions and up on the space station wish they had it this good. Steve and Denis, the owners, are both really nice guys. "Fresh is where it's at" at Rocket Burger and they have over 300 sodas in stock! But hey, don't take my word for it. Let's hear what the Steve and Denis have to say... youtube.com/watch?v=3MqQ... Gotta love that commercial. I wish it played on local TV. I'm telling you this place is seriously really great. I always go with a bacon double cheeseburger, with pickles, onions, jalapenos, and man oh man that Rocket Sauce. I think I could drink it! Good thing I don't though. Check out my picture from this place. I mean seriously, how good does that look?!? I also recommend getting a side of their ranch for your fries. I know, I'm sounding like a total health nut right now, but bear with me. I think this place would be a perfect candidate for Diners, Drive Ins, & Dives. It's T minus 10 and counting until I get in my car and blast off to Rocket Burger and Subs. I'm sure the burger and fries will have another great landing in my belly. Get Your Rocket On!

UW2bY0WNnGh2WiCJ_y151w.text: I can't seem to figure out how this place has such good reviews when the restaurant is filthy dirty.  The walls and ceilings were so dirty along with the grease and mess by the soda machines...I will admit that the burgers are good - the Chicago burger looked super fresh and yummy but the cheese curds were crazy salty.  The soda selection is huge and was fun to look at, but there was literally some homeless guy shooting heroin in the bathroom and the dust and grease on the walls and ceilings is so super gross.  I guess if you're coming here, get the food to go!!

v5Jy5kEQq2jnaubiIDGkoA.text: Really cool Mom and Pop restaurant with the largest selection of refrigerated soda pop I've ever seen. They also serve up some very affordable and tasty food as well.  Inside is very simple with a rocket theme going on here and there. Outside looks pretty old and withered. Could have probably been a convenience store at one time or another. Parking lot is a bit small but achievable. Beep beep!  Ordered way too much food the first time and could barely finish it. They have Hot Dogs, Cheeseburgers, and a large selection of every type of Sandwich known to man. Very large portions. You can even choose Rocket size if you are feeling really hungry.  My favorite so far is going to be the NY Hot Dog which comes with Pastrami, Swiss, Coleslaw and Rocket sauce. Also have enjoyed the spicy Afterburner Chicken Sandwich, the Philly Burger, Mexican Dog, Chili Dog, and Chicago Dog.  Everything comes out fresh and ready to jam in your mouth. Their Fries and Onion Rings are also very delicious. Your meal is not complete without an Ice Cold Soda Pop from the cooler or a nice soothing Homemade Milkshake.  Place can get pretty busy during peak hours. They do have some additional seating next door. Great place to bring the kids and family. Be good and treat yourself to something fun. As Jackie Gleason used to say ... TO THE MOON!  4 STARS

_Hl0aCu30UNvvYKExUKlHg.text: Ordered their Philly burger, and it was so flavorful and juicy. They had the biggest selection of soda I've ever seen. Such friendly staff, too!

r3rvf3vTb8J9rMYRVn9GDQ.text: I was disappointed. We ordered the Italian sub and the New Yorker and both were not that great. We only ate half of the sandwich. We also ordered fries which were greasy. The portion was huge so you can share them. I was grossed out and bloated all day from eating there. They do have a large assortment of different sodas. When we were there the soda fountain was leaking and the floor was wet.  All around the bottom of the walls is dirty which is gross. Maybe they are known for their burgers. I won't be going back to find out though.

MoObIvoKx66cfPRP46RCDQ.text: The reviewers on "Check Please" were right.  This funky little place that I never would have walked into if I hadn't heard about it prior, is really good!  I had the New Yorker, which is as close as I can get to a Miracle Mile New Yorker in NW Phoenix, which was pretty darned good.  My husband had the New York Burger which the same thing with a hamburger patty added to the pastrami and he loved it also.  The only reason I didn't give it five stars is that they serve the string type French fries which I'm not a fan of and wouldn't order next time.  Good luck trying to decide which soda you'll have - they surround the room.

LaK2aH7Lvknrf97cKlu-9g.text: Love the burgers and subs but the fried mushrooms are tasteless

Yj0A0ZjHO10uk9eU_17ScA.text: I ate here a long time ago and today I went back to buy a root beer. As everyone else says, their soda selection is outstanding. They have a very wide ranging menu and seem to have added to it since the last time I was there. I remember the hamburger being very good with a slight peppery taste...which I like. The fries were also well above average and service was friendly and efficient.

uq-fmL2wSaXQLbOBnrCzuA.text: First of all don't judge a book by its cover. Most people would pass up the place from the outside. Which I guess is good for us locals! There are so many great things I can say about this place. First of all the burgers are amazing and quality is consistent. We have been going here since they opened and never have any issues. The staff is so friendly they know you by first name basis. If you are a bottle soda or flavored soda drinker this is the place for you. They have over 5 fridges full of selections to choose from. Now to the good stuff. I recommend that you try the After Burner burger. It is pepper jack cheese, jalapenos, this amazing mayo, and rocket relish...pretty much a pico de gallo. The Onion Rings and Fried Zucchini are coated perfectly and fried crisp not greasy. Don't forget to ask for the ranch it is also a customer favorite. Another good burger is the Cali burger which has fresh avocados on it. They have daily specials as well. Now for dessert don't forget to get a brownie that they make or a chocolate milk shake. For the kid in you they also have slush puppies they remind me of my childhood.   I would say the main reason we go back is the vibe of the restaurant. They are like your family and they make you feel at home. They are the reason you go back!! Keep up the great work Rocket Burger!!!

ggo5VId_vpwIWFWkSj66TQ.text: Holy !##=. What a great local sandwich place. My wife and I had a French dip and Italian. Reminds me of little family owned joints in Philly. We finished it off with chili cheese fries, awesome.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Awesome chili cheese fries.  Plenty of them too,  enough for two.

Pi9n9NbOQqd4WdaT4RCcpw.text: I love burgers there! I've only been there once because I don't live that close but I will definitely go there whenever I am in the neighborhood! I love burgers and if you love burgers then I bet that you will love this place. They really know how to make them!

gUbgf9_KNWHVVyZREguDBA.text: Decided to drive a bit out of the my way to try Rocket Burger & Subs based on the "Yelper" reviews!!  This place is too clean for a "Greasy or a Dive" title, but there food reminds me of some of the BEST greasy/dives out there!    They have a wide variety of food choices and there menu doesn't tell the whole story, so you may need to ask some questions.  When I looked through their burgers I noticed the "Eddie Lopez".    To my surprise there is a better burger topping than bacon...  Hot Pastrami!!!  It was a mouth watering double burger that came with Hot Pastrami stacked on top of the two patties covered in melty-cheesy goodness, toppings and their thousand island dressing.  It was FANTASTIC!!   We also had the "sub of the day" ~ the Big Dipper.  The roast beef was delicious and it had just the right amount of cheese.  Their au jus dipping sauce was not good, but the sandwich was superb.  Their Au jus did not have a beefy taste, it was too thin, too hot and did not set well on the pallet with this sandwich.  Their fries are fresh but a bit too greasy for our taste.  Will try to get them well done on our next visit or try their onion rings.  Their cheese curds were very good!  They do have one of the largest selections of soda, pop in a bottle.  It's fun to try a soda you've never heard about before like an imported micro brew root beer or cream soda!  (Both were very good BTW)  Rocket Burger & Subs, even though it will be extremely hard for me to consider ordering something other than the Eddie Lopez burger, I'm looking forward to my next visit, trying something else and plan to bring some friends with me. If you have not tried RB&S, they are a solid place to "Book Mark"!  Yelpers, what is your favorite Rocket Burger or Sub??

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Eddie Lopez Burger ~ double with hot pastrami!!
Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Big Dipper ~ awesome roast beef with a side of Au jus for dipping!

njBaEKriGirUTuw0Cj8iJA.text: Great soda collection.. Its fun to try new flavors. Food was ok but nothing i really want to go back for.

Fto8dnpCWK8Nv4OXxFWOVA.text: Bacon cheeseburger was perfection. The meat was tender and juicy, cooked to medium perfection, the bacon was crispy and the right proportion to the beef. The lettuce was very finely shredded, onions were diced and blended well with the lettuce to add just the right amount to each bite. The bun was toasted lightly but still fluffy.   The onion rings were very good... corn meal breading that was light and crispy, the onion was soft but didn't pull out of the breading.   The cheese curds were amazing.  They were small, breading was very light and crispy.  The wall of soda is diverse and has something for everyone. I chose the Blenheim Ginger Ale pink cap (the spicier one). I was assisted with my choice which was great because I didn't know the difference between the options.  Staff was knowledgeable and very courteous.  The place has a bright and cheerful environment with "old timey" soda advertisement signs.

qy1umu9GquL3kpdBPE2Xxw.text: Was meeting up with someone for lunch in the area and decided to try it out since some friends have mentioned it before. Kind of an odd parking lot due to a Churches Chicken taking up most of the corner and HS kids are roaming around all the time. Just be patient and roll in. The lady at the counter was very nice, she not only answered our questions but asked a good amount of her own, very personable. I ordered the Cali burger with an egg and the ghost pepper cheese, It. Was. Amazing. The bread, it's always about the bread.. Perfection, amazing texture, kind of like Fuddruckers.  The meat patties were cooked perfectly and were delicious, especially with the fried egg bleeding yolk onto it. The kicker was the ghost pepper cheese, it was a good spicy, very flavorful, not hot just for the sake of being hot. Oh, and they have the largest selection of root beer you can possibly imagine, aaaand I got Dr Pepper.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Cali burger with fried egg and ghost pepper cheese

KgblOlvg112i5oVl9E9VBQ.text: Try the teriyaki burger! The fried pineapple sends it over the top. All those flavors work so well together.  Today I had the New Yorker sandwich on marbled rye. Oh my! That is not a good sandwich, that is a great sandwich!  If you have a favorite soda from your home town that you can't find here in town, you will be able to find it here at Rocket Burgers.  I love this place! It's two guys living out their dream. They get to know their customers and they cook for you as if you're family.
