ANhU6dkP0dCbWlaRpU9pbg.text: Oooooh...  I was a little apprehensive about Rocket. Their vegetarian selection did not look promising. No veggie burger? What?!  We ordered the mushrooms and zucchini to start. Oh-em-geeee! These were home made morsels of joy with a mouthwatering, well seasoned batter.   I ordered a veggie sub and everyone else ordered a burger. The burgers were raved about with every bite. My veggie sub on the other hand? Just so-so. The bread was really good and the quality and variety of veggies was good. Something just didn't work though... I think it didn't have enough mustard/ mayo/ sauce/ dressing. It needed something. And more cheese probably.  We also had fries and cheese curds on the side. Fries were fresh, not frozen. Yay! Cheese curds were tasty.  Soda wall was a bit insane. I'm not a soda person. I was getting a toothache just looking at this wall. I would prefer a beer wall...

B6cJhTd8FRbV9VzYcrVJag.text: Delicious food and a good value!   I've been going to Rocket Burger for years now and I can't get enough of it every time I pop in. Their Teriyaki burger is sublime, among the best I've had (including "gourmet" burgers) and the fries are the perfect balance between crunchy and fluffy.   The selection of sodas are to die for, there's something for everyone.   Though the price is more expensive than a meal at In-N-Out, the difference is well worth it. I spend around $8-10 every time I eat there for a burger, fries, and a bottled drink or two.   This is definitely a must-have for anybody in the Phoenix area.

_76nrGdkK5FYi_J6gdDcUw.text: My goodness, i totally underestimated the size of their "Rocket" sized sandwiches, which are a meal and a half.  I would totally go there again but this time spend a lot less knowing that im going to be more than satisfied with one Rocket sized meal.  They have a ton of variety, and i tried their Mexican sandwich which was great.

HDqdihFH8dVS9CoogBuIMg.text: This place is a hidden gem! Awesome burgers, awesome fries, and the best selection of soda I have ever seen.  Ever I'm ever back on the west side, I will be back.

SVrWiCcjgcuLRdMwpnx9VA.text: I really wanted to love this place, great service as well. Unfortunately the gyro rocket burger just wasn't very good, the bun too small and the gyro meat tasted very processed. I did enjoy the recommended root beer though! The fries are also pretty good. All in all; I think their prices are too high ($11 specialty rocket burger w/o side), but for somebody that appreciates rare sodas this is a good spot.

UZjUSSezH-Fu8qaeIjeNtA.text: I love the soda selection, I love the tie in to the Moon Valley Rockets  referencing the nearby high school.  Clubs, burgers, sandwiches, salads, all have been fantastic.  I don't drink soda, but it's fun seeing so many options, it's like a living soda museum!  It's worth stopping in.

lrpus_gvvxnBvZ5z6D2Aog.text: Very cool place. Right when you walk in a huge fridge of all kinds of different Sodas. 20-30 different kinds of Root Beer, Cream Soda, Etc. Burgers even better. Very unique place.

PpR341ZJuOtFBFUt3cQxcw.text: This restaurant is one of Phoenix's best kept secrets behind the Church's Chicken. The service is topnotch, the food is amazing, and the drink selection is up there with the best of them.   I went there for the first time two days ago with my Mom. I got the recommendation from a couple of friends who share the same love of this kind of food that I do. I ordered the Afterburner Burger and it exceeded my expectations. It had just the right amount of heat. I also ordered fries and onion rings and they did not disappoint. My mom ordered the reuben and it looked pretty good.  The food prices are cheap which made the food taste even better.  Not only is the food good, but they have a huge selection of vintage soda that would blow your mind. They receive extra points for having the Texas born "Dublin Dr. Pepper" in stock.   The owner doesn't talk much but the service is amazing. The ambiance is a little dive-y but it adds to the experience.   All in all, Rocket burger is a great restaurant to chow down on your favorite foods.

mPFEmsdghKWq-fFnDsZarg.text: Burger was big and greasy, if that's the way you like it. Huge root beer selection. HUGE. The owner was great. He stepped from behind the counter to help me pick one out.

57Uug_gkQUM_egzkvU41OA.text: Very nice burger selection (toppings not patty type), I've been here several time for lunch and enjoyed it every time.  Huge selection of soda, more then I have ever seen.  If you don't want a burger try the buffalo Chicken and the fried mushrooms...very good.  Beware, this is not a light meal, better for the younger crowd.

xwuQ3nHEzUfTG54acPAgog.text: After dining here almost every day of his week-long vacation, The Rob has decided that it is not a grease that comes off some of the burgers, (as previously stated) but a sort of au jus sauce, the contents of which is trying to break down with each visit.  Makes me feel a bit better about the massive amounts of beef, fried potatoes and fried cheese he ingested in such a short time.    Oh, and we are super hooked on the fries now too.  Like, craving hooked.  Good for them, not good for me and my estranged relationship with the elliptical machine.  Sigh.

qf6CoROAdQMGqZDJ5y1zQg.text: This was a fun place to try.  Our kids ordered off the pretty typical kids menu, but I absolutely loved the afterburner burger!  My husband and I got it rocket style and split it. That's on a large hoagie roll with three or four hamburger patties spread across it. The horseradish mayo was fantastic and all the ingredients were very fresh including fresh jalapenos. After eating there we went next door to The Pop Shop, which they also own, and bought some unique sodas to take home. Overall, great food and a fun experience!

RfMlPKvWmC7K2HbypAAG-w.text: I had the Chicago Burger. It was a nice,combination of cucumbers, jalapenos, and mustard. The fries were good and the onion rings we 're delicious. We 2njoyed browsing through their sodas. The atmosphere was casual. It was slightly cramped because we had a stroller. The staff was life and friendly. The best hamburger place we found in Phoenix, it was recommended by our family and they were right. It was great.

QyRZ4KSacCeWdchPjf6ebQ.text: One word comes to mind..... YUM!  Everyone is ranting and raving about the burgers (which are  scrumptious), but you need to try the subs here too!!!  The subs here are amazing!  They are a great price and you get a lot of sub for your buck.  The meat, bacon, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, avocado, etc are stuffed into delicious whole wheat bread (they have other types of bread too) and the toppings practically over flow out of the sandwich.  This place is great because they have different types of food to please almost any one and it is all delish.  They have a good selection including burgers, subs, mini corn dogs, salads, gyros, fries, onion rings, etc etc that are all custom made to order.  The burgers are great and I tried the "moo-yorker" on a whim which was delicious.  The fries are fresh cut on site and the kitchen is open.  They also have a HUGE soda collection that has many different types of specialty sodas from all over the place.   I have gone to this restaurant many times and the atmosphere is laid back, casual, and down to the basics.  Good place to go if you have kids.  However, it is a smaller restaurant with limited seating. Also, if you are trying to impress a pretentious date this is probably not the spot for you. The people that work here are all very friendly, helpful, and has a family owner-ship vibe.    Basically.....  This restaurant has yummy food and great prices.  I definitely recommend that you stop by if your in the area!

6WSrSCmMVyHnsUHsPH3Y_Q.text: I stopped here with my four year old yesterday with a Groupon.  We had lunch here.  I had a gyro with fries; he had a hotdog and fries.  The fries were simply amazing!  Perfectly prepared and delicious.  The gyro was done perfectly - not burnt or dry.    The interior is nothing special - a tv, some chairs and tables.  The people behind the counter are terrific.    If you like soda, this is the place for you.  They even had my home town favorite - FAYGO!  Plenty of great energy drinks.  The prices are reasonable.  Stop by.........

kG7V8XaZGAX2gtZsttwEKQ.text: YEOW, BABY!  I love this place.  I don't know how I got there the very first time, but I sure am glad I got there.  Went there tonight, and as always, was greeted like I was a long lost friend.  I love the smell of this place, as well as the taste of the food.  And I even stop there, sometimes, just for a bottle of red, cream soda.  I even ordered a root beer float, and there was so much ice cream in it, that I was miserable, when I left.  What can I say, I'm a glutton, when I eat, here.  Thank you, guys, for doing such a great job, with this little place.  I tell everyone about you.

vWJebmCRijnjug3IchRLdg.text: Yes, I know, this is my 2nd update so I'll try to make it short & sweet.   I bought a Groupon about a week ago & decided to use it this past Saturday when the hubs & I were trying to think of a place to have lunch. I got the chili cheese dog this time & it was delicious! Cheese burger & onion rings were freakin yum as usual & I have to say the fries were better this time around. We went a lil crazy & got 4 additional sodas, along with the 2 we had during lunch, 2 root beers, 2 cream sodas & 2 orange sodas. I also have to add, since this was our 1st time dining in, how clean it was! They had a girl at the register this time & she was super sweet.  We love this place!!

R5ieF3hBIdc08E_1S214jw.text: First and foremost - DON'T BE SHOCKED BY THE LOCATION OR FIRST IMPRESSIONS!  This place is awesome, has a great selection of drinks (especially root beers), and the value of the sandwiches is over the top!  Don't forget to try the onion rings. They use their own breading made out of corn meal and spices. The amount of food you get is a great value.  I travel the nation weekly, and will be visiting here again in the future.

ypCW3oJrqBDsDUQ4vfchrQ.text: This place is awesome. The food is great and they have just about any soda you could want and the fries are killer. Im lucky that this place is so close to where I live that I can eat there just about anytime I want. I still cant decide what burger is better the Teriyaki Burger, Philly Burger, or the New York Burger. They are all so good.

-Zc_emPF5THPlx9_XHkPHA.text: Rocket Burger is the best burger in Glendale. Maybe all of Phoenix. I'm not big on sandwiches or hot dogs from anywhere so I'm not judging them on that, but the burgers are enough to give these guys 5 stars all on their own.

GLv91Vm8o3bWpMqQ-mYFBw.text: I wish I would have found this place must sooner!! Rocket Burger & Subs, where have you been?  This place is amazing!  Their food is fresh ~ cooked after it's ordered.  They have several burger and sandwich options to chooses from with different sides.  They have the LARGEST cola in a bottle selection I've ever seen and they have super service!  Food~ Rocket burger was awesome! burger patties cooked to perfection and trimmed to fit on a sub role.  The role was fresh and my burger came with lots of veggies and dressing.  The fries were awesome ~ cooked fresh like mom makes them.  We also had their onion rings based on the Yelp reviews, YUM!  The cola selection is mind blowing! I'm going to keep coming back until I've tried each one : -)

lmK5e_AbziYFtJYeClupXA.text: This is an awesome place! We would come here again. The burgers and sandwiches are huge! The soda is awesome!

DaBwIOd-UNDI4_KBUT-iOA.text: Was looking for a good burger joint and this is it! Had the double Chicago burger and fries and it was outstanding! Place has a huge selection of soft drinks and pretty good fries. It's a little divy, but I prefer that. Highly recommended.

5hcJ3YSEWCPym5YTEdrqDw.text: This place rocks for value!!. I just had a California Sub and it was FANTASTIC! extra sweet coleslaw with pastrami stuffed in a fresh yogi roll. I really reccomend this one.  This place is kinda tucked away behind Churches Chicken but way worth the trip. They even have exotic sodas in bottles including REAL DR PEPPER. You should try it sometime. Best of all they now have Pepsi in the Fountain drink. A perfect compliment to an awsome sandwich.  If your on a budget and want to get stuffed come here you won't be dissapointed!

5dtUaNhG4NB1DhX-GyxJOw.text: Lots of retro sodas to choose from! Nice locally owed burger joint that also serves gyro's, and other sandwiches.  You gotta love a place that cuts their own spuds at least I do.  I had the cheeseburger special for 3.99 nice size patty, fries and a drink with free refills.

31dXz2n2yHE6GY_sAQbQUA.text: Rocket burger has been on my bookmark/bucket list of places to try and this was my first time here today.  I got the cheese burger special for 4.99 includes fries and a drink , plus the 10% off if you check in through yelp . The cheeseburger had really good flavor it was dressed with the usual and what made it so special was the burger sauce. The sauce had a little bit of a kick , not too much but enough to make you want more. The only negative is the bun was too thick for my taste, but I ripped the inside of the bun and enjoyed the burger . The fries seems to be hand cut and I think they are cooked in some kind of veggie oil like Crisco.  They looked better than they tasted. Then again everyone has their own preference in what they think is a good French fry. Who knows it might be your cup of tea. Oh and by the way they had a crazy cool collection of soda pop.

MUPgisLNqLueUtfM0qAszg.text: Sandwiches and subs not what I expected. The place is dirty.  All the tables were dirty. Fountain drinks were out of order.

WgJ4zp_YtpCAZQmRDczMNg.text: My niece and I were having that conversation...where do you want to eat...I don't know where do you want to eat when we drove past the Rocket Burger corner.  I turned around to try it because of good Yelp reviews and my curiosity regarding the variety of Soda Pop.  We both got a large hot pastrami sandwich and soda pop.  The price was reasonable, the food was good and the soda pop made it a nostalgic experience.  I brought home half of my sandwich.  Just reheated it in the microwave and enjoyed it again.  I'll return to try the french dip sandwich on the menu.  P.S.  The meat and secret sauce gave the sandwich a great bite.  It blows away the 'roast beef' sandwich I had last week at Subway that looked like reconstituted meat.

SRvTKt0HKTsDGB5RI6zMxQ.text: Best teriyaki burger I've ever had! Great tasting fries and fried zucchini. A hole in the wall place, looks like it used to be a convenience store, but such a fun little eatery. Soda selection is unique,  we bought 4 different ones to try at home. The owner is a sweet Filipino lady and so fun to talk to! I support you, rocket burger. We will definitely be coming back!!!

IE3QTR6ROrlIjx_k7Zt96A.text: Had the Cali burger. it was good. my wife had a pastrami sandwich. it had more coleslaw than pastrami, rather disappointing. soda selection was unbelievable, overall, it was middle of the road. staff very friendly.

kL_FtJNxWrjeo1wI49Bjkw.text: Thank you Yelp, for another great find in the ASU West area!  Hand breaded onion rings, homemade chili, and a wall full of sodas--I hope I sold you already. If not, try cheap. Like ridiculously cheap for every menu option.  Not much ambiance, but for a great burger, who's complaining? I like the bare bones decor, and I'm sure the high school kids would destroy anything more than that. Speaking of high school kids, if you want to avoid those heathens try to make to Rocket Burger before 2:30pm!

7n-lV-_jhQEe5Ph5kfy8hg.text: I can't believe I ate the whole burger! This place is a hidden gem. I have lived in the valley for over 15 years and have driven past this intersection many times. Recently a friend told me about the best hamburger he has ever had. I went to rocket burger not expecting anything but a regular hamburger. OMG was I wrong!! I had the chili burger and I could not believe how good it was. I will definitely be back. Thank you Rocket burger for this wonderful food!

DaVbba65aMPoH0-ITWeUGw.text: I wont be suprised if the account mgr w yelp that handles this restaurant takes this review down. Looked at reviews and got excited, sped down here bc they closed in a few minutes. Was amazed by the huge selection of bottles soda. It was quite impressive. Liked the simple, easy to order recipe. The food on the other hand stinked. The chilli dog was bland. The Chicago dog was good. And the onion ring and fries were prob the worst I've had at a quick svc restaurant. This is my 5th bad yelp rec, and it's sad. No one likes to eat bad food. Well in this case, I ate a few bites :(

1TyjxvxRo-AyRQ8Xb4OZPQ.text: A hidden gem.  Came here today for the first time. We weren't sure what to order and the young man behind the counter recommended the NY Burger which is what we order. Also we ordered the fries and the fried zucchini. The burger was cooked perfectly and it had a wonderful flavor. The fries were good and the zucchini was outstanding! 6SlO9wLAGm4U3SIE6dMqBw.text: Okay so I've said before that I'm a big fan of owner operated businesses, and small local businesses. This place is one of them. You walk in the door and to your left are six refrigerator doors chocked full of about 250 different specialty sodas. All priced at a $1.89 and to your right there are the two owners and two helpers. One of the owners is at the cash register and handling the customer service and the other is that the sandwich table whipping up delicious hamburgers subs and the like. Very friendly and helpful!!!!!   While I was there I asked a couple questions of the owners. One was do they weigh the meat before they load it into the sandwich? The guy at the sandwich making table shook his head no and said we want to make it good. Indicating they just cut a lot in there until it looks right. Needless to say my sandwich was well portioned. Rand H. and I both got a Large Ruben on Sourdough and split an order of fries. I really like this place for a lot of reasons, some of which I noted in my review. While we were eating I saw a few more orders roll by and they were all generous servings that looked delish.

hLnwOqChqZwKf8xCZTGkTg.text: I write this review as my boyfriend is next to me in a food coma! He just got back from a hiking trip and wanted a burger and fries. So I jumped on Yelp to see what we could find. After looking at a few places, we decided on Rocket Burger and Subs. When we walked through the door we were greated right away. Something I look for and think is very important. We were amazed at the soda selection! Some sodas I've haven't seen in YEARS! They even have Slush Puppies!!! What???? Yeppers, they sure do! We both decided on the birch beer. Sooooo good! I went simple and got a cheeseburger and fries. BF got a pastrami with cole slaw sandwich and fries. We go in and the menu was clear, and the prices were awesome. We got a double new york burger, and cali burger, and a regular burger, onion rings, chili cheese fries, and 3 soda's, for 33.00! 8mBsTdTv2uollharBIufZg.text: A small independent burger joint with unique menu. It's stuck in the small shopping center behind the fried chicken place, on the corner. If you didn't know what you where looking for, you would miss it. You'd best not however, because it's that good!   The menu is a mix of burgers, sandwiches and hot dogs. You can have fries or onion rings, and then there is your drink selection, that's where you can be sure of having some fun making up you mind. If you are a fan of nostalgia and love the old and new, you can rest assured that they will have something that will satisfy both. There is everything from cream soda's to root beer, they even have chocolate soda!   I had the classic bacon cheese burger with onion rings. The burger was cooked just right with extra crispy pieces of bacon melted cheese, lettuce, tomato and pickles. The onion rings was coated with corn meal batter and fried to golden brown. It was a great choice.   The locals seemed to be happy, service was great, and owner seemed genuinely interested in who was eating at his place and how we had discovered it. Overall, a good burger and well worth coming back for!

Kt1WX7eHy-DLwadNsvbSFQ.text: Much like Google search words, Hot, Spicy, Jalapeno, Habanero, "Don't do it", on a menu make me salivate like Pavlov's dog.  Most of the time I'm mildly amused or deeply unsatisfied with the level of heat and flavor from whatever it is I've ordered.  Enter the Afterburner burger from Rocket Burger.  Pepper jack cheese, horseradish mayo, fresh jalapenos, rocket relish, lettuce, tomato, pickle, onions.  Your stomach, not you, should be required to sign off on this before consumption begins.  The horseradish mayo was atomic horseradish, I know because I use it in my cocktail sauce at home.  This is not for young children or those that eat like them.  As powerful as the burger was, it wasn't that memorable or something I would want to go back for.  The bun was a little oversized for a single burger, I think they must sell a lot of doubles or bigger so the buns are probably completely right-sized for those, but both me and The Princess thought the buns were a little large.  The P had a basic burger, no cheese,  just tomato, mustard, catsup and she thought the burger was passable.  She loved the fries, I thought they were ok.  As it's been well documented on Yelp, the soda collection is legendary, you name it or want a certain flavor of soda, it's probably there, cold and ready to enjoy.  It's most likely the largest collection of bottle soda pop in the state.  This is my second time here and I feel like I'm missing something for a joint that has 4.5 stars.  I'd much rather enjoy a great burger from Lenny's or Five Guys (the Five Guys little burger with everything and jalapenos is one of my all-time favorite burgers).  I'll come back one last time and try a dog (thanks for the tip Mark R!).  Until then, a solid three stars.

jlVUwK9KtYTFRmr4k7blUQ.text: So thankful to find this local gem. Is the dining area a little small? Yep. Nothing fancy here (and it sits to the side of a Church's chicken, not a Canes - and I've never had any issue with ample parking). That said, I don't come here for the ambiance, I come here for the food!   Their service is second only to their burgers, and while the burger patty itself is nothing special, the combinations of toppings and styles they offer are nothing short of spectacular for the price. Also, if you're a fan of fried zucchini - this is *the* place. The amount of food you get is more than satisfactory and man does it taste good!!  It's small, but it's clean. It's super friendly, reasonably priced, and ... well... it's wonderful! It would be hard to go wrong in here, highly recommended!

z5kpsMK_qdewdnCRZcaAbw.text: Three different burgers for our family and all winners!  I highly recommend the Santa Fe burger as the best I have ever had.  Green chili peppers smashed and fried with a light cornmeal batter and added to the cheeseburger. Note that a "single" is definitely a lot of food, so only the big eaters will go for the next size up. Fried cheese curds are a treat and a basket is more than plenty for three.  Finding out that the Pop Shop has become part of Rocket Burger & Subs is a wonderful bonus:  imagine choosing from over 200 soft drinks for a memorable meal.  Staff were terrific and perhaps think about going early in the dinner hour.  We noticed as it got closer to 6 pm, more and more customers came in. We'll be back on a regular basis.

0gPUk1hfDXj36RNMnNCL8w.text: I've wanted to try this place based on the Yelp reviews. Bad decision! I honestly had to think twice about going in this place. It's not well lit in the parking lot and there were, in my opinion, unsavory people hanging around outside asking for change.  So, against my better judgement, I went in and was a bit confused at the theme/decor. I thought it was a liquor store, at first glance, but quickly realized it was an assortment of craft sodas. They even have two types of self serve soda stations. One, with the typical sodas (Cherry Pepsi, Tropicana lemonade, etc) and the other had craft soda flavors like Shirley Temple, Black Cherry  and a few others. I filled my cup with the Shirley Temple...yum.  When you go to order, there was an older guy standing/waiting at the counter to take your order. Don't expect any suggestions, even after advising it was my first time there and that the sandwich menu was "overwhelming ". It wasn't until I asked for a vegan option that he advised for an upcharge of $1, I could substitute a veggie pattie. I did. I ordered the California burger with the veggie pattie. It had Avocado, lettuce, tomato and something similar to a Comeback sauce which I got on the side.  $12+ later/lighter and I couldn't eat the fries because they were too hard, dry and old. The color tells me the grease should be changed. The burger initially looked delicious, but I judged the book by its cover. The bun and lettuce was fresh, but the veggie pattie was dry and some parts were inedible. Long story short, I threw it all away. The best part of the meal was the craft soda .  My only regret is that I forgot to mention Yelp for a 10% discount.  Maybe if I ate beef I would have had a better experience, but that's no excuse for bad fries. It's sacrilege. Overpriced and disgusting! Buyer beware and take security.

P_ZGBMEoov5ajc_Enl8rUw.text: Wow this place has really gone down hill. They tout their new 24 flavors of icecream. That is a joke too. They take vanilla soft serve out it in a hopper with a squirt of flavoring and then it comes out and goes into a cone. 8egahW8Nu3UFZ-xLu4JMcw.text: Rocket Burger's homemade onion rings are some of the best I've ever had. I love the California burger, and the gyro burger is super awesome. CP8Gk_OkVJ2UFZ34oJTlaQ.text: Dave was craving a cheeseburger sub, which I thought were nonexistent out here; however, after a quick search on yelp we found this place and it wasn't too far, only about 10 miles. I was hoping to find that little gem, but unfortunately I didn't. I had a single cheeseburger, I liked everything except the rocket sauce...no matter what you call it, it's 1000 island on all these burgers (In/Out, McD's and every other burger place with special sauce is either straight up 1000 island or some variant of it), and normally I like it; however, I did not care for this particular version. It was watery.  I did like the actual burger.  Again, I'm a lover of onion rings and I was super excited to see all the great reviews, until I actually tried them. I didn't care for them at all. The breading was horrible, I ate them because I was hungry...the breading did not grow on me!   The selection of sodas was amazing, they have an extensive menu, the prices are extremely reasonable, the service friendly, the customers eclectic, but the overall quality of the meal was just 3 stars for me.

8suyRuBu0EAQA69k_S3Jrw.text: A hidden gem. Awesome place. Best selection of drinks ever. Great subs, and kind workers. Don't let the exterior scare you off, great place to eat.

t1EcgjJwlzlhLsK8jE1WKQ.text: There bugers are awesome! I got the new York burger it is amazing. With fried mushrooms you can't go wrong. I will drive across town for the burgers! The inside could use a revamp design wise. Don't think twice if your in the area you can't go wrong!

TPN_fCKP0wViLdHbts346w.text: Okay, let's get this straight...there are pros and cons here.  Pro: I think they have more soda than Rocket Fizz. It's all refrigerated and ready to drink! Pro: They have a Santa Fe Burger which involves a battered, deep-fried green chili which is utter genius. I repeat, Utter Genius. Pro: The burgers are well-crafted with attention to detail and carefully laid out, not assembled by an uncaring worker and squished into a wrapper quickly. Pro: They have Pepsi products on fountain in case for some reason ~300 types of bottled soda (most made with Real Cane Sugar OH YEAH) just doesn't do it for you and you need to blend your own suicide-soda. Pro: They will make any soda you want into a float, using soft-serve, for a buck! Pro: Locally-owned by a guy who seems pretty nice and genuinely interested in his customers and their thoughts. That's a HUGE PLUS, people...pay attention!  Pro: The burgers' pickles are good! they don't taste like run-of-the-mill, cheap, food purveyor 5 gallon bucket pickles. Pro: They have a website that seems to be pretty current, it alerted me to the fact that they have some of the last remaining Dublin Dr. Pepper in the world and I should buy now. (Disclosure: While I like Dr. Pepper - I'm not a superfan, and have never tried it - so I figured the $15/6packs were better left to the superfans and collectors). Pro: The building seems to be laid out in an "L" fashion, with the soda selection and main tables on one side; and an 'extra" area of seating on the other side of the kitchen that seems to have a pass-thru ordering window. That probably comes in pretty handy during lunch rush when the kids from the hi-skool next door probably mob the place. We didn't notice this until we were leaving...so I'll have to explore that next time.  Con: The signs telling you about the $1 float options are too high to notice until you've already ordered. Perhaps this is another stroke of genius to encourage repeat business, perhaps its an oversight. Con: It's an older property, so it doesn't have that super-clean feeling about it. It's not dirty by any means...but it's at that stage of life where its not sterile, but not quite yet charming. Of course, this whole part of town is at that stage - so you can't really hold that against the place. Con: Soft-serve rather than real ice cream.  It's not that I hate soft-serve, I give it its credit...but I prefer real ice cream. (Disclosure: if they used real ice cream, I'd probably bitch about that too, because I'm kind of a dairy snob). Con: Shoestring potatoes. I know they have the skin on, and are natural-cut, and shoestrings have millions of loyal followers...I'm not one of them. Give me a tater-tot any day.  Other things of note: My single burger was BIG. You can also go double or Rocket Burger, which is 3 patties on a sub roll. I can't imagine eating that - but I'm sure its a fave amongst many!  Bottom line: Pros obviously outweigh cons and the fact that it is a family-owned/run business always weights positive in my book! We'll be back.

French fries were fresh-cut, flavorful and perfectly fried. Their fries alone will get me to come back.   I had a couple bites of my husband's burger which was very good! The bacon was cooked to the right amount of crispness and the bun tasted fresh baked (although I didn't verify)  The meats on my Italian sandwich were awesomely thick cut. If I get this sandwich again I'll probably ask for some Italian dressing on the side to dip.   Little guy's hot dog was HUGE!!! The outside skin was nice and crisp so it snapped when you bite into it.   In addition to the regular fountain drinks, they have a set of specialty fountains that contain root beer, black cherry, ginger beer, etc as well as hundreds of bottled specialty sodas. This place is awesome!

iJb2ACec1oqw4046fDQvlQ.text: Heard these rocket burgers take you to the moon and back so I said why not give 'em a try!  Location & Aesthetics - located in Phoenix just off W Cactus Road at the intersection of N 35th & W Cactus Road.  The business is behind a Raising Cane's and I almost missed it as I had to swing around on N 35th Ave. Parking was on the dismal side and there weren't enough spots available.  Luckily, I snagged that last remaining parking spot.  I'm unsure where I would've parked if there weren't any available spots....perhaps in Raising Cane's parking area (-1). Interior decor is interesting as they have pictures of famous figures from sports and other areas with the accompanying prices of things from yesteryear, e.g. the cost of a soda in the '40's or '50's. Seating was adequate and comfortable, and the dining areas was clean.  Along one wall was lined a wide selection of soda pop which was interesting.  Many different names and bottle shapes that is a must see if visiting.   One negative was the dining area was on the small side so if you're coming with a party of more than 5, you may have to put some of the tables and chairs together (-1), and sadly there's no outdoor seating.  Menus - posted on a chalk board above the cashier who also takes your orders.  There are more detailed menus on the countertop which we were given.        Service - Staff was very warm and welcoming, and answered any questions we had about the menu items. If dining in, staff will bring your food to the table.    Food - I had the double cheeseburger, fries and a strawberry shake.   The shake tasted like there were real strawberries used, very creamy and thick, and very well mixed.   The fries looked they were freshly cut with the potato skin still on them - crunchy, well seasoned, tasty, not too overcooked or limp, and not over salted. The burger was juicy, well seasoned, tasty, not very greasy or runny, and cooked perfectly.  I am interested in trying some of their other inventions and will probably return though will probably order for take-out because of the lack of parking!

HXVYSUMfbdUOV1esR6Ybyg.text: This is one of the best places for Philly style cheesesteak in the Phoenix area! The fries are also awesome as well as the humongous choices of unique bottled soda pop!

nya08ZO_qqUIk3GSGtt9lg.text: I had gone once before and didn't like my burger because it was all soggy and falling apart, gave this place a second chance and we'll the burger was pretty bomb and cream sodas are a must try, take the fam you'll all enjoy it!

WIr_wtAf705v5si6_pp9Cw.text: Rocket Burger is a staple to the neighborhood that I grew up in. I've been visiting this place pretty much since they opened up. Their food is top notch for what you would consider a fast food joint.   FOOD: So I have tried a few items on the menu over the years. My absolute favorite used to be their Tuna Sub that was discontinued because I was told that not enough people were ordering it and they were wasting a bunch of tuna. Which is sad because the sub was amazing and just great. I did try a Ruben Sandwich once and wasn't too keen on it. I mainly didn't care for it just because I took it home and the bread was soggy, but the meat and flavor was amazing. My new favorite food item on their menu is the Garlic Melt Burger. The flavor is incredible and the burgers are always cooked just right. Don't forget to grab an order of their cheese fries. They are terrible for you, but they taste amazing and are well worth it. Of course you cannot forget about the ridiculously wide selection of soda pops that you can buy and try.   SERVICE: I have never had any issues with service here. The staff is primarily all the original workers who are awesome and really dedicated to some great food.   OVERALL: Rocket Burger is an incredible neighborhood spot to stop by and grab a soda and burger. They have a ton of menu options for food to try that are all good. I wish they would bring the tuna back, but completely understand. I would highly recommend this place to anyone and I have suggested it for years now.

Eki7pdy3OEj1A8OsuWuRjw.text: Gourmet soda galore! From the street this small shop is located in the corner of a strip mall and I actually drove past it because it's so unassuming and easy to miss from the main street. The whole back wall is filled with so many different soda brands, organized by flavor.   The menu was quite comprehensive and due to the lunch line that was forming behind me, I decided to be basic and just ordered a single cheeseburger and onion rings. The burger patty was thin with a lot of bread so I think I now know why they offer double or triple patties to order. The side of onion rings was huge and they came served with two sides of ranch - score!   My favorite part of this experience was all of the cool soda flavors and I am super stoked they sell a staple from my home state, Faygo pop, here!

AW8eLe7rxm50938IpRhnBQ.text: My wife and I were jones'ing for a burger joint and this place popped up in my Yelp feed.  We had never been and decided to give it a shot. It's a fairly convenient location and it looks like to-go orders are the bulk of their business.  The restaurant itself is clean, but not much for atmosphere or ambiance.  I've no idea what it used to be, but it's a long narrow building.  Convenient store?  Liquor store?  Laundromat?  I've absolutely no idea, but there's not much for relaxation.  Probably not a place you'd go for a 1st date, but that's OK.    We ordered when we got there and only waited 10 minutes or so.  I went with the Chicago-style burger and it did not disappoint.  Burger was juicy and flavorful.  The fries were a healthy portion in a large piece of foil.  Not soggy.  Not burned.  Very flavorful and seasoned to perfection.  Not quite as many fries as the shitload you get from the cooks at Five Guys, but still a healthy portion of french fries.  Service was friendly, attentive and our order was accurate.  Definitely a step above fast food and we shall be back for another to-go / takeout order!

Burgers are real beef patties and offer the expected as well as a few surprises, my personal favorite is the New Yorker which is a hand patty piled high with NY pastrami and coleslaw from scratch. If you want something a bit spicier, go for Santa Fe which comes with fried green chilies just like New Mexico. If you're from the upper Midwest the cheese curds cannot be skipped- the best cheese curds in the Valley.

NJQxes4FK3HTmoxNMtoesA.text: As far as fancy fast-food goes, this is THE SPOT for a perfectly fried fish sandwich or an immense Chicago dog or literally any burger. You will not walk away disappointed, you will, however, walk away with a major food coma. Countering your food coma, you can get hyped with their large variety of sodas. A selection of sodas which have not seen the light of day since Baby Boomers roamed the Earth in the hundreds of millions.   Remember folks this isn't health food, this is the food you eat when you know the consequences all too well but continue on your death march. Because honestly, life is too short to not enjoy yourself every once in a while. Cheat meal, OH YES.

ySNZaVSDl0PiZAtHZ7keRQ.text: Nestled in a decrepit strip mall next to an auto loan place is a burger shop that screams...       "Go away! We were shut down by the health department! Stay away! Leper! Leper!"       Do not listen to those wailing cries in your head. That is to scare away mundane eaters who like boring, institutional burger chains with their consistently average products that are advertised nationally. Once you get past the exterior and enter the doorway, you will find the Willy Wonka Chocolate Factory of burger greatness.       The Philly Steak Burger was amazing. The bacon cheeseburger was among the best I've ever had, with a very slight spice that may have come from the savory pickles they put on it. In addition, this place has the largest collection of bottled soda and (non-alcoholic) beverages I have ever seen. All of which you can purchase to consume with your masterfully made meal.        You can order your burgers as a 'single', a 'double' or something called a 'rocket'. Find our for yourself what that last one means.       What cinches the deal is the price. Killer burgers at a reasonable price.        Tip #1: If you get a brownie for dessert, ask them to heat it up and put ice cream on it.       Tip #2: If you get there on a week day at about 3:00 or later expecting it to be empty as it's between lunch and dinner, take heed the a local school gets out just before that time and it shall not be as empty as you think- not just students but teachers and coaches frequent this place.

apFZ84coKLYX1R1yRLQrVA.text: The area is pretty sketchy, but the burger was great.  There were tons of interesting menu items and I wish I could try each one, but I went with the standard cheese burger.  Of course I had to get it "Rocket" style though.  The burger plus an order of fries could have easily been a challenge on Man vs. Food.  With that said I couldn't finish the fries and burger which is a rarity for me.  For about ten bucks it was a pretty good value and well worth it.  The burger was well seasoned, cooked perfectly and wasn't greasy.  The bun held up great so I didn't make a mess of my shirt as is almost always the case when I have a burger.  I will definitely return because the Eddie Lopez burger has my name all over it!

Xm-gw0XI0apxYoHTTsNlDg.text: This place is a little hole in the wall. Tucked in to a small strip behind Church's Chicken. Worth looking for! Juicy, flavorful burgers. E0O0-9UeNXF5_rgsjrfrAw.text: I've been coming here off and on pretty much since the place opened, but took a break of about a year. Recently, however, I'm not sure if I can still think of it as 4-star, because of the inconsistency that appears to have woefully only happened to me based on these reviews.  The last burger I ordered looked and smelled wonderful until I picked it up and so much rocket sauce ran out that I considered hooking up my pool draining equipment to siphon some of it out. Rather overpowering. After scraping some off, I took a bite and holy black pepper! It was like an employee played a prank and unscrewed the top of the pepper shaker and instead of making a new burger thought "eh, they might like coughing and gasping for breath while army-crawling to the sink for water". After shoveling off the pepper, I enjoyed the burger. They have great buns and I know great buns, because I do daily squat thrusts.  Well, aside from the fact that half of the burger was medium-rareish (I like) and the other half well-done (nooo!). Not sure how that was managed.  Fries: completely inedible. The oil was obviously not hot enough. The only texture was soggy followed by waves of oil coating my mouth.  I'll keep occasionally going there, but probably never at nights again. The kitchen staff looked rather young. I recall that I used to stop by on school day afternoons, back when I would have easily given this pace 4-stars.

XBGhoNzewre5jUYF2zTaIA.text: I saw all the great reviews for this place and decided to try them. The New York burger was terrible. Thin flavorless  patty and the bun was not fresh. The only good part of the order were the onion rings and fries. For the money Five Guy's or even In and Out Burger are so much better. Don't  waste your time or money. What a shame!

2JtfvmTHLDaOXGdM4TuYMA.text: I was wary of trusting Yelp after the debacle of culinary excrement served to me at Wineburger, but Rocket Burger delivered the beefy goods. GvTfSqPBYBfuvvAas3jMLA.text: OK I will admit I am pretty ashamed of myself here. I did not realize I had not reviewed this place yet. SHAME ON ME!!!  I have been here half a dozen times and this place always makes me smile, and full.  The food here is awesome, dozens of Burgers, Hot Dogs, sides and do not forget the fried Cheese Curds. Then there is the infamous Rocket Burger. You can get any burger turned into a Rocket Burger (on a sesame seed sub bun) it is delicious but you have to have a huge stomach.  Sometimes I will stop in just to get a 6 pack of soda and then spend 20 minutes deciding which one I want. I believe I counted approx 360+ sodas?  They also have slush puppies, I have not seen or had these since I was a kid.  I would love to see this place expand it is awesome. All of the food I have tried was extremely good.  My kids beg to come here for dinner all the time!  ...Why are you still reading this and not driving to this place? GO!!!

PU7YoqLnMwrffQ954xotFw.text: We are from So. Cal., have travelled far/wide in southwest/more & have never had as good a green chile cheeseburger anywhere. This scrumcious burger is called the Santa Fe Burger. Veggies (tomatoes, onions pickles), cheese, fried green chile, bacon & rocket sauce. The depth, taste, & texture was amazing. Served hot in a perfect crunchy outside/soft inside bun! Was not sure about a fried chile, thinking it may be heavily dipped/fried, but it was 'heavenly' breaded & fried to perfection, not oily, but fairly thick & crisp, adding another dimension to the old standby found in many New Mexico burger shops. Don't think it was the unsurpassed New Mexico Hatch chili which is the only thing that would improve this outstanding burger. I had the single which I could not finish because of its size & hubby had the double which he did finish. Num!  Fries were not memorable. Oil not hot enough, I believe.  They wilted as they cooled.  Next time we'll try the onion rings, zucchini, or mushrooms. Apparently for these other veggies, they use the same coating as the above-mentioned chili in the burger.    We stuck w/ the regular soda machine, but hundreds of choices in chilled bottles are behind glass to choose from.  Wish we were staying one more night so we could go back and totally ruin our diets! Ha!  Excellent price points, as well. Get yourselves over there before they have to expand to a pricier market.

0vTJJCxb1qnez_BjzERNeA.text: Who doesn't love a good neighborhood burger joint?  I will emphasize the "good" and "joint" on this one because chances are even this little hole-in-the-wall will surprise you.  I had seen the great reviews on Yelp as well as the Phoenix New Times about this place, so I decided to take a chance on grabbing lunch here on a Friday.  I was a little apprehensive about coming just because of the proximity to Moon Valley High School (it's literally next door).  Lunch + Friday + high school conjures up images of when I and hoards of classmates used to go to our favorite lunch spots with friends during high school.  Worse yet, the place is in a tiny old strip mall with almost no parking.  Shockingly, the place wasn't busy at all and I easily got a parking spot.  When you walk in you almost feel like you've stumbled upon an old convenience store as you immediately notice the soda machines, the large refrigerator area full of soda, and even the soda six packs on the shelves.  Notice a theme here?  Yeah, they've got A LOT of soda.  In fact they claim to have the widest variety of sodas to choose from in the state.  As in the entire state of Arizona!  I have no way of verifying this claim, but I did indeed see many soda brands and flavors I had never seen before from chocolate to watermelon, to lemon, and on and on.  If you're a soda junkie, you'll be in heaven here.  But I came for one reason, the burgers.  They actually have a variety of hot dogs, gyros, and submarine sandwiches as well, but its Rocket "Burger".  I saw one person eating a Rocket sized burger which is insanely huge (basically a submarine burger sandwich with at least 4 patties by my count).  I wasn't feeling that bold so I went with a bacon double cheeseburger instead and got a side of fries.  The burger was excellent.  Hearty portion with plenty of cheese and bacon and their special sauce (basically a rendition of thousand island from what I could tell).  The fries were pretty average so nothing special there.  All totaled, the burger, fries and a drink were $8.  The dining area is pretty small with tables, chairs and a couple of booth.  But like I said, it wasn't crowded and I was easily able to get a seat.  I was in and out in about 20 minutes  Overall, a pretty cool place and certainly unique to the west side of town.  The fries were really the only big negative of this place.  Burger was great, prices are right, and the soda selection will blow your mind.

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Pretty small place, but the soda  selection is nuts

All the ingredients were well balanced. The pastrami in the burger was so tender and juicy. The coleslaw had a lot of great flavor to it, along with the tasty sauce.   I really enjoyed the French fries. Some of my favorite french fries.   My husband had the Cali burger. The cheese in it looked so luscious on top of the patties, bacon, and avocado that I had to try it. I definitely recommend the Cali and new york burger. The bread, ingredients, and protein were all incredibly delicious and my taste buds can concur! ;)

FWbggHNYCjqrE9Dkw2xa9Q.text: This place is awesome.   I wish I lived closer... actually I take that back, if I lived closer I'd gain 50 pounds because I would be here every other day.   The claim to fame at Rocket Burger & Subs, I would say, isn't the Burgers or the Subs... It's the assortment of soda. That rhymed. See how I did that? Assortment of Sodas. Sorry, I'm easily distracted.   Anyhow, there are so many sodas. I had heard about this soda assortment. There I go rhyming again like P-Diddy. But I don't think you can really appreciate it until you see it.   Being a craft beer fan, I first tried a root beer made by Abita, a brewer based out of Louisiana. I don't even consider myself a liker of root beer but it was a solid choice.   As far as food, I got a chili dog which was good, but didn't knock my socks off because I was wearing sandals. Flip flops, I think... because I'm classy.   I did however really like the fried mushrooms. So good. The breading tastes like they surely make it in house. Being from the south originally it reminded me of the breading used on really good fried green tomatoes. So what am I saying here? I'm saying I would like the owner of RBS to consider making fried green tomatoes. But if they don't, it's fine because they also have a fried zucchini that is fantastic.   I couldn't get get through the meal with out a second soda so I got a Swamp Pop Cola, another Louisiana drink. I didn't plan the Louisiana soda theme, but it worked out because it was pretty good as well.  Will I be back to Rocket Burgers and Subs? Yep! As many times as possible.   Will I put on at least 10 pounds due to these visits? Yep! Don't judge me...

XiQ9Im4rNoK6yu95yYmIWA.text: I know many people like this place but I am just telling my experience.  I was not impressed at all.  We got the Afterburner burger and cali burger, fries and onion rings.   We were the only people in the place and all our food was luke warm or room temprature.  The patties were very thin and thinking I would get pickled jalapenos on my burger they were actually raw. Every burger place I have been has never had raw jalapenos - maybe I should have asked or maybe they shoul post they are raw.  The onion rings batter was not even batter it tasted more like cornmeal and they were room temperature - should be hot.  The buns were hard and not soft at all.  Our first time is our last time there. Sorry but very poor food quality.

E0chg7U7Jmog3fveUURowA.text: Went here a few weeks  ago actually just moved to the neighborhood kind of looking for a hole in the wall restaurant and we saw this because there is awesome pop shop next-door that carry pops that I believe is also connected to the rocket Burger shop. Was really good the interior was really cool to be that I had a whole bunch of old authentic sign and it looks like it was probably family run probably still is , good food, price was great, they had all sorts of different pops along the back wall very clean so definitely would go back there again.

gZjqxhYQ1nwQqv83Ur83Fg.text: Rocket Burger & Subs is a very casual and divey. You won't get the most high end burger in the valley but you'll get 100% angus flat patties that are prepared to your likening  and are delicious with several choices of sizes and toppings. Besides burgers they offer sandwiches, subs, beef hot dogs, soft serve, floats and the biggest selection of bottled sodas I've ever seen. Portions are very large and prices aren't much more than fast food. You are getting food that's MUCH Better than fast food.  After watching RB&S on Check Please Arizona I went with what everyone else tried the popular NY Double Burger with fries. I liked that they carefully toasted the buns and the burgers were prepared medium just like I asked for and were juicy and tasty. A generous amount of tasty grilled pastrami and house made slaw and rocket sauce topped the burger. It was all good tasty and humungous and a giant amount of fresh cut fried potatoes were yummy too.   Check out Rocket Burger!  It's a Blast!

rLatpF0g7bsP6XzY5otJ0Q.text: This place is great.  You really can't get much better.  They have unbelievable food at great prices. 6IQ9rgU2103KwKWyM8UhbQ.text: I discovered this place via Yelp. Again, my fellow Yelpers weren't wrong! This place was delicious. I had the Cali Burger and rings. uyJ8KVdjsiv2dzSc9vOfuQ.text: This place is bad ass , so many different burgers its radonk! I highly recommend this place

47GyNKbbTOtix2hoW6FrCg.text: I absolutely love this place! The food is excellent, the eddie burger and meatball sub have been my favorites so far. The chilli cheese fries are incredible, and the onion rings are awesome! You can tell a lot of love is put into this food, and if I go out to eat I drive 20 minutes out of my way to go to Rocket Burger. Absolutely love this place, and the soda selection is incredible!

U94WwmriucGRu3DJm-IWPA.text: This review is based on a recent, first time visit to Rocket Burger.  Pros  - Friendly Service - Amazing Cola Selection - Hole in the Wall vibe  Cons - the Rocket Burger  On recommendation from the staff, I ordered their flagship burger the Rocket New York which is three patties on a 12 in sub with pastrami, cheese, and cole slaw. No fries (too much food already) and a root beer. I believe I paid about $14 bucks.  So the burger was huge and I was exited to get into it. However, I was disappointed with the quality of the meats. The pastrami was super salty and chewy, and I had to take it off the sandwitch after two bites. The burger meat was low grade, fatty, thin, and had an awful brown-granular texture too it. Fresh meat should have a reddish glow to it. This tasted it like was frozen, defrosted, cooked, refrozen, and reheated. The slaw was drown in mayo sauce. The bread was the best part. Nice sub roll with just enough crust on it. I eat half and had to stop. Not because I was full, but because I was getting an ulcer. I took the other half to go, and toss it. Felt bad tossing it in the store because the staff was friendly.   I will most likely return because of the service and potiental I saw on the menu. Get a single or double burger, on a roll, simple toppings, and a fancy root beer. Hopefully it will be better and I can update this review to a 5!!!!!

g8qdEXJpLTQbgDd1HmpSqg.text: Great little place with cheap, good food. Ruben sandwich with chili cheese fries - great lunch!

tTB5uv4DxNI0pjlL39SCzQ.text: Was in Phoenix from Toronto for business conference. Drove about 25 minutes to get this burger based on reviews on Yelp. If you are a fan of soda, they have a HUGE selection of about 300 different sodas to choose from. I grabbed a 4-pack of Jones Blue Cream Soda for about $7.50 (!).  NASTY!  The onion rings were coated in a VERY thin layer of disgusting batter. it was of a dark brown colour and not very good at all. Both of my burgers (I love food) had soggy buns and were not very good at all. I don't recommend this place at all. I would rather eat at In & Out.

1OhuZKkeDarJRUbEXCPlYw.text: Editing my review for this place. Originally gave them 4/5 stars after my first visit because you need to buy two of their hotdogs to fill up and now having gone there many times, I feel stupid for ever giving such a place only 4 stars when it clearly deserves 5. The hotdogs, while delicious, are the least interesting thing on the menu (although I recommend this place if you're in the mood for a gourmet hotdog).   Their burgers however, are PHENOMENAL! In n' Out has NOTHING on this place (and I love In n' Out). There are a bunch to choose from, reasonably priced and so full of flavor they can only be described as MIND BLOWING. The fries are the best I've ever had as well, seasoned to perfection and cooked just right, just like their burgers. Definitely the best burger place I've ever been too in my entire life.   Also, they have a gigantic wall full of designer soda's from all around the world, I believe they are only $2 a pop (no pun intended) or $1 upgrade onto a combo meal.  All in all, if you live in Phoenix you are blessed to be able to eat here on a regular basis, if you are passing through or here temporarily it is an experience you'll never forget.

fOeXbrr1DJpw76nJ1SjykQ.text: Holy smokes! This place is FANTASTIC!  I was super starving this afternoon and was craving a good burger. I remember going to this joint about a year ago with some co-workers and decided to head on over again. The place seems to have grown since I was there a year ago. The counter seems to be back more than before but maybe I'm just going crazy.  Anyway, on to the experience! I was quickly helped at the counter by a very nice guy who took my order.  I ended up getting the Eddie Lopez Burger which had a SUPER tasty burger,  pastrami and is topped with lettuce, tomato, onion, pickle, swiss, and rocket dressing!  The only bad part was the part when it was all gone!  I also ordered the Onion Rings. I am not even a fan of onion rings but I had to give them a try since everyone suggested them. Wow! There was a pile of them and they were so good!  Next time I'm getting a double!  Forget going to any of those franchise burger places, hit this place up and be prepared to drool!

-AdYGjzT7POvf6fhLm8WSQ.text: So I arrived at Rocket at noon totally in the mood for a greasy spoon type lunch and this place hit the mark.  I've passed by a number of times with the promise of the Latina Meat Market which never opened or closed before I had the chance to go in. Anyhoo, I ordered a double cheeseburger with fries and a can of Diet Coke.  It took a little bit even though I was one of four patrons in the restaurant, but I'll accept that in that it means they cook your meal to order.  Good thin patty burger and thin natural cut fries, though the bun was a bit large.  I'm not a big exotic soda pop fan, but as previously noted if you are they've got probably 6-8 big coolers worth of everything from cream soda to energy drinks to regional colas. The only issue I had with this place hit about 12:15 when a swarm of teenagers descended upon the restaurant and all of a sudden it's completely packed and noisy as all hell.  Guess the adjacent Moon Valley High isn't a closed campus...

hUGlxzE1QCZR_YvgaWoOSw.text: Groupons are great and lead me to fun new places like this.  Went today for lunch- Teriyaki and Cali burgers, plus fries and one of the many bottled sodas they offer (vanilla creme).  The burgers were slightly smaller than at other burger places I've been to, but still more than enough.  Fries are freshly cut and yummy.  Prices are very reasonable and the owners were nice.

ywvyK6jyYuvxHW7wWpTB3w.text: Have I got a place for you un-health conscious, frugal foodies out there!  Rocket Burger and Subs serves up huge sandwiches and fried delights for astonishingly low prices, and much of the food is home-made. There's also an enormous section of unusual soft drinks; for instance, there's over two dozen brands of root beer to choose from. Dennis, one of the owners worked for A&W for 8 years, so he probably has root beer running through his veins by now.        I saw Rocket Burger in a listing of new valley eateries, then did a little research. The reviews I saw were all stellar, so I knew we had to give it a try. It doesn't look like much, inside or out - it's in a little strip mall tucked behind Churches Chicken at 35th Ave. and Cactus. But it's clean, and everybody is helpful and pleasant. Ken gave a happy whoop when he saw Cheese Curds ($2.49/$4.49) on the menu. We decided to get an order while waiting for our friends Randy and Marty to join us. The curds came quickly out of the kitchen, piping hot, served with some tasty homemade marinara. They were a touch greasy, as they should be, and the oil was fresh. Marty and Randy arrived in time to save us from ourselves by helping to finish off the curds. Then we took a while trying to make our selections from the extensive menu. Eventually Randy and I both went for the New Yorker: pastrami with homemade slaw and thousand island dressing ($2.99, $3.99 or $4.99). Ken had a homemade-meatball  sub, with more of that good marinara and some provolone. It was the same price structure as our New Yorkers and all the rest of the entries under Classic Subs and Sandwiches. Marty went with a double burger ($3.89, the singles are $1 less). He could have opted for a Rocket Burger - !0 inch sub with three burgers and the fixings in either plain, cheese, bacon, teriyaki, or chili style ($4.99 to $5.99). Of course we had to try the fries and onion rings.       Again our food arrived quickly, served in plastic baskets. It became very quiet, except for the occasional growl of pleasure. The onion rings ($1.99) had been dipped in a thin cornmeal batter which made them nice and crunchy.  The handcut fries ($1.49) were skinny, the way I like them. Randy thought they were undersalted, but I thought they were fine - our usual disagreement. At any rate, they disappeared quickly. Unlike the sandwiches. They were so big that we all ended up taking half of each sub home. The slaw on the New Yorkers was delicious, as was my whole wheat sub roll. The meat balls were nice and tender, and there was plenty of cheese on top. Randy had found a bottle of ginger beer imported from Australia that had a wonderfully refreshing True ginger taste. There seemed to be actual pieces of ginger in it - instructions on the label said to invert the bottle before opening. It never did tell you to turn it right side up again - the Aussies give us more credit than we deserve.        Other food items available: Hebrew National hot dogs in several styles ($2.49), Pizza   Bread with various toppings, Gyros ($3.69), salads ($1.99 - $3.99), a fish sandwich ($2.49) served with homemade tartar sauce. And lots more. I don't know how Dennis and Steve manage to turn out food of this quality for so little money, but I surely do hope they continue and prosper!

KGpfX-I0hcDymXb2AHa1jw.text: Amazing!! The New Yorker is addictive as well as the onion rings. The selection of soda is a blast. We'll be back!!

e6rvHQrSvt65dFymfs8Izw.text: This little place showed up on yelp and the wife and I just decided to give it a shot. When we entered we were greeted by two very nice men then I noticed the soda pop. Everything you have ever wanted in a soda pop selection. Everything from real sugar Pepsi to saranac Shirley temple. I decided to have the biggest burger I could and what a choice. I decided the newyork burger was what I craved. Burger on a fresh bun with tons of thin sliced cole slaw and amazing pastrami. The hot dog was the best my wife Ashley has had. Top it all off with chili cheese fries. No bean chili the way I like it. Fresh cut fries and it was cheesy heaven. The best part, 2 full people, 2 great sodas.....$12. Love it.

E5BEV49IRe5VBm2OtrAxaw.text: Wow! This place is awesome. The Mexican hot dog is to die for. They make their own salsa and it tasted like they make their own bread too. The fries were fresh. I didn't notice that they don't normally open until 11 but the guy was super cool and warned me it would take an extra few minutes, but had no problem serving me. It was well worth the wait!

w6gPnZRzuwtFXroZNtbPRA.text: This place is awesome and I haven't even had the chance to go inside. My husband has picked up food and yummy sodas from here twice. C0Rr9FM30qFeoCgqEqdVNg.text: Beverage mecca.   Rocket Burgers is a new addition to the NW side of Phoenix. It is tucked away behind Church's Chicken on the SW corner of 35th Ave and Cactus. I would have never seen it had it not been for Yelp. I'm not sure what was there before it but it is set up like a 7-11. It's nothing fancy but clean. It is decorated in red, white, and blue and has a painting of a rocket shooting over the desert on the far wall. A tribute to the Moon Valley Rockets down the street. There are a few booths and some tables and chairs. There is a convenient store size glass cooler on the largest wall. Inside contains just about any kind of drink you can think of. I'm talking every Gatorade invented and several sizes, bottle waters of every variety, Yoohoo, V8, Jarritos, Jolt, Coke products, Pepsi products, craft brewed root beers of about 20 different varieties, craft brewed ginger ales, crush in every flavor, any kind of juice you can think of, the list goes on. I'm not a big soda drinker and I wanted to try them all. I must have looked at all of them for about 10 minutes before making my decision.   I ordered a chili cheese dog and onion rings. My wife ordered a single cheeseburger with fries. The guys/owners behind the counter are very cool. Anyone who wears a Fitz t-shirt deserves a shot at my business. My wife mentioned I had heard about them on Yelp and the gentleman was very happy to hear it. He smiled and said he had never heard of Yelp until recently and he has got a lot of business from it and its really working out well for them.   So I settled on a Maine Root Beer that was gluten free and caffeine free and delicious. After about 5 minutes or so our order comes out. My wife's burger was very good. It had a huge round top bun and some very fresh veggies on it. The fries were homemade, thin and very fresh. The burger tasted great. It reminded me of Lenny's but with fresher toppings and a much higher quality bun. The chili dog had what appeared to be homemade chili on it. They put cheese slices and mustard on the bun first and then the National Hebrew huge dog and smothered it with chili then put more mustard and onions on the top. Just like I make it at home and it was very tasty. The bun was sesame seeded and toasted. The onion rings were battered lightly with corn meal. They were good and different. I'm really not a big fan of onion rings so I wasn't in love with them but that's not saying they weren't good. The amount of food was very generous. It was hard to finish it and I ended up giving up rather than over filling myself.   I really enjoyed the beverage options these guys are serving up. The food wasn't out of this world but they did go the extra mile in everything they served. I appreciated that very much.  Another value was our huge meals with cool drinks came out to 12 bucks before a tip.  Plus they seem like they are a couple of great guys who started a business and who doesn't like to support that? We will definitely be going back to try out the subs and some other gourmet sodas.

RQHB1BIpUKVyvgkvsoVgfg.text: 2 weeks ago my bf and I were discussing Sonic and their slushies. That prompted a conversation about  "Slush Puppie" drinks that I grew up with back in Tennessee. I loved the lemon/lime ones that they used to sell at the local corner store. That prompted me to Google to see if anyone sold them now and in Phoenix. To my surprise Rocket Burger popped up! We decided to check them out as they also have over 300 sodas for sale some that are hard to find. I let out a child like squeal when we walked it. There it was, glowing like an angel!! SLUSH PUPPIES!!!!! I purchased the biggest size they had and it was as good as I remember as a child. The owner, Steve was very nice and we chatted him and his counter guys up for a bit. We took a look at their menu. WOW is all I can say. So many options. We went for the Double Bacon Cheese burger, fried mushrooms (with cornmeal). Absolutely delicious. The burger was tasty, flavorful and the bun toasted to perfection. The mushrooms were divine! Best outside of Bun Huggers up in Flagstaff. I would highly recommend this place. If you love vintage soda pop, a great burger and Slush Puppies check them out. We ended up ordering them for takeout last Friday night. My bf had the gyro burger and we ordered the french fries. I had the BCB again. Once again a great meal!! Will be returning over, and over again..

8ysGfhZtYFWkK-PoVAl7tA.text: I was running some errands and figured it was time to go check out Rocket Burger's and subs. I've heard some pretty good things about this place so I stopped in and checked it out.  The place is located in a strip mall and actually kinda cool.  It's got a huge selection of pop along the wall, and has a great menu of items to choose from.  Prices are fair, and over all, it was a great experience.  I went with the Gyro burger with a pop, and it was out to my table in no time. Hot and tasty, and it hit the spot.  The burger itself was actually quite big, and stacked real high.  Pretty cool!  There's a reasonable amount of seating, with booths and tables like.    One thing I noticed is that they only have one unisex bathroom. I guess I'm used to a Men's and a woman's, but that's okay.  The parking lot was also overrun with teenagers for some reason, so I'm not sure what that's about.  There must be a high school near by, but they were just all hanging around, and some of them were in the restaurant as well. I guess it must be a fun place for them to hang out at!  Either way, if your on this side of town, and want something different and cool, go check this place out.  They seem to have something on the menu for everyone.

l5FFgruhS71SHXh6bzdE5g.text: After going to SmashBurger and not getting my burger smashed, I was not surprised when the burgers here were not actually made out of rockets. Interstellar is one of my favorite movies of all time and I wanted to feel like Matthew McConaughey blasting off into space as I ate. Unfortunately, my burger made me feel more like Anne Hathaway, which is weird because I've never been in love with Captain Edmunds, although I do agree that his planet shows the most promise. Still it was a pretty decent burger.  The atmosphere makes me feel like I'd traveled back in time about 50 years. This is, of course, possible with the help of some 4th dimensional beings, AKA ourselves in the future. If I could travel back in time to the day I ate at Rocket Burger, I would order another burger.

UDUcrnamCosdA-N06KTluA.text: I stopped in for lunch, based on the reviews I was SO stoked for this burger and "best onion rings" and was disappointed. The burger was OK, like a whopper is ok. And the onion rings were some of the least flavorful I've tasted. I will not be returning for $12 burger, onion rings and drink meal. The soda selection is impressive but that's about it. Too bad I don't drink soda.  The girl at the counter was very pleasant though.  I ordered the afterburner burger, and ate half of it; the sauce was very spicy and that was the highlight of the burger. Eh.

Yy5OHLHpHS3GUzFzZbiIAw.text: I love this place. I am trying to not write this review with my emotions, but to hell with it; Best Burger in Phoenix! I have sampled an array of the offerings and I proclaim them all to be of better than decent quality, some are in fact astoundingly crafted to be in a high range of quality. My primary example of this is the New York Burger, which is a layer of pastrami a layer of cole slaw and a slice of really delicious cheese on the already amazing all-beef burger. The bread is also noticeably awesome here, the sub rolls are soft yet sturdy for stacking meats onto and the burger buns are to die for. If I let this review go by without mentioning the fried zucchini it would be a crime against having good taste in the realm of food. The zuke is breaded and tastes very fresh, it is expertly packaged so as to not get mushy and the presentation is very appetizing to the eyes.  I need at least one of these burgers a month in order so that I do not devolve into madness.  I work in food prep and I can say that I recognize all the details they put into their food at Rocket Burger. I will leave the surprising selection of soda and bottled beverages for you to experience on your own as it adds to the charm of the establishment.  A high five to the crew and owners for getting it right.

-yDlgd_pkFS_t0eWec_I5A.text: A friend recommended this place while we were in town for a baseball tournament last week and goodness we are so grateful! The best burgers, good fries, beyond delicious  chicken tenders and a housemade rocket sauce that you will want to drink!! Also a plethora of sodas from around the world!! The fountain ginger beer was my fave!! Will definitely return everytime we are in town!!

Odt7vQ09vbQvbt7w5Q9SgQ.text: First time visit, found using Yelp.  Decor is a little funky with colorful rockets painted on the walls.  First thing you notice is a set of large coolers with every brand of soft drink bottles and cans.  I had no idea there were so many different varieties and brands on the market.  Staff was very friendly and offered several suggestion as they have a large number of burgers with all sorts of choices available as single  and multiple patties.  My wife selected the California Burger with Avacado, Bacon, Swiss Cheese, Lettuce, Tomato and Onion Rings.  They offer their "Rocket Sauce" which is based on a variant of Thousand Island.  She had an order of Onion Rings.  I had a Teriyaki Burger which came with Cheese, Pineapple, Lettuce, Tomato, Mayo and a homemade  Teriyaki Sauce.  I had French Fries.  The Burgers were fabulous!  They have a special Bun, a giant step up from the more conventional mass produced bun.  The beef was not overcooked and was delicious. The bun was more dome shaped than flat and a challenge to open wide enough to get the burger in your mouth gracefully.  Generous slice of Pineapple and Tomato.  The Onion rings were some of the best we have ever had.  The coating was thinner than what you normally get but fabulous in taste.  The portion was very generous and came with a couple small containers of Ranch Dressing.  Unfortunately the French Fries were a disappointment.  Generous portion but rather small cut, texture was overly soft and color dark brown indicating a non premium type of potato.  Too little starch and to much sugar causing the overly dark color and somewhat oily taste.  Would have rated the meal as five stars but poor fries dropped them a full star.  Will definitely return and perhaps talk to the staff about selecting a better potato or more optimum cooking method.

KwufUM4slbelY56MHDA27g.text: Delicious chili burger, I was impressed by the soft bun and the tender burger. Over all a great experience, they were fast at getting the food out to us and the experience of looking at all the sodas they have out was a great part of the lunch we had there. Very family friendly

3DKgMhU2sWVt8rgXBLUfuQ.text: I love the selection of drinks and how laid back it is! The only complaint I have is that the fries could be a lot better but hey, pretty good joint overall.

EQdGoeEsT9kqeRNKxzv4Eg.text: Only disappointment leaving rocket burger is that we dont have room for more! Had the New York burger..again..and it was amazing as usual. Wife had the kraut dog and said it was the best sauerkraut she's had. Baby had a side of avocado that she chowed. Fried mushrooms were on point, and of course the awesome assortment of pop makes this Michigan family happy.

qs_54s8J-DwAOwTAggpwig.text: My reasoning for checking out Rocket Burger is kind of weird but I'm glad it got me through the door.  One of my friends from Ohio always talks about Faygo soda and when I saw that in one of the pictures for Rocket Burger I knew I had to go for that and then after seeing all the great reviews I was excited about the food too.  Had a little trouble trying to find it at first so for everyone trying to find it for the first time, it's on the South West corner of Cactus and 35th Ave.  You probably won't see it from the street but there's a Church's Chicken right in front of it so just pull into that parking lot and Rocket Burger is right behind it.  I got the Single Bacon Cheeseburger with fries and a Faygo soda (of course!).  The guy at the counter was nice and polite but not overly friendly.  The food came out very quickly, probably under 5 minutes and it was nice and hot.  The burger was good, they really stack it with the toppings too and you can tell they're quality.  No soggy veggies and limp bacon here.  I loved the fries too!  They're shoestring and they're coated with some kind of seasoning salt that gives them a great flavor.  So glad that my quest for soda helped me discover a great burger place too!

ESDPo9WpUrQ3A8r1mBYy2w.text: Meh. I've had better burgers at the local Denny's. The fries were either old or refried. The chilli on my chilli-cheese-fries tasted like cheap canned chilli. Won't go back... Nothing there I can't get cheaper and better at other places.

M75NhKuNqsOT9TZH774lsw.text: Absolutely love Rocket Burger! Dont forget to add a scoop of ice cream to make anyone of those amazing sodas a FLOAT! There chicken tender bites are to die for.

eTSrjPifzoBGowWhVG6fQg.text: I can not believe that I have not reviewed this place yet with as much as I go there!   I have been  going to Rocket Burger for a couple of years now and on a regular basis... maybe 2-3 times per month. I have NEVER been disappointed.   I get the Cali Burger which has bacon (which is always crispy) and avocado (which is always perfectly ripe).  It also has rocket sauce  on it which is like no other "secret" sauce I have had before. You just have to try it.  The amazing bun that the hamburger comes with is more like a crusty roll type bread rather than the standard seeded bun.   The fries are good, but overshadowed by how amazing their burgers are.   The soda selection is like nothing I have ever seen before. Hundreds of choices. Bottled sodas from across the nation and soda I have not seen in years!   Oh and the service - they are great! They actually thank you for coming in and say by when you leave. They know who I am (as they should since I go there so often), but they really give it a personal touch!   This is my#1 burger joint - hands down! So glad I work so close to this place!  You would be a fool not to give this place a try!

_bSBHh0B0owrJRjJocLWVA.text: Outstanding! Gets a bump for being a friendly, family owned establishment on the Northwest side. Will be back.   1) Afterburner fried chicken sandwich- Considering I don't eat beef or pork, I've had my fair share of fried chicken sandwiches. I would have to put this is the top 5 I've ever had- the breading was perfect, the veggies were fresh, but the rocket relish makes the sandwich unique and memorable. A legitimate "spicy" chicken sandwich.    2) New York Burger- my wife decided to go for an extra meaty option, and she loved it. It comes with a burger patty, pastrami, and her husbands bacon from the chicken sandwich. Also cole slaw. She also said the fries were well seasoned.   3) SO MANY SODAS- I'm not a huge soda drinker, but the sheer volume and variety is pretty amazing. Chocolate, bacon, and more root beer flavors than you can imagine are all options.
