YRXHMnEeNEyQafCTRnFxxQ.text: Had a burger here a few months ago and it was really good. I love the selection of sodas as well.

kJyibU-4tTTMwAgFRNI-qw.text: Nothing Fancy but Oh So Good.  You couldn't tell by looking at the outside.  However, as the old adage goes " You can't judge a book by its cover."  The same can be said about Rocket Burgers and Subs. Nothing fancy here but the food is oh so good.  The food at Rocket Burgers and Subs   doesn't cost much more than the average fast food establishments around town.  However, you would be challenged to find a burger that compares to the quality and taste of the food  served at Rocket Burgers and Subs.  Rocket Burgers and Subs serves up various styles of burgers, beef hot dogs, sandwiches, and of course subs.  On this visit I went with the Lunch Special ($4.99).  The lunch special consisted of a burger, fresh cut fries, and a soft drink.  The lunch special was a great price and the food was delicious.  The hamburger roll was perfectly grilled, hamburger  grilled to medium, and the fries which were made from fresh cut potatoes with skins  were seasoned perfectly and so tasty.  In addition to great food, Rocket Burgers has the largest selection of bottled sodas I have ever seen. Every soda combination you can imagine and even those you can't is served at Rocket Burger.  The  dining is casual. You order at the counter and seat yourself. The prices are more then reasonable, staff is friendly, portion sizes are large, and the food is delicious.  What more could you ask for.

SikC0ZgDPe0NinNlhT1GQA.text: I was looking for an alternative to 5 guys.  I'll stick with 5 guys.  They have better tasting burgers and are about the same price.

COpdhFpY1nRapLwZTy0Rvg.text: Firstly...really friendly staff.  The guy at the counter was patient and helpful.  We ordered easily, and the food came out quickly.  Secondly...both our burgers (I got a regular hamburger and hubby got the Santa Fe burger) were drenched in their "Rocket Sauce".  My burger was literally falling apart, and I couldn't even taste if I had a patty in there, or not.  It was dripping so much in my basket, I wouldn't have been able to put it down, to taste anything else.  The sauce has a very pickley flavor to it, which neither of us are fans of--we always ask for no pickles on any sandwich.  Hubby couldn't taste his green chile, which is the main reason he got that burger.  Thirdly...I got the fries as a side, and they were the best part of our meal.  Hubby ended up sharing them with me, which I didn't mind, since they do give you a lot.  They're thinly cut and somewhat crispy, but they were all gone at the end of our meal.  As a side, hubby got the fried zucchini.  They were okay, and you could tell they were made there and not frozen.  The only problem was, they were cut way too thick, and the breading was falling off.  We didn't even finish them.  Lastly...the walls of sodas was really impressive.  Hubby got an orange soda by Faygo (we'd seen someone mention it on "Check Please, Arizona!").  He downed it quickly.  I'm not a soda-drinker, so I got a bottled water...sorry, not too exciting.  But, it was fun to look at the different brands they had.  Chances are, we won't be going back...we were a little disappointed.

The avocado addled freshness to my burger. The thin fries were nicely seasoned. Tip: Yelp check-in is 10 percent off your whole order.

cqjaZHMMl1T5SUi3sFgf1w.text: First time here and it was very tasty. The service was fast. There is no exaggeration on the soda options. There must be over 100 different craft options. Very unique flavors such as pumpkin apple and snoozberry. Burgers were great and the fries are fresh.

fzo-jM704kIjWcxRAx3-Jw.text: Looking for a great burger joint with never ending variety of sodas?  Then you found your place.  Rocket Burger is another one of those diamonds in the rough.  A classic no frills burger place with plenty of flavor and a vast selection of sodas to wash it down.        For my visit I had the Eddie Lopez burger which is your standard burger topped with pastrami and some of their rocket sauce.  The pastrami was excellent with just the right amount of caramelizing and not too crazy with the sauce.  The burger was well seasoned and bursting with juicy flavor.  You gotta love when a place seasons their burgers correctly.  The included fries were also seasoned quite heavy, but I feel this is a classic burger place style, especially when you're piling them down with plenty of ketchup.        You can't have a proper greasy spoon burger with out a good soda to wash it down.  Luckily Rocket Burger offers over 1,000 sodas, juices, and teas.  They have everything from obscure energy drinks to classic Mexican Cokes, it would take years to taste every soda in this place.  Even if you're not a burger fan you can easily find something you like in the cooler.      Overall Rocket Burger was fantastic, and I will be going back to enjoy another delicious meal.

ZnGfzNED34yXiRoZyMl6hw.text: We're back! Love this place! Try the Santa Fe burger. Hubby loves the Philly cheese steak. Lots and lots of sodas to choose from. Fried zucchini is yummy too!

KQhdaFBdxzSOZEtd2eVinA.text: Ok.. Yummmmmmmmmmm   Positives: Best cheese curds ever. Amazing seasoning on their fries and the California burger was bomb. Not our usual area of town but hubby wanted to check it out and I am so glad we did!  Anyone looking for a phenomenal burger you must give it a try.   Negatives: The location isn't great for me.   I will be going back!

UeM_qG3NJ1V2oBdB3BSQbg.text: An old classmate of mine, that comes here regularly, highly recommended this place.  It definitely doesn't disappoint.  I didn't try the burgers but the fish sandwich I ordered was great.  It was dressed with a pico de gallo slaw.  You won't go away hungry with this dish or any dish probably.  And, they have a throw back to classic sodas...that was cool.  It appears that they own/operate the Pop shop next door too; which houses even more soda...nice overall throw back feel.  The place has about 8-10 tables, so it can easily seat about 40 people.  I believe it's a family run place and they are all friendly.  I can parking will be an issue if the have a full house, just plan to going during less busy times and/or order to go. I will definitely be back whether dine in or take out... ;p

KREMKwrGZ15YN_v30Z8fKg.text: I was in the area and starving.  Read the reviews and this place was spot on.  It's got that soda shop feel with classic big burgers.   I went with the bacon one and it did not disappoint.  It's off the roadway but worth the stop.  Friendly staff!

8eqc5jDOgS54wYnyl4WYKw.text: Rocket Burger's restaurant setup is far from trendy, especially in comparison to all of the other burger places that keep popping up all over the city. But don't let this fool you. Rocket Burger offers an above average burger, including some unique creations that might be somewhat intimidating to try at first.    Everything I've tried has been good, but not quite as alarmingly great as some people describe. Additionally, both their regular seasoned and cheese fries are also worth trying when paying a visit.  The cool thing about Rocket Burger is their massive variety of sodas! They carry many of my favorite brands, including Boylan and Jones, as well as many obscure flavors that you probably won't find anywhere else in Phoenix.  Very cool place that I recommend trying!

50QRGCLW2ECzCXhuzKN5vg.text: I wish I could give this place more stars. But a place with the word "Burgers" in it led me to setting high expectations for the burger I ordered. I'll give it another chance someday because of high rating.

FzzLZ09dGxAydA6-3wZezg.text: Our burger was juicy and perfectly cooked to order and the fried green chili was different,  but really good.

LMLNtSiotF2LdSsfPFwKTg.text: This place is a neat find! More then the usual burger shop, but hidden is a strip center. Not an impressive atmosphere but don't let that turn you away. The dining  area is surrounded by coolers full of unusual bottled beverages. Besides the bottled variety there is also a fountain full of other choices that that will please anyone that are included in your typical combo meal. I had one of the specials on the chalk board and I have to say it was one of the best burgers I have had in a while, pepper jack cheese and spicy mayo just made my mouth the happiest it's been for a while. There is plenty to look at while waiting for your burger to be served to you at your table. During your wait you can check out the beverage selection, and I will just say I have never seen such a great selection! Check this place out!

yUschkuncpBjHds0yS0JGA.text: huge selection of burgers. The wait was a bit long but was def worth it. All in all its a must try and a nice little experience.

The fish sandwich is good but messy to eat by hand.  I don't drink soda, but if I did this place would be like heaven: a monterous  selection of carbonated beverages lines the back wall.

tldlil5LtgjeY8IP7XoCdw.text: Found this hidden gem and we absolutely love eating here! They have so many menu options as well as drinking options! It's a nice cozy restaurant with very friendly staff and the dining area is very clean! Highly recommend checking them out.

ornedbHhY5iWlnI-5zlicg.text: Everyone who is a foodie knows that the best places to eat are A) Not a chain and B) Are located in "a hole in the wall." Being wheat intolerant, I can't give any place 5 stars that doesn't have a gluten-free bun option. That said, EVERYTHING else was very good.  Food is flavorful through and through. I ended up risking on a Rueben. I figure if I have an allergic reaction I'm going to make it worth it. And it was 100% worth it. I scarfed all of it down! No looking back  Drinks are FABULOUS! I have seen soooo many varieties of soda! I had a ginger beer from a "microbrew" in New Hampshire. Its recipe boasts of being 152 years old.  If you are near 35th Ave and Cactus stop by here!

KAxfVaiVEEPaR0sTT1i50A.text: These guys know how to fry!  I had fried zucchini with a good cheeseburger. Terry had the fried chicken sandwich   The best he has ever had!  They have a huge wall of sodas!

6qjVOwc2US8vOsC0-1JZnw.text: This was my surprise birthday lunch, and I could not have been more pleased. The burgers were excellent, but of course if you want to visit the first and last word on soda pop variety, this is it. Cases from wall to wall greet your eye. For any given flavor, you will see maybe twenty or thirty different varieties from all over this great land of ours. The staff was very friendly and helpful, and the service overall was excellent as well. Steve, busy as he was, came out personally to act as soda sommelier, guiding me to some of his favorites. The blueberry soda from Maine was amazing, as was Gales Root beer and a cream soda called something like Sprechers form Wisconsin where the honey used came through nicely. The Manhattan Orange was good as well, although not quite in the same league. With lunch, my wife had a Boyland's grape which, like almost all Boyland sodas, is first rate. Highly recommended for food, drink, and just the overall experience. We heard about this place on Check Please and are so glad we did. Next time I will try the kosher dogs which look tempting..and maybe pick up a few special bottles...

ZExjT4a9e5PSXcS-m_CReQ.text: Low prices and great food. Fast service.... definitely one of my favorite places! AMAZING selection of indie sodas!

IKpNq75XQ3HR4pu-0oMy4Q.text: i dream about this place...in fact my stomach is growling just thinking about it. been here a few times, always down to try something new each time. however, my heart belongs to the eddie lopez burger. i've yet to get down on the cheese curds, the fries are tasty as well as the onion rings. the kids and i spend at least a good 15 minutes perusing the soda selection. this place makes me happy, so very very happy. i just wish i didn't live so bloody far...

Lwp0l-iIhPfBSdr30YCJxQ.text: Oh my goodness, this place is the best especially all of the sodas they have. Every flavor, the burgers and fries are great with the special sauce. I would love to go back in the near future.

Gd4W98HZS-k8jH25VBWEMg.text: Disappointing. Had a so-called Philly cheese steak. I think it's the first one that's ever been made. Had to explain how to make it. Tasted strange. I believe I asked for onions and green peppers and I'll be darn if I could find them. The mustard had a strange taste to it also. The place was also unbearably hot inside. I guess they're saving on air-conditioning. Don't plan on going back.

NtufKBpf5vAWsG1WYSphdQ.text: Try the New Yorker just the way they recommend it and you won't be disappointed.  It may be the best New Yorker, I've had.  Also, try the brownie with homemade whip cream, hot out of the oven, mmmm so delicious.  My girlfriend loved the veggie sub, and while she normally stays away from shoestring fries, these shoestrings were mouth popping.  Also, there were sooo many different novelty sodas in the bottle to choose from, I can see the quest beginning here to try, but not succeed at tasting them all.  The food was great, but what really put this place over the top for us, was the friendly service.  You could tell they really wanted our business.

lMkyG93AJmdna6rYo8GgXg.text: This place pretty much rocks! Our friends introduced us to the place last night. Our experience was so exciting that we went again today for lunch. The first meal was a philly burger, amazing, and a gyro burger, an another amazing! Both burgers were spot on with big flavor! The burgers are great, but the other thing that made the place pop for me was the selection of artisan sodas. The place has a giant selection of sodas that are so rare to find. I'm from Maine and they had Moxie. I can't get Moxie soda anywhere here in the valley, that is except at Rocket Burger! This review isn't for the soda Moxie, it is definitely an acquired taste. Rocket Burger on the other hand is not a place that has to grow on you. You'll fall in love with it right away.

B6xai8dECDuT3UkwRSPLDA.text: I never do reviews, but I had to after going to Rocket Burger heaven!  This is my new guilty pleasure.  The burgers are juicy, big and satisfying, their subs are tasty and inventive, and their onion rings are awesome, crunchy greatness.  Their fries are perfectly crisp, and their fried mushrooms are crunchy, fresh and wonderful.

AJFWxHg0TrM_CkXDJ2VMJA.text: Was looking for a good hamburger so reviewed Yelp and saw Rocket Burger. Went in on Saturday and I see why they get the great reviews. Great fresh burger and good bun. Service was great as I was asked twice by whom I assume was owner or manager how food was and if I needed anything else. My wife and I loved this place and will be back next weekend.

w17LUX7zoLIuwY1kq_izRA.text: This place is amazing.  The food is far and above any fast-food place you could go to.  Heck, you would probably pay less here and get superior food.  An Slush Puppie machine!? Crazy big bottled soda selection?! This place is a hidden jem that all should go to!

9OxZf1lhHIw1RUIPjy_lxQ.text: So glad I found this place on Yelp. I've passed it for years unaware it was there. Had Chicago burger, it was amazing!  Cheese curds were great! Yes, salty.. but that is how they should be. I'll absolutely be back!

U4eelPQb65y3wGGk5mRzvw.text: My girlfriend and I went for the first time this month, we will be back again and again.  I had the Rocket burger and she had the Reuben sandwhich, we shared an order of fries.  The best burger and fries I have ever had.

7f8eBcXCenqB3hAUZ9CNVg.text: This place is tucked away in my old stomping grounds. As a former "Rocket" I had to see what they hype was about. Took a drive into my ol' hood. And was shocked how the neighborhood had changed so much in 30 years! Rocket Burger is tucked behind Church's Chicken. It did not disappoint! I have been there twice now. I have tried the rueben sandwhich, California club, California burger, the NYer fries and onion rings. All of it was great and affordable. The subs are packed with meat and the sandwiches are big enough for two people to split. My least favorite was the burger. But for subs I would go back. The onion rings were crunchy, with a light coat of batter, and thinner which I like. The fries were just ok. But then, fries are not my thing. My kids liked that they could pick out any type of soda. I picked one that tasted like a mojito. My daughter had a pear soda, and my youngest had a delicious rootbeer that had butterscotch in it. The coleslaw on the NYer was great! It was fresh and crunchy! In fact all the vegetables were fresh! Even the avocado, it wasnt just a little bit that came on the burger, but it was enough to cover the entire bottom bun. The tomato was wasnt chintzy either, Yay! Great family business that I would support any day over the big guys. This place rocks. And all of us can find something to eat here. Score!

okv6nakqPQqNRDRFkpQwBw.text: Simply put, one of the best burger shops in the city.  The meat is fresh, albeit a tad greasy, the cheese and bacon rock, and their crazy twist on 1000 island is awesome!  Only detractor is the grease as it destroys the bread.  But the main event?  The cooler packed with the 350 best soft drinks you never new existed!  Sprecher rootbeer at 1.89 a bottle all day!

9hI9TCRAjhnwpRB2WegrCA.text: Super cheap, super tasty.  Like everyone says they've got a crazy amount of sodas (try Gale's rootbeer) and a Slushpuppy machine.  Everything I've tried has been good and they're quick.

bK7hetsaSrdJBqBJS3t8YQ.text: We LOVE this place!! Excellent food at reasonable prices!!! It is clean and the service is outstanding. Worth a drive from anywhere in the valley. Goodbye Churches and hello Rocket Burger & Subs!!! May your stay be a long one!!!!!

eVa1o0LG82fRFEMWON1C3w.text: this place is right around the corner from my house. the guys who run it are nice guys. the food is great and the bread is local. i'm glad to see everyone else likes this place as much as i do. let's hope they stick around.

bwQdsOamzq9eZt0UsQyDzA.text: This place is amazing! Don't let this rough looking little shopping plaza scare you off because inside the shop is some of the tastiest food in this part of town.  The Chili Cheese Fries are a must!  The "Rocket Burger" is a steal, imagine 3 burger patties with cheese and all the fixin's on a sub roll for 6 bucks (makes the $6 burger at Carl's Jr. look like child's play).  If you want something spicy ask for the "Thunder Bird", a buffalo chicken sub with bacon, ranch or blue cheese, and the optional fresh jalapenos. And if all of that is not enough to make you want to go these guys stock an insane amount of rare sodas that you will not find just any where. I think they had about 12 kinds of root beer! This is defiantly not fine dining so please excuse the rough decor, this is straight up man fuel.

vp5_wnen6PhM7jrbHoSX9A.text: I have dined twice for their sandwiches, and they are average at best. Haven't sampled their hot dogs or hamburgers yet, maybe that is their strong point. However, they have a HUGE selection of bottled pop.  And they have FAYGO, in glass bottles made with cane sugar.  Excellent!  If you haven't had faygo go and try a bottle.

urO9PJjvYJrEk7Yw-wUDXQ.text: Went here with my husband after craving a good burger and reading good reviews on yelp. We will certainly return! I ordered a cheeseburger which was prepared to order. The beef is never frozen, fresh angus beef. Cheeseburger is made with American cheese. I would have preferred cheddar which wasn't an option. Hubby got the Philly burger- an amazing burger to see piled high with meat and all the cheese steak fixings. I've read poor reviews about the fries- don't pass them up! Fries were perfectly cooked- crispy but not burnt with some softness in the middle. Seasoned to perfection. The owner took our order, he was very friendly and helpful. We bought 6 sodas (drank 1 each, took the rest home) out of amazement. The selection is like nothing I've ever seen. I think this place should be featured on a show like diners, drive ins and dives. The wall of sodas bottles for sale is enough to make a trip for, and the burgers are very tasty.  The sodas come from from every state, maker, flavor, etc you could ever imagine. Lots of nostalgic flavors and memories await you here. This would be a really fun place to go for fathers day or a birthday- a man cave for sure. Parking isn't great- its a hole in a wall place in a strip mall. Nothing fancy- just tasty, laid back. The perfect dive and tons of fun!!

zTb-pSy2TYul7zoZExgYBw.text: rocket burger is by far THE BEST.BURGER.PLACE.EVER!!!! I found it's also the best valley... when i eat here i feel i get way more than what i pay for!! we eat there on a regular basis and have never been disappointed even a little bit!!! when i move next month this is the only place i will miss in arizona!! and every visit back home we will come and eat here!!! oh and do you like soda? any kind that you can imagine they have it in cool glass bottles! Oh and slush puppies too! This place is great just come try it for yourself you'll know what I mean!!

p8ev65F7sZnNJDOOOJm2cQ.text: We were in Phoenix for one day while on a big road trip. Being from out of town, we got lost trying to get there, but it was totally worth it.   The soda selection alone was worth the trip, but the sandwiches were really top-notch too. The fries were thin-cut and really tasted like potato. They were fried fairly dark, and some of them were limp by the time we got them back to the hotel, but I've never had fries that stayed crispy after being transported in Styrofoam, so it's hard to say what they would have been like fresh from the fryer. I thought they were delicious.    The Teriyaki burger featured Teriyaki sauce that was flavorful (not super salty) and, most importantly, DEEP FRIED PINEAPPLE RINGS. I ordered the Italian sub and sort of regretted not getting something more unique, but the sandwich was probably the best I've had since moving away from the Philadelphia area. The lunchmeat seemed high quality and the bread tasted fresh.  We ate at a lot of great places during our road trip and this was definitely a highlight.

pxLprj5YuIX3-oxOu0LDIA.text: This place has an Amazing soda selection.  I had the gyro burger it was great. We also ordered the Garlic Melt burger which was good as well. We will come back.

B7aL7RVwh_BR38mmKInQPg.text: Amazing burgers, good fries, so many soda they even have mini corn dogs  a huge menu.  can always find something to eat.

smAZifXAPvIBRWMlwgeLMQ.text: This place is very expletive good. It isn't a place that's high end where their cows get back massages and pedicures before getting slaughtered and cooked in some fancy french culinary term, it's better. Just when I thought their burgers were the best, I tried my wife's teriyaki chicken sandwhich after I swallowed my burger and it was heavenly. We don't drink soda either but we always split one, vanilla cream is the best. I would eat here all day everyday, unfortunately my pants are already getting tighter lol. It's a solid 10. Go have some please. Guy fierri needs to go there ASAP.

n6MS30B9JkRNtbA2pu4xyA.text: Never Ending   This describes the choices of food and drink here.   On today's menu was a small toasted California Club and a Black Cherry sodee-pop.   Don't let the sound of small fool you either, it is huge! Crammed packed with turkey, bacon, tomato and sprouts. This is a sub to try!  The staff including the owners are amazing. They have such a great selection of food and drink you can take your picky eating kid or a cranky grandad, both will find something to enjoy.

OkNBFGVmks4JKfElyFdugA.text: This place is Legit! Had such a good meal and the soda selection really is awesome! A whole wall dedicated to different sodas in glass bottles! My Gorlfriend had pumpkin pie soda and I had butterscotch root beer and it was delicious!!   Definitely a win for local restaurants!

UzRWrt3b5eUzbPU2H8zd2g.text: Went to Rocket Burger tonight and Jesse ( not sure if that's his correct spelling) but the last few times we were in he waited in us and he's always very friendly and really knows the menu well! Great place, great food, you never have to wait long for your food to arrive! The only thing is the hamburger buns do tend to fall apart while your eating, but otherwise you won't be disappointed stopping in here to eat!

5rXdlGvgyumFLJ9-FZwIig.text: A large menu offering many different flavors that will impress you in comparison to even Red Robin. The venue is nothing to brag about so it's hard to bring guests from out of town here. The bottled soda selection will spin your head trying to select so hopefully you have an idea before going in.

NhoCcgha1TQAaIYHkMp2Rg.text: I have never been disappointed here. Amazing food, tons of cool sodas to choose from if you want to pick some up on the way out. Every time I have been there the owner has too, he is in the back cooking and is a really great guy.

W0j3gE_7XPTSysL2n49UVg.text: Found this place on Yelp today.  Can't believe I've never heard of it!    Crazy selection of sodas, (picture Rocket Fizz + some).  Old school burgers and sandwiches abound here.  My friend ordered the Cali Burger and loved it.  I ordered the Afterburner Chicken sandwich and loved it, except the bun fell appart and was a little big for the sandwich.  The fries were really good, but the onion rings were exceptional.  I am very picky about onion rings and usually stay from them.  These only have a thin batter coating, and it's very flavorful.    I'll go back to try several of the other menu items, and the onion rings again!

ucnMXk8cCFpgj5UVvHA4AQ.text: What can't I say about this place? Extremely friendly staff, amazing selection of sodas both on tap and in bottles, and the burgers are something special too! I love burgers but my taste for them has evolved into something more defined as I've gotten older. Rocket Burger has an impressive menu with varying tastes where anyone can find something that suits them. I tried the New York and the Garlic burger. Wow. Those were extremely different and delicious! Made fresh to order and quicker than I thought it should take. The only drawback? It's in Phoenix and I live in Mesa... My poor gas tank. Can't wait to come back!

nPm3Tzk1tz4QwlJyvG5LZg.text: Amazing one if the best burger spots in Phoenix, I eat here every time I think I deserve a treat.. Never tried the sodas but the food is always great

W4AQzKsj8ldRIFJfeW1DyA.text: One of my favorite burger joints. They have such a fun selection of soda in all flavors. And lots of different types of burgers. Their rocket sauce is very good.

LLV6-vax6l7zV1r8pkGhNQ.text: The wall of soda is damn impressive. and so are the burgers, but they are only 1/3 pound each. Still. obviously you can get a double, but actually the smaller weight almost guarantees that they make the burger well done. The bun was nice and squishy and fresh toppings were included along with the secret thousand island sauce which turned out to add a good flavor to the food. Of course, the highlight is the soda factory and if you get the combo, make sure to add 2 more bucks to have it include one of the beverages in the case. I ended up going radical with the pumpkin pie soda and yes it did taste like a lighter version of the pie and it was all natural as well. Fries were pretty addicting too.

Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Single cheese

LoGiMcy0ZOq05Y5rniUyoQ.text: All I know is. The Hubs and I were hungry so I yelped a burger joint in PHX. I was all Bae this place has 254 reviews .. Let's go there ! We were in PHX from Prescott for the day. Got the Teriyaki Burger Rocket size and fries ! delishioursh ! Hit The Spot ! The owner even chased us to the parking lot to make sure we enjoyed our Food  Yay!!!!!

photos.caption: Photo of Rocket Burger & Subs - Phoenix, AZ, United States. Teriyaki Burger Rocket Size Split &amp; Fries with a couple of Root Beers ! Yum !

vcME-zSXYC50p7wZlBAxJw.text: Always a fun time here! Food is great and cheap definitely come here if you live close and if you don't then make the drive!

yQUkCdIA7Dtnquz0vOt8pg.text: I love local shops but this food is sub par to say the least. Im all about greasy hole in the wall, but that does not mean quality has to be terrible, and that is what this place is. I give it two stars for the excellent selection of drinks!

ZokgNlZfshnG0pFz5pGI5A.text: Love this place!  I often bring my guests from out of town and never fails... Everyone loves the food and atmosphere!  My guests often just want to come back for the wide variety od drinks!

wObi_mKxuLONsCz8uzG-cA.text: This place offers so many options!  Walk in see a lot of sodas and interesting drinks to find in one place. The food is yummy.  Owner is nice.

K9JJOIuE4-LSBahIkdn3gA.text: Ok...I was so excited to eat here, from out of town and was sold by all the great posts and photos!! But it was one of the worst meals of my life. We enjoyed the sodas and bought 6. We ordered: New York burger, Mexican burger, Chicago dog, chili cheese dog, fried mushrooms. The hot dog buns were very hard, both me and my brother got a couple bits into our burgers and were almost completely turned off and couldn't eat another bit. The hot dogs were barely enjoyable as well... maybe the burger was so bad it made everything taste bad. Mushrooms were ok. We did take our food togo, but I wouldn't expect it to ruin the food this much. Very disappointed

1-S4MA6GaaI5YRY2_q_4gw.text: Burgers are awesome, the buns really make the sandwich amazing. Cooks are really cool and care about how everything comes out. The family loves this place and the price is almost the same as fast food and only a million times better

v6m0G1sPYtXRiptSsXzKlA.text: Bomb ass hamburger.  No hamburger extraordinaire could go unsatisfied.  The burgers come on sesame submarine buns so they are quite bigger than most. The fries are a tad sloppy and they have the largest selection of craft soda I've ever seen.  If you ate everyday you'd be the biggest man on the planet, but a satisfied one at that.

bV-hK168kQ2czmVLeErYyw.text: holy crap, best burger alive!!  why have i not been to this place until today!!

3IZDaQSYn9H2MqL6aVI-Yw.text: Enjoyed my Italian sub so much while visiting AZ for the first time that we went back for lunch back-to-back days instead of trying out other places! Highlight of my trip.

TBZtfSnyEorIffOHy2vADw.text: Amazing burger, fantastic cheese curds, and soda, soda, and more soda. Fun place to come and try new flavors of soda.

nYF-YYieFyTrjm_KoxQhPQ.text: This little hole in the wall has delicious sandwiches! They have a huge collection of old school sodas and you can turn any one into a float.

OuiFPkofzlU8GIPJmh-Oyw.text: Great local place. Excellent burgers, sandwiches and sodas.

LgNOiNQ-qydlHDvt3XgsCQ.text: Came to Rocket Burger for take-out dinner, and the bbq pulled pork sandwich was absolutely delicious! By far one of the best burger places around!

QirqX9HgzuhC3xyDfjWMGw.text: Burger was delicious and fresh. Fries were well seasoned and crispy. Huge selection of bottled sodas from across the nation. Fun and good! Definitely coming back.

dUFVQK4gJM6XVs_hXHQfww.text: I was really impressed. Went to Paradise Valley Burger yesterday and this definitely compares. The price is very right, was 1/2 the cost of PVB and I think the quality of beef was on par. I really enjoyed the fries too. This is a really good classic burger.

7aKoGyzyc-xaxO9HFvM3fg.text: I love this place! They have amazing food with a HUGE selection of bottled sodas. I have not yet had anything that I didn't like. Awesome burgers and subs!

Z5SmYybraB7t8Jj88rxCVw.text: The burgers are great, a little greasy but delicious. Their's a great list of burgers to choose from. I try a new one every time I go and have never had one that I didn't like. If your new try the New Yorker or the Teriyaki Burger (be advised both are extremely messy but delicious). If you never have been here you should try it out. O yea, I forgot to mention their is like 500 different sodas to choose from!!!

PqZmrjRTOd28CqVewN0N3Q.text: Great food.  Great prices.  Hundreds of different kinds of sodas!  Had turkey, roast beef sandwiches - good.  Sandwiches are better toasted.  Chicago dog - yum!  Cheeseburger - ok

U1g5R58CWiq1NRmzzg8vjA.text: Went here with the family and it was delicious! Really love their selection of glass bottled sodas too! Picked up a few cases for a birthday party. We're definitely going to go back to eat and have a soda. BUT the ONLY thing we didn't like is the sticky floor.

ekzIvxTky3IMrBd03ofFmg.text: Was searching for a place to eat before a Halloween party. Saw rocket burger on the map and had heard someone mention them a week earlier. Ordered the "Eddie Lopez" double burger, had pastrami on top. Best damn burger.....not better than mine....but close :-D Fries suck but i just wont order them again. Service was good and the owner is there every time i go and is very friendly. Which is probably the reason for 5 stars, i don't hand them out like candy.... (Edit: Changed to 4 star, gotta keep the 5 stars exclusive) They have over 200 different sodas in the fridge which is pretty unique.  Ive been back 3 times and will keep going back.

ExhKaX5sc2ItujbOHCyekA.text: My head was spinning from the gourmet soda selection. It sort of overshadowed the food in this, my first trip. I had the Chicago style burger...the accoutrements were perfect, down to the last pickled relish drop. My only complaint is that the bun was sub-par...a nice, soft sesame seed bun would have made the burger more memorable. Burger to bun ratio was a little bit off. I will definitely return, and suggest you do the same!

xGTtHZ0LRID9VM_BbFAhKw.text: 5 for sure. I love this place. Found on Yelp. We are from Cleveland, Ohio & it's hard to find anything in Phoenix to fit our taste buds. Fortunately for us, we stumbled upon this place and decided to try it out. First off, I give them a 5 for customer service. They were so nice, helpful and accommodated to our every need. I am beyond picky. I ordered a gyro burger & I have to say it was one of the better gyro I've had. I also  ordered a plain hot dog but I  had to customize it with a few things just like I would back home (fries, bbq sauce & coleslaw) aka polish boy. And I'd have to say it was one of the best we've had. The coleslaw was perfect, bbq sauce was great & the fries, yummm. The only complaint I have is that I couldn't get a picture fast enough before we devoured our food.  We will definitely without a doubt be coming back.  Thank you so much Rocket burger for fulfilling our cravings.

GDELvDNJGYooK__jXu6foA.text: Best pulled pork i have found in Phoenix!! And love the drink selection found a huckleberry cream soda I drove 1200 miles to get last time!! New favorite! Can't wait to go back for another sandwich and after reading other reviews onion rings I think. Ugh but Which of the bagillion sodas to choose from??!? and def trying The ice cream..... Tomorrow for real.

Fb89LPwiMrc5745ePfxOeQ.text: For a local hamburger place this is it for me.  They have it all.  Great fries, wonderful burger, and good buns (and yes that's vital!).  Any soda you can think of!  GREAT PLACE!
